      "The Tuning Staff (A heavy brass rod topped with a glowing, vibrating filament)",
      "The Tuning Staff",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nBiomechanical: The Priest is a construct of dead bone and alien machinery. It does not breathe, making it immune to suffocation and gas-based attacks. It is completely immune to the Poison, Disease, Bleeding, Charmed, and Fear conditions.\n\nResonant Shielding (Aura): The Priest treats the battlefield like an instrument, maintaining the \"harmonic\" of its legion. The Priest projects a 30-foot aura of shimmering, vibrating air. All allied AakZad units within this aura (including the Priest) gain a +5 to their Armor Mitigation, and any Ranged weapon attacks (arrows, bolts, bullets) made against them automatically suffer Disadvantage as the kinetic barrier deflects the projectiles.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nDiscordant Hum(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Priest emits a frequency that thickens the air into a physical wall of vibrating pressure. Until the start of the Priest's next turn, any enemy that attempts to move closer to the Priest must pass a Willpower(7) test. On a failure, their movement is instantly halted, and they are violently pushed 10 feet backward by the sheer pressure of the sound, losing the remainder of their Movement for that turn.\n\nVoid-Siphon Surge(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): Triggering a Frequency Collapse, the Priest draws the lingering necrotic energy from the fallen. The Priest targets up to two destroyed AakZad units (or mundane corpses) within 60 feet, completely disintegrating them into dust. For each body siphoned, the Priest instantly heals 2d10 Wounds, and the damage of its next spell is increased by +15 Wounds as its staff overloads with void energy.\n\nVoid-Pulse Burst (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The terrifying culmination of the Priest's tuning. A 30-foot radius around a target point is hit with absolute silence and zero-gravity, momentarily lifting all enemies helplessly into the air. Make a Casting roll (+4 To-Cast) against all enemies in the zone. On a success, the vacuum violently collapses, slamming them into the earth. Targets take 3d10 + 35 Sonic Wounds, are knocked Prone, and gain 1 Stunned condition from massive internal organ damage."
    ],
    "imgSrc": ""
  },
