      "1",
      "Fused Vibrating Cleavers (Built into its forearms).",
      "The Fused Cleavers",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nBiomechanical: As a construct of dead tissue and alien machinery, the Titan does not breathe and has no vital organs. It is completely immune to the Poison, Disease, Bleeding, Charmed, and Fear conditions.\n\nResonant Output (High-Frequency Blades): The Titan's cleavers vibrate at a molecular level, powered by the glowing green filaments. Its Melee attacks naturally bypass the first 5 points of the target's Armor Mitigation. Furthermore, if the Giant starts its turn within the Resonant Shielding aura of an allied Crypt Priest, the Titan's Movement speed increases by +15Ft as the frequency overclocks its systems.\n\nFilament Reconstruction: The glowing green external tendons constantly work to keep the patchwork body together. At the start of its turn, if the Titan has not taken any Holy or Radiant Wounds in the previous round, it automatically heals 2d10 Wounds.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSickly-Green Cleave (Melee Cost: 3 Actions): The Giant swings its massive, vibrating arm-cleavers in a devastating 20-foot frontal arc, leaving a blinding trail of necrotic light. It makes a single To-Hit roll against the Defense of all targets in the area. Anyone hit takes normal 1d10 + 50 Wounds and is violently pushed 15 feet backward. The trail of green light lingers in the air until the Gaiant's next turn; any creature moving through that space automatically takes 2d10 Necrotic Wounds.\n\nVibrating Sunder (Melee Cost: 2 Action): The Giant brings a single cleaver straight down like a guillotine. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 2d10 + 50 Wounds. The sheer vibrating force of the impact forces the target to pass a severe Physique(11) test. On a failure, their physical weapon or shield is violently shattered from their hands and rendered useless for the rest of the encounter. If magical, then the shield is dropped and target must expend 1 action to retrieve it.\n\nOverclocked Thrash (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): This ability can only be triggered if the Giant is below half its maximum Wounds. The green filaments glow blindingly bright as the Giant overrides its own safety protocols. It makes two rapid Melee attacks (+3 To-Hit), but the violent exertion causes the Giant to automatically take 3d10 Wounds to its own health pool as its necrotized muscles begin to tear apart from the strain."
    ],
