      "Obsidian Greatshield",
      "Heavy Void-Blade",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nBiomechanical: The Phalanx-Guard is a construct of dead bone and alien machinery. It is immune to Poison, Disease, Bleeding, and Fear.\n\nRelentless Phalanx (Aura): The Guard provides +2 to Armor Mitigation for every other allied Aakzad unit within 5 feet of it.\n\nKinetic Redirection: When using a shield, a successful Defend roll against a melee attack allows the Guard to immediately push the attacker 5 feet back.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nShield Bash (1 Action): The Guard slams its obsidian shield into a target. Melee +6 To-Hit. If successful, target takes 1d10+10 Wounds and is knocked back 10 feet.\n\nDefensive Wall (1 Action): The Guard locks its stance. Until the start of its next turn, it gains +5 to its Defense and Mitigation, but its movement is reduced to 0.\n\nVoid-Cleave (2 Actions): The Guard swings its blade in a wide arc. All enemies within a 5-foot arc must pass an Agility test or take 2d10 Wounds, ignoring non-magical Armor."
