      "5-25",
      "Extruded Marrow-Plate, Vibration-Blade (Polearm or Sword)",
      "Vibration-Blade",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nBiomechanical: As a construct of dead tissue and alien machinery, the Warrior has no vital organs. It is completely immune to the Poison, Disease, Bleeding, Charmed, and Fear conditions.\n\nCalcified Geometry: The Warrior's armor is not worn; it is an extruded, living part of its skeleton. The Warrior is completely immune to any effects, spells, or attacks that \"Sunder\" or permanently reduce Armor Mitigation (such as the Wyvern's or Yeti's armor-breaking attacks).\n\nThe Resonant Drone (Aura): The signature terror of the legion. If a living creature starts its turn within 30 feet of three or more Aakzad Warriors, the collective humming physically weighs down the air. The target must pass a Willpower(7) test or suffer 1 Exhausted condition and permanently lose 1 Action for that turn as their heartbeat is forcibly slowed to match the machines' cold rhythm.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nMolecular Cleave (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Warrior strikes with its humming, serrated polearm. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 18 Wounds. Because the blade vibrates at a frequency that shatters molecular bonds, this attack automatically bypasses half of the target's Armor Mitigation.\n\nThermal Vent (Cost: 1 Action): The Warrior expands its chest plates, violently purging the buildup of heat from its internal biomechanical engine. All adjacent enemies within 5 feet must pass an Agility(7) test or take 2d10 Fire/Necrotic Wounds and be pushed 5 feet backward by the blast of oily steam. Using this ability also instantly cures the Warrior of any Cold/Ice-based Movement penalties or conditions.\n\nPhalanx Lock (Cost: 2 Actions): The Warrior interlocks its calcified geometry with an adjacent allied Aakzad unit, forming a seamless wall of vibrating bone. Until its next turn, the Warrior's Defense increases by +2, its Armor Mitigation increases by +5, and it gains a free Reaction to perform a Molecular Cleave against the first enemy that moves into its melee range."
    ],
