      "1 - 5",
      "Fused Harvesting Scythe, Necrotic-Tether Harpoons.",
      "lloy Scythe & Scuttling Claws",
      "Necrotic Harpoon. Hurls an alloy tether up to 60ft",
      "Passive Traits\nInertia Nullification: The AakZad completely ignores the laws of physical momentum. It can Disengage from melee combat, pivot, and move its full 30 Movement speed without triggering any free attacks of opportunity from engaged enemies. Furthermore, it takes zero falling damage, as its multi-jointed legs instantly absorb the kinetic impact.\n\nSpider-Cavalry: The AakZad treats vertical walls, sheer cliffs, and even ceilings as normal terrain. It can charge up the side of a watchtower or hang upside down from a cavern roof without needing to make any Agility checks to maintain its grip.\n\nSingular Consciousness: Because the rider and mount share a fused soul and a biomechanical nervous system, the AakZad is incredibly resistant to mental manipulation. It is completely immune to the Charmed and Fear conditions.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nReaping Charge (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The AakZad sprints in a straight line (along the ground, a wall, or a ceiling) up to its maximum Movement (60 ft), holding its fused scythe outward. It makes a single Melee attack (+3 To-Hit) that is compared against the Defense of every enemy in its path. Anyone hit takes normal 1d10 + 20 mounted Wounds and suffers 1 Bleeding condition.\n\nTether and Drag (Range Cost: 1 Action): The AakZad fires a harpoon connected to its glowing, necrotic nervous system. Make a Ranged attack (+2 To-Hit) against a target up to 60 feet away. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Wounds and the target is Grappled. On its next turn, if the tether isn't broken, the AakZad can use its movement to drag the grappled player across the battlefield with it.\n\nCore-Pulse Overload (Cost: 1 Action): The AakZad intentionally surges the violet/necrotic energy through its alloy ribcage, releasing a shockwave of localized radiation. All enemies within 10 feet must pass a severe Physique(10) test or take 2d10 + 15 Necrotic Wounds and gain 1 Exhausted condition as the alien energy saps their strength."
    ],
