      "usted Slaughterhouse Cleavers (Fused to its hands)",
      "The Rusted Cleavers",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Emerald Tether (Hyper-Regeneration): The glowing green vein of necromantic magic makes the Titan incredibly resilient. At the start of its turn, the Titan automatically heals 2d10 Wounds and re-knits any severed limbs or shattered joints. However, if the Titan took any Holy or Radiant Wounds in the previous round, the emerald light flickers and dies—this regeneration does not trigger for that turn.\n\nMonument of Dead Flesh: As a chaotic mass of necrotized muscle, the Titan has no vital organs. It is completely immune to the Poison, Disease, Bleeding, Charmed, and Fear conditions. Additionally, Piercing weapons (like arrows and rapiers) simply get stuck in its dead meat, dealing exactly half Wounds.\n\nSlaughterhouse Momentum: The Titan cannot be knocked Prone, Stunned, or forcefully moved by any physical attack. It marches forward with the terrifying, rhythmic inevitability of a machine.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nCharnel-House Cleave (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Titan swings its massive rusted cleavers in a brutal, sweeping 15-foot arc. It makes a single To-Hit roll (+2) against the Defense of all targets in the area. Anyone hit takes normal 1d10 + 45 Wounds and must pass a Physique(10) test. On a failure, the rusted, jagged metal inflicts 2 Bleeding conditions and 1 Disease condition (preventing them from receiving magical healing until cured).\n\nThe Butcher's Block (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A devastating single-target overhead strike. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful against a target that is currently Bleeding, this attack automatically gains Advantage and deals 2d10 + 45 Wounds, permanently denting their physical armor (reducing their Armor Mitigation by 2).\n\nNecrotic Rupture (Reaction): The Titan uses the magic holding it together as a weapon. If a player rolls a Critical Hit against the Titan, the blow severs a pocket of the pulsing green tether. The Titan instantly sprays highly pressurized, acidic embalming fluid in a 10-foot radius. All enemies in the radius must pass an Agility(11) test or take 2d10 Acid Wounds."
    ],
    "imgSrc": ""
