  {
    "values": [
      "Aethon, The World-Breaker",
      "Titanic",
      "Titan / Elemental",
      "",
      "Aethon is a \"Terra-Titan,\" standing nearly 100 feet tall as a walking mountain of jagged obsidian and glowing mantle. He wears no armor; the crust of the earth is his skin. Fused to his arm by cooled magma is a weapon that is actually the spire of a long-forgotten cathedral. Titans operate on a scale far beyond the Agility pillar—they do not dodge, they simply endure. Aethon views the world as unfinished clay, finding the \"order\" of the Celestials and the \"contracts\" of the Hells to be offensive clutter on his canvas. When Aethon moves, the map of the world literally changes.",
