      "The Earth's Crust (Skin), Magma-Fused Cathedral Spire (Improvised Titanic Weapon).",
      "Cathedral Spire Sweep",
      "Tectonic Boulder Toss. Rips chunks of the earth to hurl up to 200ft",
      "Passive Traits\nBeyond Agility (Endurance): Aethon operates on a scale where traditional combat rules fail. He is completely immune to the Prone, Stunned, Grappled, Bleeding, and Poison conditions. He cannot be moved, pushed, or knocked back by any force less than a localized meteor strike. Attacks against his Defense of 5 are practically guaranteed to hit; the challenge is overcoming his immense 80 Armor Mitigation.\n\nTerraforming Strides: Aethon does not walk on the battlefield; he is the battlefield. Every time he moves, the ground he steps on is permanently shattered and turned into a pool of molten rock. Any space Aethon walks through becomes severe difficult terrain that inflicts 2d10 Fire Wounds to anyone ending their turn there.\n\nThe World's Crust: Aethon is made of solid stone and magma. He takes only half Wounds from all physical slashing and piercing weapons, as swords and arrows simply chip away at his obsidian skin without hitting anything vital. He takes normal Wounds from massive blunt/crushing weapons, and double Wounds from high-tier Water/Ice magic.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nCathedral Sweep (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): Aethon sweeps the magma-fused cathedral spire across the battlefield in a massive 60-foot horizontal arc. He makes a single To-Hit roll (+8) against the Defense of every creature and structure in the arc. Anyone hit takes normal Wounds (120) and is violently thrown 30 feet backward. Any mortal-made buildings or walls caught in this sweep are instantly annihilated.\n\nTectonic Stomp (Cost: 1 Action): Aethon brings his foot down with apocalyptic force. All creatures within a 100-foot radius of Aethon must pass a severe Agility(14) test. On a failure, the localized earthquake knocks them Prone and inflicts 3d10 blunt Wounds. The violent shaking also immediately destroys all active localized spell-zones (like protective wards or magical walls) on the ground.\n\nMantle Eruption (Cost: 4 Actions): Aethon flexes his colossal musculature, intentionally cracking his own obsidian skin to release the pressurized, glowing mantle beneath. A 40-foot radius around him is flooded with a tidal wave of liquid magma. All creatures in the zone must pass a severe Physique(18) test. On a failure, they take 6d10 + 100 Fire Wounds and their non-magical armor/weapons instantly begin to melt (permanently losing half their effectiveness). On a success, they take half damage. Aethon himself heals 4d10 Wounds from the release of geological pressure."
    ],
    "imgSrc": ""
