      "None",
      "Hard Air & Living Lightning",
      "The High Winds",
      "Passive Traits\nDiamond Atmosphere (Hard Air): The Lord’s body is so densely compressed that it acts as the ultimate armor. Any physical Melee attack that fails to deal more than 10 Wounds (after mitigation) causes the attacker's weapon to violently shatter against the air pressure. Furthermore, it is completely immune to all non-magical Ranged attacks.\n\nLung-Collapsing Resonance: The Sky-Tearer's very presence is a weapon. Any enemy starting their turn within 40 feet of the Lord must pass a severe Physique(10) test. On a failure, they take 15 Sonic/Bludgeoning Wounds and suffer 1 Exhausted condition as the sheer barometric resonance collapses their lungs.\n\nMaster of the High Winds: Gravity in the Lord's presence is merely a suggestion. The entire battlefield is considered severe Difficult Terrain. Any flying creatures (other than the Lord) automatically have their flight speeds reduced to 0 and are violently grounded.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSupercell Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Lord swings an arm of violet lightning and compressed air. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 55 Bludgeoning/Lightning Wounds, and the target is knocked Stunned and blasted 20 feet backward.\n\nCelestial Frequency (Range Cost: 3 Actions): The Lord unleashes the ultimate high-altitude wind designed to strip skin from bone. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against all targets in a 60-foot radius. On a hit, targets take 4d10 + 35 Slashing Wounds. Any non-magical armor worn by the targets is permanently shredded and loses all Wound Mitigation.\n\nStratosphere Updraft (Cost: 1 Action): The Sky-Tearer reverses gravity in a localized column. It targets one enemy within 30 feet. The target must pass a severe Agility test or be instantly violently launched 60 feet straight up into the air. They will fall at the start of their next turn, taking massive falling damage and landing Prone."
    ],
    "imgSrc": ""
  },
  {
    "values": [
      "Air Elemental: The Gale-Wisp (Lesser)",
      "Medium",
      "Elemental",
      "",
      "A spinning vortex of pressurized atmosphere, visible only by the dust, leaves, and debris trapped within its cyclonic form. It hums with a high-pitched, whistling drone, like wind whipping through a narrow canyon. It doesn't move so much as it \"refracts,\" blurring across the battlefield in jagged, non-linear paths. To stand near one is to struggle for breath, as the creature literally pulls the oxygen into its own spinning core. These lesser anomalies act as hazards as much as active combatants.",
