      "1-4",
      "None",
      "Debris Buffet",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nRefracting Trajectory: The Gale-Wisp moves in unpredictable, jagged lines. It completely ignores difficult terrain, can move through spaces occupied by enemies, and never triggers free attacks of opportunity when leaving melee range.\n\nInsubstantial Anomaly: Because its Physical stat is exactly 0, normal weapons pass right through it. Any physical Melee or Ranged attack that successfully hits the Gale-Wisp automatically has its Wounds halved before mitigation is applied. Magical weapons deal full damage.\n\nOxygen Drain: The spinning core constantly pulls air inward. Any player character that ends their turn adjacent to one or more Gale-Wisps automatically loses 1 Focus point and suffers 2 Asphyxiation Wounds as the breath is stolen from their lungs.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nDebris Buffet (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The wisp lashes out with the rocks and twigs trapped in its cyclonic form. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 10 Wounds.\n\nSuffocating Envelopment (Cost: 2 Actions): The wisp attempts to occupy the exact same space as a target to suck the air from their mouth. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals no immediate Wounds, but the target is Silenced (cannot cast verbal spells) and takes 10 Asphyxiation Wounds at the start of their next turn unless they use an Action to step out of the wisp's space.\n\nErratic Burst (Cost: 1 Action): The wisp instantly shifts up to 20 feet in any direction without triggering any reactions, allowing it to swarm a backline caster or quickly retreat."
    ],
