      "1-3",
      "None",
      "Buffeting Winds & Static",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nAmorphous Vortex: The elemental is never truly solid. It can move freely through enemy spaces and squeeze through cracks or keyholes as narrow as 1 inch without penalty. Furthermore, all physical Melee attacks made against the elemental suffer Disadvantage.\n\nHigh-Speed Harassment: Flowing like the wind, the Air Elemental never provokes free attacks of opportunity when moving out of melee range. Its presence automatically extinguishes all non-magical flames (torches, campfires) within 30 feet.\n\nWind Deflection: The swirling zephyr protects it from ranged fire. Standard projectiles (arrows, bolts, throwing axes) are instantly blown off course and automatically done with Disadvantage when attempting To-Hit.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nThundercloud Buffet (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The elemental slams into a target with a wall of dense, static-charged air. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Bludgeoning/Lightning Wounds, and the target must pass a Physique(5) test or be violently pushed 15 feet straight backward.\n\nLocalized Cyclone (Cost: 2 Actions): The elemental spins at terrifying speeds, creating a localized tornado. It targets a 15-foot radius. Every enemy in the zone must pass an Agility(9) test. Those who fail take 2d10 + 20 Wounds and are violently thrown 20 feet in a random direction (potentially off cliffs or into allies), landing Prone.\n\nSuffocating Vacuum (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The elemental pulls the oxygen directly out of a target's lungs. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Wounds, and the target is instantly Silenced (unable to speak or cast verbal spells) for 1 round as they gasp for air."
    ],
