      "Air Elemental: The Sky-Reaper",
      "Giant",
      "Elemental",
      "",
      "A towering column of storm-fronts and grinding tectonic air, standing between 20 and 30 feet tall. It appears as a swirling nebulous of bruised clouds shot through with jagged internal lightning. Its \"face\" is a hollow vacuum, and its whip-like funnel arms can pick up a stone house as easily as a toy. Ancient and aloof, with a booming voice like distant thunder, it doesn't just occupy space—it dominates it with sheer atmospheric pressure. Summoned only by the most powerful archmages, to stand before a Sky-Reaper is to feel the weight of the entire sky pressing down on your shoulders.",
