      "Whip-Like Funnels",
      "Jagged Sheet Lightning",
      "Passive Traits\nAtmospheric Lockdown: The Sky-Reaper dominates the space around it. The area within 30 feet of the elemental is considered severe Difficult Terrain due to hurricane-force winds. Any enemy that ends their turn within this radius must pass a Physique(10) test or take 10 Bludgeoning Wounds from the crushing barometric pressure and flying debris.\n\nAmorphous Storm-Front: The creature is a living cloud. It is completely immune to the Prone, Grappled, and Bleeding conditions. Additionally, standard Ranged physical attacks (arrows, thrown weapons) are instantly shredded by the winds, automatically dealing 0 Wounds.\n\nThe Eye of the Storm: While the outer winds pulverize melee attackers, the center is a vacuum. The Sky-Reaper never suffers penalties or Disadvantage when making Ranged lightning attacks against distant targets, even if it is currently engaged in melee combat.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nPulverizing Vortex (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The elemental grinds the air around its base. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) against all targets within 15 feet. If successful, targets take half Wounds, 1d10 +20 and are violently sucked 10 feet closer to the elemental, ensuring they cannot escape the Atmospheric Lockdown.\n\nTectonic Funnel-Whip (Melee Cost: 2 Action): It lashes out with a funnel capable of lifting a stone house. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) against a single target. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 40 Wounds. The target is hurled 30 feet straight up into the air and immediately takes standard falling damage(3d10) when they hit the ground, landing Prone.\n\nJagged Internal Lightning(TN11) (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Sky-Reaper targets the casters or archers hiding outside its wind zone. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against up to two distant targets. On a hit, targets take 3d10 + 25 Lightning Wounds and gain 1 Stunned condition from the deafening thunderclap."
