      "Special Abilities",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nLuminous Platinum Presence: Because the Archangel's body is composed of flawless, dense light, it cannot be harmed by mundane means. It is completely immune to all non-magical physical weapons. Even magical physical weapons deal only half Wounds. It is immune to the Grappled, Prone, Poison, Disease, and Bleeding conditions.\n\nStained-Glass Refraction: The Archangel's four wings constantly bend the ambient light. Any enemy that attempts to make a Ranged attack against the Archangel from further than 15 feet away suffers Disadvantage, as the geometric light patterns create blinding optical illusions.\n\nThe Weight of Purity: The Archangel's very existence suppresses the unholy. Any Undead or Daemon that starts its turn within 40 feet of the Archangel automatically suffers 1d10 Radiant Wounds and loses 1 Action for that turn as their dark magic violently boils inside them.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nDecree of Subjugation (Cost: 2 Actions): The Archangel speaks a single, vibrating syllable of cosmic law. All enemies within a 60-foot radius must pass a severe Willpower(15) test. On a failure, their souls are forced into submission: they take 60 Sonic/Radiant Wounds, are instantly knocked Prone, and cannot spend Actions to stand back up until the Archangel moves or ends the Decree on a subsequent turn.\n\nDecree of Eradication(TN11) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Archangel points a single, flawless finger at a target within 80 feet and speaks a word of unmaking. Make a Casting roll (+8 To-Cast). If successful, it deals 2d10 + 60 Radiant Wounds. This attack completely ignores all Armor Mitigation and automatically destroys any active magical spell - shields, walls, or wards the target is hiding behind.\n\nDecree of Silence(TN8) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Archangel dictates the rules of engagement. Make a Casting roll (+8 To-Cast) against a target within 60 feet. On a success, the target is completely Silenced and muted. They cannot cast spells with verbal components, communicate with their team, or use any abilities that require speech or sound until they pass a Willpower(11) test at the end of their turn to break the holy lock."
