      "None. It incinerates anything it touches",
      "Obsidian Claws & Jaws",
      "Pitch-Black Fire",
      "Passive Traits\nStorm of White Ash: The dragon is perpetually wreathed in a blinding, superheated ash storm. Any non-magical Ranged attacks targeting the dragon automatically suffer Disadvantage. Furthermore, any enemy starting their turn within 30 feet of the beast takes 1d10 Fire Wounds and must pass a Physique(8) test or suffer 1 Exhausted condition from choking on the air.\n\nObsidian Siege Plating: Its scales shatter standard weapons on impact. If a physical Melee attack fails to beat the dragon's Defense of 9 or fails to deal more than 30 Wounds (after mitigation), the attacker's weapon violently shatters, becoming permanently destroyed (magical weapons lose 1 tier of effectiveness instead).\n\nIncinerate the Weave: The dragon's internal heat destroys latent magic. Any player attempting to cast a spell within 60 feet of the dragon must spend an additional Focus point (or take 10 Fire Wounds) simply to force the magic to manifest through the superheated air.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nAsh-Blight Breath (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The dragon unhinges its jaws, unleashing a terrifying vortex of pitch-black, magic-consuming fire. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against a 60-foot cone. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 40 Fire/Necrotic Wounds. Additionally, the black fire instantly incinerates any active magical buffs, shields, or enchantments on the targets, stripping them completely.\n\nHurricane Wings (Range Cost: 1 Action): The dragon beats its vast, powerfully corded wings, generating a blast of superheated wind. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against all enemies in a 40-foot frontal arc. On a hit, targets take half Wounds 1d10 + 20 and are violently blown 30 feet backward, landing Prone.\n\nMolten Crush (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The dragon brings its massive, obsidian-plated mass down on a target. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 60 Wounds. If the target is currently Prone, the sheer weight ignores 50% of the target's Armor Mitigation."
