      "Banshee: The Keening Void",
      "Medium",
      "Undead / Incorporeal",
      "",
      "\"The wind does not howl in these moors; it weeps. And when that weeping turns to a rhythmic, soul-piercing keening, you do not run. To hear the Banshee is to know that your thread has already been cut.\" A Banshee appears as a luminous, ethereal silhouette of a woman draped in tattered burial silks that float as if submerged in water. Her skin is the color of bruised moonlight, stretched thin over a face frozen in agonizing sorrow. Her sunken, lidless eyes are voids of swirling gray mist, and her hair flows like white stringy smoke, defying gravity. When she prepares to strike, her jaw unhinges to reveal a huge, gaping mouth—a dark abyss from which her supernatural voice erupts.",
