      "Tattered, floating burial silks.",
      "None",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nEthereal Silks: As an incorporeal entity, the Banshee takes only half Wounds from all non-magical physical weapons. She is completely immune to the Grappled, Prone, Bleeding, Poison, and Disease conditions. She can drift through solid stone walls, locked doors, and other creatures as if they were mist.\n\nThe Cut Thread: The Banshee knows whose time has come. At the start of the encounter, the Banshee fixates on the party member with the lowest current Wounds. All of her To-Cast rolls against that specific target automatically gain Advantage, and she completely ignores any cover or line-of-sight penalties when targeting them.\n\nEchoes of Sorrow: Because her body is made of \"bruised moonlight\" and mist, any physical Melee attack that successfully strikes her causes the attacker's weapon to pass through her freezing form. The attacker immediately takes 1d10 Cold Wounds from the chilling contact.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nThe Soul-Piercing Keening(TN11) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Banshee's jaw unhinges into a dark abyss, unleashing a rhythmic, devastating shriek in a 40-foot cone. Make a Casting roll (+6 To-Cast) against all enemies in the area. On a success, targets take 2d10 + 30 Sonic/Necrotic Wounds. They must also pass a Willpower(12) test or suffer 1 Exhausted condition and become Frightened (unable to willingly move closer to her) as their soul trembles.\n\nGrasp of the Grave (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Banshee reaches out a translucent, glowing hand toward a target within 30 feet. Make a Casting roll (+6 To-Cast). If successful, it deals 40 Necrotic Wounds. The target's Movement is instantly halved for their next turn as the ethereal cold seeps into their marrow.\n\nMist-Step Fade (Cost: 1 Action): Driven by her fractured focus, the Banshee instantly dissolves into stringy, gray smoke. She immediately Disengages from all melee combat without triggering any free attacks and teleports up to 30 feet away to an unoccupied space she can see, resetting her position to continue her mournful weeping from afar."
    ],
