      "1-2",
      "None",
      "Toxic Jaws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nEight-Legged Scuttler: The Basilisk treats completely vertical cavern walls and ceilings as normal terrain. It can climb and hang upside down effortlessly without making any Agility checks, making it a terrifying ambush predator from above.\n\nOily, Toxic Sheen: The Basilisk's mottled green scales secrete a highly corrosive poison. Any time an attacker successfully hits the Basilisk with a physical melee weapon, the attacker must pass an Agility(7) test or immediately take 1d10 Acid Wounds as the toxic sheen splashes back onto them.\n\nAvert Your Eyes: At the start of their turn, any player within 40 feet of the Basilisk can declare they are \"Averting their Eyes.\" Doing so gives them automatic Disadvantage on all To-Hit and To-Cast rolls against the Basilisk for that round, but completely immunizes them from the beast's Flesh to Flint ability.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nFlesh to Flint(TN9) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Basilisk locks its pale, glowing yellow eyes onto a target within 40 feet who has not averted their eyes. Make a Casting roll (+4 To-Cast). If successful, it deals 25 Transmutation Wounds as the victim's blood turns to silt. The target must pass a severe Willpower(12) test. On a failure, they are inflicted with the Petrifying condition (their Movement is permanently reduced to 0, and they lose 1 Action per turn). If a target with the Petrifying condition fails a second Willpower test on a subsequent turn, they are permanently turned to solid stone until magically cured.\n\nChemical Plume(TN10) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Basilisk exhales a searing cloud of chemical breath in a 15-foot cone at ankle-level. All enemies in the area must pass a Physique(11) test. On a failure, they take 2d10 + 25 Acid/Poison Wounds, gain 1 Poison condition, and are temporarily Blinded for their next turn as the fumes burn their eyes.\n\nAmbush Snap (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A brutal, lunging bite used when dropping from the ceiling. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 20 Wounds and the target is Grappled in the Basilisk's heavy jaws, unable to move away from the creature's deadly gaze on their next turn."
    ],
