      "Clattering Bone Staff, Molted Furs, Blood-Moon Charms",
      "Bone Staff",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nRot of the Woods (Aura): Fungi, grasping roots, and mold rapidly bloom wherever the Shaman's hooves touch the earth. The ground within a 20-foot radius of the Shaman is permanently considered Difficult Terrain for all non-Beastman creatures, halving their Movement speed and forcing Agility tests to sprint.\n\nThe Old Winds (Messy Magic): The Shaman's magic is violently unfiltered. Whenever the Shaman successfully casts a spell, the surrounding environment reacts; the sudden change in atmospheric pressure causes any enemy within 10 feet of the Shaman to automatically take 1d10 blunt Wounds from churning earth, flying debris, and ozone backlash.\n\nPredator's Seizure: Seizing magic like a wolf catching prey, the Shaman is highly opportunistic. The Shaman automatically gains Advantage on all Casting To-Hit rolls against targets that are currently suffering from the Blinded, Prone, or Poison conditions.\n\nAction-Based Abilities \nBlood-Moon Spores(TN9) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Shaman crushes a bone charm, releasing a 20-foot cloud of toxic, rust-colored spores up to 40 feet away. The cloud obscures all vision (blocking line-of-sight) and persists until the Shaman's next turn. Any enemy entering or starting their turn in the cloud must pass a Physique(9) test or become Blinded and suffer 1 Poison condition.\n\nGrasping Roots(TN8) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Shaman slams its staff into the dirt. Make a Casting roll (+6 To-Cast) against a target within 50 feet. If successful, animated, rotting vines erupt from the soil, dealing 2d10 + 30 Nature Wounds. The target is Grappled (Movement 0) and perfectly set up for the Beastman frontline.\n\nSacrifice and Surge(TN11) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Shaman's desperate, spiteful trump card. The Shaman draws on the life force of an adjacent allied Beastman (or nearby living flora), dealing 20 Wounds to them to heal itself for 20 Wounds. The Shaman then immediately unleashes a devastating Lightning Call in a 40-foot line. Make a Casting roll (+6 To-Cast) against all targets in the line. On a success, it deals an overcharged 3d10 + 30 Lightning Wounds."
