      "10-30",
      "Scavenged Iron Plate, Jagged Rusted Cleaver, Throwing Hatchet.",
      "Jagged Cleaver",
      "Hurled Hatchet",
      "Passive Traits \nThe Herd Mentality: Beastmen draw terrifying confidence from the smell of their kin's sweat and the sound of the Bray-horn. If a Beastman Warrior starts its turn within 15 feet of at least two other conscious Beastmen, it gains Advantage on all Willpower tests and its Melee attacks deal an additional +3 Wounds as the \"meat-grinder\" engages.\n\nRelentless Pursuit (Scent of Blood): Once they catch a scent, they will run until their lungs burn. If any enemy within 60 feet is currently suffering from a Bleeding condition, the Beastman's Movement speed increases by +15Ft when moving directly toward that target, and it completely ignores all Movement penalties from Difficult Terrain during the chase.\n\nDespiser of Stone: Taking perverse joy in destroying civilization, the Beastman's attacks deal double Wounds to any physical structures, barricades, magical stone walls, and constructs (like Golems). They will aggressively sunder player shields if given the chance.\n\nAction-Based Abilities \nThe Crush (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Beastman launches itself with the explosive energy of a cornered predator. It moves up to its Movement speed in a straight line and makes a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If it hits, the target takes 1d10 + 18 Wounds and must pass a Physique(9) test or be violently knocked Prone by the sheer mass of the charge.\n\nJagged Butcher (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A brutal, wild swing with its rusted cleaver. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If this attack hits a target that is currently Prone, it automatically inflicts 1 Bleeding condition as the jagged iron tears through armor.\n\nWall of Noise (Cost: 1 Action): The Beastman beats its chest and unleashes a terrifying, bleating roar. It chooses one allied Beastman within 30 feet. That ally immediately gets to use its Reaction to move 15 feet toward the nearest bleeding or fleeing enemy, keeping the relentless pressure on the party."
    ],
