  {
    "values": [
      "Beastman: Greater Gore Beast",
      "Giant",
      "Aberration / Monstrosity",
      "",
      "\"It does not simply eat; it consumes the very concept of life. When you see the multiple limbs threshing the air and the ribcage that splits open like a second, jagged mouth, you realize that nature didn't create this—it's a wound in reality that has learned how to walk.\" The Gore Beast is a towering, nightmarish fusion of muscle and bone, standing nearly 15 feet tall. Its body is a knotted mass of scarred, flayed flesh. It possesses four primary limbs: two massive, trunk-like arms ending in obsidian claws, and two smaller, sickle-like appendages used for delicate evisceration. Its head is a terrifying eyeless skull-dome with a vertical maw. Most unsettling is its hollow thoracic cavity—a jagged \"rib-gate\" that clamps shut to pull victims into its internal digestive acidic pits.",
