      "None",
      "Obsidian Trunks & Sickles",
      "Bone Shrapnel",
      "Passive Traits \nWound in Reality: The Gore Beast does not belong in this world, and the universe passively degrades around it. Any living creature that starts its turn within 20 feet of the Gore Beast regain Wounds by half whether by magical, potion or physical means.\n\nFlayed Titan Anatomy: Because its body is a chaotic, stitched-together mass of externalized organs and scarred meat, the Gore Beast has no discernible weak points. It is completely immune to Critical Hits (they deal normal damage) and the Bleeding condition.\n\nJagged Thorax (Reactive Hunger): The split, hollow ribcage operates with an autonomous, predatory reflex completely separate from the beast's main skull. Whenever an enemy successfully lands a Melee attack against the Gore Beast from an adjacent space, the jagged, bone-needle ribs violently snap shut on the attacker's overextended weapon or arm. The attacker automatically suffers 1d10 Piercing/Acid Wounds from the crunching bone and corrosive internal bile. This makes close-quarters combat against the beast an absolute, unavoidable meat-grinder.\n\nAction-Based Abilities \nSickle Evisceration (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The beast lashes out with its smaller, razor-sharp secondary arms. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals half Wounds 1d10 + 30 but automatically severs the straps of the target's armor, permanently reducing their Armor Mitigation by 2.\n\nObsidian Trunk Smash (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The beast brings its massive primary arms down like falling trees. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 2d10 + 60 Wounds and the target is violently knocked Prone and Stunned for 1 round.\n\nSeismic Meat-Stomp (melee Cost: 3 Actions): The Gore Beast lifts a massive, scarred foot and drives it into the earth with terrifying force. A 20-foot radius around the Beast violently shatters. All enemies in the area must pass a severe Agility(12) test. On a failure, they take 3d10 + 30 Bludgeoning Wounds and are violently knocked Prone. Any target that is already Prone before the stomp takes double Wounds as they are crushed into the dirt like an insect.\n\nReality Vomit (Range Cost: 2 Actions): Utilizing its Ranged To-Hit (+4), the beast forcefully expels a stream of anti-life acid from its primary maw up to 40 feet away. Targets hit take 3d10 + 20 Acid Wounds and gain 2 Poison conditions."
    ],
