      "None",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits \nThe Anti-Magic Cone: The Eye-Tyrant's massive central eye projects a 60-foot cone of suppressed reality. At the start of its turn, it decides which direction the eye faces. Any player inside that cone is completely Silenced (cannot cast spells), and any active magical buffs, auras, or magical weapon properties they possess are temporarily disabled while they remain in the cone.\n\n360-Degree Paranoia: Because of its writhing crown of eyestalks, the Tyrant can never be caught off guard. It is completely immune to the Blinded condition, cannot be Flanked by melee attackers, and completely negates any Advantage players might gain from attacking out of Stealth.\n\nXenophobic Levitation: The Eye-Tyrant never touches the dirt of the lesser races. It is immune to all ground-based traps, spells, and Difficult Terrain. Furthermore, it takes zero Wounds from falling, simply arresting its momentum telekinetically.\n\nAction-Based Abilities \nRay of Exhaustion(TN6) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Tyrant targets the party's physical powerhouse. Make a Casting roll (+4 To-Cast) against a target within 60 feet. On a hit, it deals no Wounds, but the target instantly gains 2 Exhausted conditions and loses half their Movement on their next turn as the ray saps their will to live.\n\nTelekinetic Reposition(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Tyrant takes control of the battlefield. It targets one enemy within 60 feet. The target must pass a Willpower(9) test or be violently thrown 20 feet in any direction the Tyrant chooses (including into hazards or directly out of melee range), taking 1d10 + 15 blunt Wounds upon landing.\n\nDisintegration Beam(TN12) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The ultimate punisher. Make a Casting roll (+4 To-Cast) against a single target within 40 feet. If successful, it deals an agonizing 3d10 + 40 Aberrant Wounds. If this attack misses, or if the target uses a physical shield/barricade to block it, the object used as cover is instantly reduced to fine gray dust."
    ],
