      "Pneumatic Forge-Hammer, Shoulder-Mounted Magma Mortar, Volcanic Exoskeleton",
      "Pneumatic Forge-Hammer",
      "Voild-Rifle",
      "Passive Traits\nCruel Efficiency: The Overseer demands perfection from his forces. If an allied Bin Uluhm Dwarf or slave within 30 feet misses an attack, the Overseer can instantly use his Reaction to vent a jet of scalding steam at them, dealing 5 Fire Wounds to the ally but forcing the attack to be rerolled with Advantage.\n\nVolcanic Exoskeleton: The Overseer is immune to the Burning and Poisoned conditions. Furthermore, because he is mostly encased in machinery, any Critical Hit scored against him by a physical weapon only deals normal Wounds, as the attacker merely severs a pneumatic hose or dents a cog rather than striking a vital organ.\n\nVolatile Munitions: All of the Overseer's weapons are laced with explosive black-powder or magma. His Melee and Ranged attacks completely ignore physical shields, blasting right through the block and dealing full Wounds to the defender.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nPneumatic Overdrive (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Overseer triggers the pistons in his hammer for a devastating strike. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 30 Wounds, and the sheer kinetic force knocks the target 10 feet backward and inflicts 1 Stunned condition from the concussive shockwave.\n\nDeploy Crawling Mine (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Overseer throws a mechanized, spider-like bomb onto the battlefield. The Mine has 10 Hit Points and acts on Initiative Count 0. It will scurry up to 30 feet toward the nearest player and detonate, dealing 2d10 + 20 Fire/Piercing Wounds to everyone in a 10-foot radius.\n\nMagma Mortar (Range Cost: 2 Actions): He fires a glob of cooling magma from his shoulder cannon. Make a Ranged attack (+3 To-Hit) against a target within 40 feet. On a hit, it deals 2d10 + 25 Fire Wounds, and the target's Movement is halved on their next turn as the magma rapidly hardens into heavy slag around their boots."
    ],
