    "values": [
      "Black Dragon: The Rot-Lord",
      "Giant",
      "Dragon / Monstrosity",
      "",
      "The Black Dragon is visually distinct for its sunken, skull-like face. Its skin has receded around its snout, giving it a permanent, skeletal grin. Its horns curve forward like a crown of blackened bone, and its scales are dull, matte black, designed to absorb the dim light of the marsh. They are the masters of ambushes. A Black Dragon doesn't roar a challenge; it waits submerged in a pool of acid-filled muck, breathing through its nostrils like a crocodile, until its prey is waist-deep. They find joy in the \"Slow Kill,\" often letting a victim crawl away just so they can track the scent of their melting flesh through the trees.",
      "5",
      "12",
