    "values": [
      "Blight-Spider: The Web-Stitcher",
      "Large",
      "Beast / Monstrosity",
      "",
      "A Blight-Spider is roughly the size of a carriage, but its silhouette is jagged and uneven. It reinforces its own exoskeleton by \"stitching\" pieces of rotted wood, rusted metal, and the bones of past victims to its legs using a thick, oily black silk. This makes it look like a moving pile of forest detritus—until its eight glowing, multi-faceted eyes snap open. They spin a three-dimensional lattice of toxic tripwires through the air and are masters of agility, dropping from the canopy to snatch prey before vanishing back into the leaves. They do not eat immediately; they paralyze and stitch their victims to the trees to be slowly digested by black sap.",
