      "None",
      "Toxic Mandibles & Barbed Legs",
      "Oily Black Silk. Shoots web projectiles up to 60ft",
      "Passive Traits \nDetritus Camouflage: As long as the Blight-Spider remains motionless, it is indistinguishable from a pile of dead wood, rusted scrap, and forest rot. It automatically gains Advantage on any Stealth checks to initiate an ambush, and enemies cannot target it from afar until it moves or attacks.\n\n3D Toxic Lattice: The spider constantly trails invisible, toxic tripwires. Any area within 30 feet of the spider (including the air above it) is considered a hazard. If an enemy moves more than 10 feet during their turn within this area, they snap a tripwire and must pass an Agility(9) test or immediately take 1d10 Acid/Poison Wounds and have their Movement halted for the rest of that turn.\n\nMaster of the Canopy: The spider completely ignores all difficult terrain and vertical climbing penalties. When it uses a Move action to climb up a wall or tree, it instantly Disengages from all melee combat without triggering any free attacks of opportunity.\n\nAction-Based Abilities \nCanopy Snatch (Range Cost: 1 Action): The spider drops from above or fires a thick tether of oily silk. Make a Ranged attack (+3 To-Hit) against a target within 40 feet. If successful, the target takes 15 Wounds and is Grappled. The spider can immediately pull the grappled target 20 feet toward itself or hoist them into the air.\n\nBlack-Sap Bite (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): A vicious, venomous strike from its mandibles. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 25 Wounds, and the target must pass a severe Physique(10) test. On a failure, the black sap enters their bloodstream, inflicting the Stunned and Poisoned conditions for 1 round.\n\nThe Macabre Stitch (Cost: 1 Action): The spider rapidly binds a Stunned or Grappled target to the environment. The target is violently pinned to a nearby tree, wall, or the floor with oily black silk. While stitched, the target cannot take any Physical or Agility actions and automatically suffers 2d10 Acid Wounds at the start of each of their turns as the black sap begins to digest them alive. They (or an ally) must spend an Action and pass a Physique(9) test to rip the silk away."
    ],
