      "A massive hoard buried deep beneath the desert",
      "The Lightning Horn & Claws",
      "Chain Lightning",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Living Lightning Rod: Static electricity constantly hums through the dragon's body. Any time a player successfully hits the Blue Dragon with a metal Melee weapon, the kinetic impact discharges the static, instantly dealing 1d10 Lightning Wounds back to the attacker.\n\nDune Ambusher: When buried beneath the sand, the dragon is entirely undetectable by non-magical means. It automatically gains Advantage on its Initiative roll. When it erupts from the sand, the superheated lightning fuses the ground in a 40-foot radius into jagged glass, turning the battlefield into severe Difficult Terrain that causes Bleed 1d10 damage if fallen upon.\n\nThe Sapphire Tribute: The dragon's immense ego is its only real weakness. As an Action, a player can hold up a gemstone of significant value and grovel. The dragon must pass a Willpower test; if it fails, its ego wins out, and it will spend its next turn demanding the gem and conversing rather than attacking that specific player. Sapphires impose Disadvantage on the dragon's Willpower test to resist.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nEruption of the Storm (Melee Cost: 3 Actions): The dragon bursts from its sandy grave. It makes a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) against every target within a 30-foot radius. On a hit, targets take 1d10 + 60 Wounds, are violently thrown 20 feet backward, and are knocked Prone amidst the newly formed glass.\n\nMidnight Sky Beam (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The dragon lowers its massive horn and unleashes a concentrated beam of static energy. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against a 100-foot line. On a hit, it deals 4d10 + 30 Lightning Wounds, and targets are completely Deafened and Stunned for 1 round from the thunderclap.\n\nArrogant Pin (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The dragon slams a claw down on a single target to demand its tribute. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals half Wounds 1d10 + 30, but the target is Grappled and Restrained under the sheer weight of the beast, completely unable to move until the dragon lifts its claw."
    ],
