    "values": [
      "Boar (Razorgor): The Living Battering Ram",
      "Large",
      "Beast / Monstrosity",
      "",
      "Twisted by the same dark energies that birthed the Beastmen, these boars are unnaturally large—some standing as tall as a pony at the shoulder. Their hides are thick as cured leather, often embedded with rusted spear tips and broken arrows from failed hunts. They don't just bite; they impact. A charging boar carries enough kinetic energy to shatter shields and snap the legs of horses. They are notoriously difficult to kill, refusing to acknowledge pain until their heart finally stops beating. The Beastmen use them as living line-breakers to shatter defensive formations.",
      "6",
      "5",
