      "1-5",
      "Barding if Mount",
      "Rusted Tusks & Trampling Hooves",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nUnstoppable Momentum: Once the Razorgor begins its gallop, it cannot easily turn. If it moves more than 15 feet in a straight line during its turn, it can freely move through spaces occupied by other creatures (friend or foe). Any creature it passes through must pass an Agility(6) test or take 1d10 Bludgeoning Wounds and be knocked Prone.\n\nDeadened Nerves: The boar simply refuses to acknowledge pain. It is completely immune to the Stunned and Exhausted conditions. Furthermore, when its Wounds are reduced to 0, its heart stops, but its adrenaline carries it forward—it immediately takes one final, full turn before dropping dead.\n\nThe Line Breaker: Designed to shatter formations, the Razorgor deals double Wounds to physical shields, barricades, and magical walls. It completely ignores any defensive bonuses a player might receive from standing in a \"Shield Wall\" or defensive formation.\n\nAction-Based Abilities \nBattering Ram Charge (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The boar lowers its head and explodes forward. It moves up to its maximum Movement (45 feet) in a straight line and makes a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 2d10 + 20 Wounds, permanently shatters the target's shield (if equipped), and violently knocks them 10 feet backward and Prone.\n\nGutting Tusk (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A brutal, upward thrust with its massive rusted tusks. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If this attack hits a target that is currently Prone, it automatically inflicts 1 Bleeding condition as the tusk tears through armor and flesh.\n\nFrenzied Thrash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): If cornered or surrounded, the boar violently thrashes its massive head from side to side. It makes a single Melee attack (+3 To-Hit) against the Defense of all enemies within 5 feet. Anyone hit takes half Wounds 1d10 + 10 and is pushed 5 feet away."
    ],
