      "None",
      "Suction-Cup Tentacles",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nPerfect Peat Camouflage: As long as the Bog Octopus is submerged in mud or resting against a cypress tree, it is entirely indistinguishable from the environment. It automatically gains Advantage on Stealth checks. If it attacks a target who has not detected it, that attack gains Advantage and automatically Grapples the target on a hit.\n\nParalytic Mucus: The creature's skin constantly secretes a numbing slime. Any time an enemy successfully hits the Bog Octopus with an unarmed strike, or starts their turn Grappled by it, the enemy must pass a Physique(12) test or suffer 1 Poison condition and lose half their Movement speed as their limbs go numb.\n\nAnaerobic Drag (Drown Mechanics): The Silt Lurker does not fight fair. If the Octopus has a target Grappled, it can use its innate Movement to drag that target directly underwater or deep into the thick mud. Once submerged, the target cannot speak or cast spells with verbal components, and they immediately begin suffering from Drowning/Suffocation rules.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nEruption of Suction Cups (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Octopus bursts from concealment, lashing out with massive tentacles. It makes a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) against up to two targets within 15 feet. If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 50 Wounds, and the targets are violently pulled into spaces adjacent to the Octopus and Grappled.\n\nMarinate the Prey (Range Cost: 1 Action): The Octopus forcefully expels a thick glob of paralytic mucus at a target within 30 feet. Make a Ranged attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 +20 Acid/Poison Wounds, and the target is completely Stunned for 1 round as their nervous system locks up.\n\nDrag to the Depths (Cost: 1 Action): The Octopus tightens its grip on a Grappled target and violently crushes them. The target automatically takes 2d10 + 30 Bludgeoning Wounds. If the Octopus and the target are submerged in the mud/water, the target instantly loses 1 additional round of their held breath (accelerating the drowning process)."
    ],
