    "values": [
      "Bog-Witch (Swamp Hag)",
      "Small",
      "Fey / Humanoid",
      "",
      "The Swamp Hag is a creature of stagnant rot and ancient, bitter magic, born when a forest spirit is completely corrupted by the runoff of dark rituals or a plague-ridden graveyard. Standing barely four feet tall, she is a twisted, hunched figure draped in sodden moss and discarded human hair. Her skin is the color of bruised eggplant, feeling like wet, cured leather. Instead of eyes, two glowing pits of yellow bile see perfectly through the thickest bog mists. She carries a gnarled staff of petrified driftwood, and the air around her hums with the sickening buzzing of thousands of carrion flies.",
      "2",
