      "Petrified Driftwood Staff, Sodden Moss Rags",
      "Driftwood Staff",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits \nBile-Sight: The Swamp Hag's glowing yellow eye-pits perceive reality flawlessly. She completely ignores all cover penalties from fog, smoke, and magical darkness. She is immune to the Blinded condition and cannot be ambushed.\n\nThe Carrion Halo: Thousands of flies constantly swarm around the Hag. Any ranged attacks (arrows, bolts, thrown weapons) made against her from further than 15 feet away automatically suffer Disadvantage, as the dense buzzing cloud throws off aim and obscures her frail silhouette.\n\nAura of Stagnant Rot: The graveyard magic that birthed her actively suppresses life. Any magical healing cast by players within 30 feet of the Hag is automatically halved (rounded down) as the rot absorbs the ambient holy energy.\n\nAction-Based Abilities \nBlighted Hex(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Hag points a rotting finger and whispers an ancient curse. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit) against a target within 40 feet. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 25 Necrotic Wounds, and the target must pass a Willpower test or suffer 1 Exhausted condition as their life force is sapped.\n\nGraveyard Runoff(TN9) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Hag strikes her driftwood staff against the ground, causing the earth in a 20-foot radius to liquefy into foul, acidic muck. The area becomes permanent Difficult Terrain. Any enemy that ends their turn in the muck takes 2d10 + 25 Acid Wounds and gains 1 Poison condition.\n\nSwarm Command (Cost: 1 Action): The Hag commands her carrion flies to attack. Make a Ranged attack (+3 To-Hit) against an enemy within 30 feet. If it hits, the target takes no Wounds, but the flies swarm their eyes and throat, instantly inflicting the Blinded and Silenced conditions until the target spends an Action to swat them away."
