      "8",
      "1",
      "Uprooted Mausoleum Pillar with Chains",
      "Mausoleum Pillar Greatclub",
      "Chunks of Graveyard Stone",
      "Passive Traits\nAmalgamation of Death: Because it is a golem made of hundreds of corpses rather than a single undead entity, standard \"Turn Undead\" or banishing spells are highly ineffective. It automatically succeeds on Willpower tests to resist being turned, commanded, or frightened. Additionally, it takes no extra damage from Critical Hits, as it has no vital organs or singular structural weak point.\n\nChorus of the Damned: The vortex of trapped souls in its ribcage is an overwhelming hazard. Any living creature that starts its turn within 30 feet of the Giant takes 10 Psychic/Necrotic Wounds from the wailing spirits and is Deafened.\n\nSiege Engine: The Bone Giant is built to reduce fortresses to dust. It deals double Wounds to all environmental structures, walls, vehicles, and physical shields. It ignores Movement penalties for walking through difficult terrain, as it simply crushes the obstacles beneath its massive feet.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nMausoleum Sweep (Cost: 2 Actions): The Giant swings its massive stone pillar in a brutal, horizontal arc. Make a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit) against up to two adjacent targets. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 50 Bludgeoning Wounds. Targets struck must pass a severe Physique(12) test or be violently hurled 30 feet backward, landing Prone.\n\nVortex Vent (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Giant forcibly opens its ribcage, unleashing a torrent of the screaming souls trapped within. Make a Ranged attack (+3 To-Hit) in a 60-foot cone. On a hit, targets take 3d10 + 20 Necrotic Wounds and gain 1 Stunned condition as the spectral hands tear at their life-force.\n\nUnnatural Trample (Cost: 1 Action): The Giant uses its terrifyingly fast stride to crush the frontline. It moves up to its full 60-foot Movement speed in a straight line, passing freely through the spaces of any smaller creatures. Any enemy whose space it moves through must pass an Agility(10) test or take 30 Bludgeoning Wounds from its colossal, skeletal feet."
    ],
