    "values": [
      "Bugbear: The Shadow-Stalker",
      "Medium",
      "Goblinoid",
      "",
      "A Bugbear is a contradiction: a seven-foot-tall mountain of muscle and coarse, matted fur that can move as silently as a ghost. Their joints seem unnaturally loose, allowing them to squeeze into spaces that should be far too small for them, and their long, gangly arms give them a reach that catches most adventurers off-guard. They don't hunt for glory; they are apex bullies who enjoy the moment of pure, frozen terror when a sentry realizes the \"shadow\" behind them has breathing and a morningstar.",
