      "Cave Spider: The Jagged-Ambusher",
      "Medium",
      "Beast / Monstrosity",
      "",
      "A Cave Spider is roughly the size of a squat human or a large wolf, but its eight spindly, multi-jointed legs give it a much wider footprint. Its thorax is covered in jagged, calcified plates that perfectly mimic the texture of wet stalactites or jagged limestone. They do not build massive, visible webs; instead, they spin nearly invisible, high-tension \"trip-wires\" across cave floors and narrow corridors. They are patient stalkers, preferring to drop from the ceiling to deliver a single, paralyzing bite before retreating into the shadows to let the toxin do its gruesome work.",
