      "1-4",
      "Calcified Plating (Natural Armor)",
      "Paralyzing Fangs",
      "High-Tension Silk. Shoots invisible trip-wires up to 40ft",
      "Passive Traits\nStalactite Camouflage: When clinging to a rocky ceiling or wall and remaining motionless, the Cave Spider is virtually indistinguishable from a jagged limestone formation. It automatically gains Advantage on any Stealth checks to initiate an ambush, and enemies suffer Disadvantage on Awareness checks to spot it in the dark.\n\nHigh-Tension Trip-Wires: At the start of the encounter, the Cave Spider has already laid invisible silk trip-wires in the immediate 30-foot area. Whenever an enemy uses a Move action to travel more than 10 feet through this zone, they must pass an Agility(9) test or violently trip, falling Prone and ending their Movement for that turn.\n\nCeiling Scuttler: The Cave Spider completely ignores all difficult terrain modifiers for climbing. It can move at its full speed of 40 across sheer walls and ceilings, and takes zero falling damage if it intentionally drops onto a target.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nThe Jagged Drop (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The spider releases its grip on the ceiling and plummets onto an unsuspecting target. It moves up to 20 feet vertically and makes a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 25 Wounds, and the sheer weight of its calcified thorax knocks the target Prone.\n\nParalyzing Bite (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The spider's signature execution tool. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit) against a target. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Wounds, and the target must pass a severe Physique(10) test. On a failure, the venom takes hold—inflicting 1 Poison condition (1d10 wounds) and the Stunned condition for 1 round.\n\nScuttle to the Shadows (Cost: 1 Action): Adhering to its hit-and-run nature, the spider instantly Disengages from melee combat without triggering any free attacks of opportunity. It can immediately move up to 20 feet, preferably up a wall or into a narrow crevice, to let its venom do the work."
    ],
