      "2-6",
      "Serrated Black-Iron Cleaver, Volcanic Blunderbuss, Barbed Whip",
      "Serrated Black-Iron Cleaver",
      "Blunderbuss/Rifle",
      "Passive Traits\nLava-Forged Resilience: Born in the infernos of Bin Uluhm, the Chaos Dwarf is completely immune to the Burning condition and takes 0 Wounds from mundane or magical Fire. If hit by a Fire-based attack, their obsidian armor absorbs the heat, automatically granting them +10 Wounds on their next Melee attack.\n\nThe Meat Shield (Cruel Taskmaster): The Chaos Dwarf surrounds itself with expendable thralls. If the Dwarf is targeted by a Melee or Ranged attack and has an allied minion (or a summoned slave) adjacent to them, the Dwarf can use its Reaction to violently pull the minion into the path of the blow, forcing the minion to take all the Wounds and effects instead.\n\nDark Engineering: Their weapons are crafted to maximize suffering. Any time the Chaos Dwarf rolls a Critical Hit, the jagged edges of their weapons automatically inflict 1 Bleeding and 1 Poisoned condition as toxic ash is ground into the wound.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSerrated Cleave (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A brutal hacking motion meant to rip flesh rather than cleanly cut. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 25 Wounds, and the jagged wound is so horrific that the target's healing received from spells or potions is halved for 1 full round.\n\nVolcanic Blunderbuss (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Dwarf levels a crude, heavy firearm packed with black powder and obsidian shrapnel. Make a Ranged attack (+2 To-Hit) against all targets in a 15-foot cone. On a hit, targets take 2d10 + 15 Fire/Piercing Wounds, are knocked 5 feet backward, and gain 1 Burning condition from the white-hot slag.\n\nCrack the Whip (Range Cost: 1 Action): The Dwarf weaponizes terror to drive its forces. It targets one allied minion or slave within 15 feet. That ally instantly takes 5 Wounds from the barbed whip, but the sheer adrenaline and fear grant the ally 1 free Action to immediately move or attack out of turn."
    ],
