      "3-18",
      "usty Slag-Shovel, Unstable Black-Powder Flask, Scrap Iron.",
      "Rusty Slag-Shovel",
      "Hot Cinders",
      "Passive Traits\nStrength in Misery: The Slag-Drudge is far more afraid of its boss than it is of the players. If a Slag-Drudge is standing within 30 feet of an allied Bin Uluhm Taskmaster or Overseer, it automatically gains Advantage on its Melee To-Hit rolls out of sheer terror of missing.\n\nSpiteful Demise: They carry unstable flasks of mining powder on their belts. When a Slag-Drudge is reduced to 0 Wounds, it spitefully detonates the flask. Every creature (friend or foe) within 5 feet must pass an Agility(5) test or take 10 Fire Wounds from the blast.\n\nAsh-Blind: Having spent their entire lives staring into magma vents, they are completely immune to the Blinded condition and ignore all visibility penalties caused by smoke or ash.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nShovel Strike (Cost: 1 Action): A desperate, heavy swing with a crude mining tool. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 12 Bludgeoning/Slashing Wounds.\n\nHot Cinder Toss (Range Cost: 1 Action): The Drudge reaches into its apron and throws a handful of burning slag. Make a Ranged attack (+1 To-Hit) against a target within 15 feet. On a hit, it deals 5 Fire Wounds and the target gains 1 Burning condition.\n\nCowardly Scramble (Cost: 1 Action): The Drudge drops to all fours to escape. It moves up to 15 feet. This movement completely ignores Difficult Terrain and does not trigger free attacks of opportunity."
    ],
