  {
    "values": [
      "Chaos Wizard (Warlock)",
      "Medium",
      "Humanoid",
      "",
      "A corrupted scholar who gazed too deeply into the void and let the void in. Shrouded in dark, shifting robes and surrounded by the smell of ozone and rotting copper, this caster is a living conduit for daemonic energies. They are physically frail, but the reality-bending magic they wield makes them an apocalyptic threat if left unchallenged on the battlefield.\n\nArtifact Drop: The Void-Glass Eye\nIf the party manages to corner and slay the Warlock before being torn apart by the void, they can loot the artifact from the scholar's cooling corpse.\n\nType: Magical Amulet / Wondrous Item\n\nRequirements: Can only be attuned by a character with at least 10 Willpower.\n\nDescription: This heavy, jagged amulet is strung on a chain of blackened iron. The centerpiece is a sphere of clouded, swirling glass that feels freezing cold to the touch. If stared at for too long, the smoke inside seems to form a slit, unblinking pupil. It smells faintly of ozone and old blood.\n\nCustom Passive Traits:\n\nWhispers in the Dark: The Eye is constantly feeding the wearer secrets from the void. The wearer gains a permanent +2 bonus to their Intellect and Awareness characteristics while the amulet is worn. However, the whispers make restful sleep nearly impossible. The wearer must pass a Willpower DV(10) test every morning; if they fail, they wake up with 1 Exhausted condition that cannot be removed until the next day.\n\nCorrupted Attunement: The amulet bonds with the wearer's lifeforce. If the wearer attempts to take the amulet off, they immediately suffer 3d10 undefendable Wounds as the void-glass fiercely resists being removed.\n\nAction-Based Abilities:\n\nGlimpse the Abyss (Cost: 1 Action): The wearer can clutch the amulet and channel its dark energy to cast the Gaze of the Abyss ability. They lock eyes with a target within 40 feet, forcing the victim to make a Willpower test. On a failure, the victim suffers 1 Stunned condition and loses all Wound Mitigation from their armor for their next turn.\n\nThe Void's Toll: Magic this dark always demands a price. Every time the wearer successfully uses the Glimpse the Abyss action, they must roll a d10. On a roll of 1 or 2, the Eye feeds directly on their lifeforce, causing the wearer to permanently lose 1 point from their maximum Physical characteristic.",
