      "",
      "1",
      "Magic Robes",
      "Short Sword or Long Sword",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nConduit of the Void: The Warlock is not fully anchored to the material plane. They take only half Wounds from all non-magical physical attacks. However, if they take Wounds from a Holy or Radiant source, their connection to the void flickers, and they lose 1 Action on their next turn.\n\nShifting Robes: The dark, tearing energy around the Warlock bends light. Any Ranged attack (arrows, bolts, thrown weapons) made against the Warlock from further than 20 feet away automatically suffers Disadvantage.\n\nApocalyptic Presence: The smell of rotting copper and ozone suffocates the area. Enemies that start their turn within 30 feet of the Warlock cannot regain Focus points, and any active healing potions or spells cast in this radius heal for exactly half their normal amount.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nGaze of the Abyss(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): Channeling the power of their artifact, the Warlock locks eyes with a target within 40 feet. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals no Wounds, but the victim must make a Willpower(10) test. On a failure, the victim suffers 1 Stunned condition and loses all Wound Mitigation from their armor for their next turn as the void strips their defenses.\n\nOzone Rend(TN11) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Warlock tears a hole in reality. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit) against all targets in a 20-foot radius. On a success, targets take 2d10 + 25 Daemonic/Lightning Wounds and are violently pushed 10 feet away from the epicenter of the blast.\n\nVoid Step(TN6) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Warlock folds space to protect their frail body. They instantly Disengage from melee combat without triggering any free attacks, teleporting up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space they can see, leaving behind a cloud of freezing, foul-smelling smoke."
    ],
