      "None (It is the weapon)",
      "Brazen Hooves & Wings",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nOmniscient Wings: Covered in thousands of golden eyes, the Cherubim perceives the absolute truth of the battlefield. It is immune to the Blinded condition, ignores all forms of invisibility or magical darkness, and can never be Flanked.\n\nLiving Alloy: The Cherubim’s body is immune to mundane weaponry. Any physical attacks made with non-magical, non-adamantine weapons deal exactly half Wounds (before mitigation is applied) and have their armor sundering effects completely ignored.\n\nThe Fourfold Visage: At the start of the Cherubim's turn, its massive head violently rotates to reveal a new face, fundamentally altering its combat loop for that round:\n\nFace of the Lion (Might): Its Melee To-Hit becomes an overwhelming +8, and all Melee Wounds are increased by +20.\n\nFace of the Ox (Endurance): Its Armor Mitigation doubles to 50, and it becomes completely immune to being knocked Prone or moved.\n\nFace of the Eagle (Agility): It unfolds its wings, gaining a Flight speed of 80 feet, and its Defense increases to 11 while airborne.\n\nFace of the Man (Wisdom): It projects an aura of divine law. Any enemy attempting to cast a spell within 60 feet must pass a Willpower(12) test, or the spell fizzles and is wasted.\n\nAction-Based Abilities \nJudgment of the Hoof (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Cherubim rears up and brings its celestial bronze hooves down on a target. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit, modified by Visage). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 35 Wounds and permanently shatters the target's physical shield, if non-magical.\n\nSearing Gaze(TN9) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The thousands of eyes on its wings flare with blinding, infrared light. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit) against a target within 40 feet. On a hit, it deals 2d10 + 20 Radiant Wounds, and the target is permanently Marked. The Cherubim's melee attacks automatically gain Advantage against Marked targets.\n\nGatekeeper's Banishment (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Cherubim strikes the earth, unleashing a shockwave of moral and magical energy in a 20-foot radius. All enemies caught in the blast must pass a Physique(12) test or take 3d10 + 35 Radiant Wounds and be violently thrown 15 feet away, landing Prone. Summoned creatures or undead hit by this blast take double Wounds."
    ],
