      "None",
      "Claws, Horns, & Fangs",
      "Dragon's Scorch",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Three-Way Civil War: Because the Chimera has three distinct brains, it is incredibly difficult to shut down. The Chimera is completely immune to the Charmed, Stunned, and Flanked conditions. If a spell or ability would normally Stun the creature, it only suppresses one of the heads for a round, costing it 1 Action instead of its entire turn.\n\nScrap-Heap Anatomy: The Chimera's internal organs are a tangled, nonsensical mess. Any Critical Hit landed on the Chimera only deals normal damage, as the attacker merely strikes a vestigial mass of muscle or a redundant bone plate instead of a vital organ.\n\nUnpredictable Thrashing: At the start of the Chimera's turn, roll a d6. On a 1 or 2, the Goat head takes charge (gains +15Ft Movement speed for that turn). On a 3 or 4, the Lion head takes charge (Melee attacks gain +10 Wounds). On a 5 or 6, the Dragon head takes charge (flies up to 20 feet without triggering attacks of opportunity).\n\nAction-Based Abilities \n(The Chimera uses its 3 Actions to let each head strike once per turn)\n\nLion's Rend (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The lion head lunges to tear flesh. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 +25 Wounds and automatically inflicts 1 Bleeding condition as its fangs lock in and violently shake.\n\nGoat's Gore (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The goat head delivers a brutal, concussive headbutt. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals half Wound bonus, 1d10 + 13, but the sheer kinetic force knocks the target 10 feet backward and violently Prone.\n\nDragon's Scorch (Range Cost: 1 Action): The dragon head exhales a chaotic burst of flame. Make a Ranged attack (+3 To-Hit) against all targets in a 15-foot cone. On a hit, targets take 2d10 + 20 Fire Wounds and gain 1 Burning condition."
