      "Needle Fur",
      "Serrated Bite",
      "Needle-Spray",
      "Passive Traits\nPhotosynthetic Camouflage: The wolf gains Advantage on all Agility tests to hide while in the brush of the Chromatic Weald.\n\nNeedle Fur: Any creature striking the wolf with a melee attack takes 1d10-3 automatic piercing damage from the pine-needle coat.\n\nPack Tactics: The wolf gains a +1 To-Hit bonus for every other Chlorofel creature currently engaged with the same target.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nNeedle-Spray (1 Action): Ranged +5. The wolf shakes its coat, firing needles in a 15ft cone. Deals 1d10+5 wounds and causes 1 Bleeding condition.\n\nSerrated Bite (2 Actions): If the hit is successful, the wolf latches on with hooked teeth. Target is Grappled (Def 0).\n\nFloral Scent (TN 6 - 1 Action): The wolf releases an alluring aroma. Target must pass a Willpower test or be Stunned for 1 turn."
