      "8",
      "1",
      "The ruined wealth of five fallen kingdoms",
      "Five Maws & Titanic Claws",
      "The Symphony of Breath",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Five-Fold Initiative: The Sovereign does not take a single turn. Instead, her 5 Actions are split across the initiative order. At the start of combat, the GM rolls 5 distinct initiatives (one for Red, Blue, Green, Black, and White). Each head takes exactly 1 Action on its specific turn. If the Sovereign's Wounds drop by 170 (one-fifth of her health), one head is severed, permanently reducing her Actions by 1.\n\nChromatic Shimmer: Her scales constantly shift elements to protect her. At the end of every round, she absorbs the element of the last spell or magical attack that hit her, becoming completely immune to that specific damage type for the entirety of the next round.\n\nElemental Symphony (Combo Magic): The heads work in tandem to multiply destruction. If a target is currently suffering from an elemental condition (like Burning or Frozen) and is hit by a different elemental breath weapon from the Sovereign, the conflicting magic violently combusts, dealing an additional 3d10 undefendable Wounds.\n\nAction-Based Abilities (5 Actions to Spend - 1 Per Head)\n(Each head uses its specific action on its own initiative turn)\n\nThe Red/Black Maw (Range Fire/Acid - Cost: 1 Action): The head exhales a 60-foot cone of either melting acid or roaring flame. Make a Ranged attack (+6 To-Hit). On a hit, targets take 1d10 + 50 Wounds and gain either 1 Burning or 1 Melting condition (permanently degrading armor).\n\nThe Blue/White Maw (Range Lightning/Cold - Cost: 1 Action): The head fires a 100-foot line of blinding lightning or freezing ice. Make a Ranged attack (+6 To-Hit). On a hit, targets take 1d10 + 50 Wounds and are either Stunned (Lightning) or have their Movement reduced to 0 for 1 round (Cold).\n\nThe Green Maw (Melee Poison Gas - Cost: 1 Action): The green head sweeps the battlefield, biting a specific target. Make a Melee attack (+7 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 70 Wounds and the target is swallowed by a cloud of toxic gas, suffering the Blinded and Poisoned conditions (d10 wounds)."
