      "Clay Golem: The Tomb Guardian",
      "Large",
      "Construct / Elemental",
      "",
      "Clay Golems are not merely statues; they are semi-liquid constructs of primordial clay imbued with a fragment of a spirit. Standing nearly ten feet tall, the golem has a disproportionately large upper body with long, trunk-like arms. Its head is a featureless dome, save for a single glowing glyph etched into its forehead. Its surface is perpetually damp and shifting. Unlike stone or iron golems, the clay version is disturbingly silent, its footsteps making a soft \"thud-squelch\" sound on the stone floors of the tombs it protects. When struck, the clay doesn't shatter; it ripples like water, sealing the wound almost as quickly as it is made.",
