      "Trunk-like Arms",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nRippling Clay (Self-Sealing): Mundane weapons get stuck in its body or pass through harmlessly. Any physical Melee attack that deals Slashing or Piercing Wounds has its total damage cut in half before Armor Mitigation is even applied. Furthermore, the Golem is completely immune to the Bleeding and Exhausted conditions.\n\nSilent Squelch: Despite being 10 feet tall, the Clay Golem makes virtually no sound. It automatically succeeds on Agility tests to move silently, granting it Advantage on its opening attacks against a party that is relying solely on hearing to navigate a dungeon.\n\nBerserk Degradation: If the glowing glyph on its forehead takes targeted magic damage, or the Golem's Health drops below 20%, the binding spirit fractures. The Golem enters a mindless Frenzy, attacking the closest creature (friend or foe) with Advantage on all To-Hit rolls, completely ignoring any defensive tactics.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTrunk-Arm Slam (Cost: 1 Action): The Golem brings down a massive, mud-caked fist. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 25 Bludgeoning Wounds, and the target must pass a Physique(8) test or be knocked Prone.\n\nSmothering Embrace (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Golem attempts to absorb a target into its semi-liquid chest. Target one adjacent enemy. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 20 Bludgeoning Wounds, and the target is pulled into the clay. The target is instantly Grappled, Restrained, and Silenced (unable to breathe or cast verbal spells). They take 10 Suffocation Wounds at the start of their turn until they use an Action to break free.\n\nGlyph of Sluggishness (Cost: 1 Action): The glyph on the Golem's featureless dome flares with ancient curse magic. All enemies within a 20-foot radius must pass a Willpower(7) test. On a failure, their Movement speed is reduced by half on their next turn, and they cannot use Reactions, replicating the heavy, dragging sensation of wading through deep mud."
    ],
