      "Mask of Frozen Mist, Sky-Sapphire Scepter, Gravity-Defying Silks",
      "Sky-Sapphire Scepter",
      "Atmospheric Crush",
      "Passive Traits\nWeight of the Sky: The Cloud Giant weaponizes the ambient air pressure around them. The area within 60 feet of the Giant is treated as extreme Difficult Terrain for all hostile creatures. Any enemy that attempts to Move or Dash within this radius must pass a severe Physique(12) test or have their Movement reduced to 0 for the turn, pinned by the heavy air.\n\nMask of Frozen Mist: The Giant's shifting cloud-silver mask protects their mind and senses. They are completely immune to the Blinded, Charmed, and Taunted conditions. If a player attempts to target the Giant with a psychological or illusion spell, the mask shifts to an expression of terrifying wrath, reflecting the spell's energy back as 20 Psychic Wounds.\n\nUntouchable Silks: The Giant floats effortlessly. They are completely immune to falling damage, ignore all ground-based traps or hazards, and cannot be knocked Prone, Grappled, or Restrained by any creature smaller than Enormous size.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nScepter of the Stratosphere (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Noble swings a massive, gilded scepter with terrifying grace. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) with a massive 30-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 50 Bludgeoning/Force Wounds, instantly shattering any non-magical shields.\n\nBarometric Implosion (Range Cost: 3 Actions): The Giant clenches their fist, instantly increasing the atmospheric pressure in a localized 30-foot radius up to 100 feet away. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit). On a hit, all targets take 4d10 + 40 Force/Bludgeoning Wounds. Any metal armor worn by the targets is instantly bent, reducing their Wound Mitigation by 5 for the rest of the encounter as it crushes inward.\n\nGale-Step Reposition (Cost: 1 Action): The Giant dissolves into a flurry of pristine white clouds and instantly teleports up to 80 feet to an unoccupied space. This movement does not trigger attacks of opportunity and leaves behind a localized vacuum that violently pulls all enemies within 20 feet of their previous location 15 feet inward, causing them to collide and fall Prone."
    ],
