      "Razor Chitin",
      "Tri-Bladed Forelimbs",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nVacuum Strikes: The sheer speed of the Mantis's forelimbs warps the air pressure around the blades. Its Melee attacks completely ignore the Armor Mitigation provided by physical shields, and players cannot use the \"Parry\" reaction to deflect its blows, as the vacuum simply pulls their weapons out of alignment.\n\nCompound Omnivision: The Tri-Mantis's massive, multifaceted eyes process movement in a 360-degree arc. It is completely immune to the Blinded and Flanked conditions, and attackers can never gain Advantage from striking it from behind or from Stealth.\n\nCrimson Stillness: Despite being bright red, it perfectly mimics bloody detritus or specific crimson flora in its environment. If it remains completely motionless, it gains Advantage on Stealth checks. If it attacks a target who hasn't detected it, it automatically wins the Initiative tie for that round.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nWhistling Cleave (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A blindingly fast slash with one of its bladed arms. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 20 Wounds and automatically inflicts 1 Bleeding condition as the razor-edge surgically parts flesh.\n\nVacuum Guillotine (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Mantis strikes with two blades simultaneously, crossing them like scissors to create a localized barometric drop. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 2d10 + 30 Wounds, and the target is Deafened and Stunned for 1 round as the sudden vacuum pops their eardrums and stuns their nervous system.\n\nPredator's Vault (Cost: 1 Action): Relying on its powerful hind legs, the Mantis instantly Disengages from melee combat without triggering free attacks of opportunity. It leaps up to 30 feet in any direction (including vertically). Upon landing, any adjacent enemy must pass an Agility(9) test or be knocked Prone by the sheer force of the impact."
