      "1-8",
      "Rusted Broadsword, Heavy Iron Shield, Pitted Plate Armor.",
      "Rusted Broadsword w/ Shield or 2H Weapon",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nPhalanx Discipline: If a Crypt Guard ends its turn adjacent to at least one allied Crypt Guard, they automatically interlock shields. While interlocked, they gain Advantage on all Defense checks against frontal attacks, and they become completely immune to being pushed backward or knocked Prone.\n\nCold Vengeance (Undead Fortitude): They simply do not care about environmental trauma. The Crypt Guard is completely immune to the Bleeding and Exhausted conditions. Furthermore, they ignore all Movement penalties from difficult terrain if it was created by environmental hazards (like a wall of fire, acid pools, or caltrops), marching straight through the pain.\n\nVeteran's Muscle Memory: Their combat reflexes are ingrained in their bones. If an enemy makes a Melee attack against the Crypt Guard and misses, the Guard may immediately use its Reaction to make a Melee attack (1 Action) (+4 To-Hit) in retaliation.\n\nAction-Based Abilities \nGrinding Advance (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Guard steps forward in perfect unison and thrusts. It moves 5 feet directly toward an enemy and makes a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 20 Wounds, and the target is forcefully pushed 5 feet backward to make room for the marching wall.\n\nShield Wall Lock (Cost: 2 Actions): The Guard plants its heavy iron shield into the stone floor and braces. Until its next turn, its Armor Mitigation doubles (from 10 to 20). Any physical Melee attack that strikes the Guard while braced causes the attacker's weapon to shudder violently, costing the attacker 1 Action on their next turn from the jarring impact.\n\nBalefire Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Guard channels the cold blue fire of its eyes down the blade of its sword. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Cold/Necrotic Wounds, and the target's Movement speed is halved on their next turn as the chill of the grave sinks into their muscles."
