      "oul-Forged Plate, The Abyssal Greatsword",
      "Abyssal Greatsword",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nAura of Dark Majesty: The Lord's presence suppresses hope. Enemies within 30 feet of him cannot gain Advantage on any attack rolls, regardless of flanking or stealth. Additionally, any allied Daemons within this aura gain +5 to their Wounds dealt as they are driven to impress their master.\n\nThe Duelist King: If forced into a 1v1 engagement (meaning no other allies or enemies are adjacent to him and his target), his strikes sever the soul. Any target he hits in a 1v1 cannot be healed by magical means for 1 full round. Furthermore, he completely ignores the Flanked condition, smoothly pivoting to parry.\n\nMaster's Guard: Because he relies on flawless parrying rather than dodging, any Melee attack that fails to beat his Defense of 7 results in the attacker being smoothly deflected and pushed 5 feet backward, ruining their positioning.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nThe Voice of Ruin(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): He speaks a command that reality forces mortals to obey. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit) against a target within 40 feet. On a hit, it deals no Wounds, but the target must instantly use their Reaction to move up to 15 feet in a direction of the Lord's choosing (forcing them into traps, off cliffs, or away from the healer).\n\nFlawless Riposte (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Lord executes a breathtakingly precise sword technique. Make a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 45 Wounds and the target is violently Disarmed. Make a Physique vs Physique test. if failed, their weapon is knocked 10 feet away, and they gain 1 Stunned condition from the agonizing shock to their nerves.\n\nGrand Commander's Edict(TN12) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Lord points his blade, directing the flow of battle. He chooses one player; immediately, any allied Daemon on the battlefield may use its Reaction to move its full speed toward that player and make a single Melee attack. If the Lord has no allies currently alive, this Action instead summons 1d4 Lesser Daemons to the edges of the battlefield."
