      "5",
      "1",
      "A masterwork, corrupted mortal weapon (e.g., a twisted halberd or a screaming rapier).",
      "Screaming Rapier/Longsword",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Favored Son (Jealous Gods): The Chaos Gods are watching their pet perform. If any character other than the one the Prince is actively dueling deals Wounds to the Prince, the gods violently intervene. The interloping attacker instantly takes 1d10 undefendable Warp Wounds from a sudden burst of abyssal lightning.\n\nMortal Insight: He knows exactly how to wound human pride. If an enemy attacks the Prince and misses, the Prince mocks them, automatically gaining Advantage on his next Melee attack against that specific enemy.\n\nCrystalline Deflection: The gifts of his patron make his anatomy unpredictable. He is completely immune to Critical Hits (they only deal normal damage), and players cannot sever his limbs or disarm him, as his weapon is fused to his nervous system.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTheatrical Challenge(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Prince points his screaming blade at the strongest hero, demanding a duel. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit) against one target within 40 feet. On a hit, it deals no Wounds, but the target is Charmed into a rage—they cannot willingly target anyone except the Prince on their next turn, and they suffer Disadvantage in their first turn of combat and or they attempt to flee.\n\nSmoke-Step Flourish (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): Moving with impossible, smoky grace, the Prince instantly Disengages without triggering free attacks of opportunity, teleports up to 20 feet, and makes a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 25 Wounds.\n\nGift of Mutation (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Prince grabs an enemy and forces raw, warping chaos into their veins. Make a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 2d10 + 15 Acid/Warp Wounds, and the target must pass a severe Physique(10) test. On a failure, their flesh temporarily warps: they gain 1 Poison condition (1d10 wounds) and drop any weapons or shields they are holding as their hands painfully fuse into useless lumps of flesh for 1 round."
