      "Twin Noktorian Daggers, Hand-Crossbow, Vials of Spider-Venom, Shadow-Silk Cloak.",
      "Twin Daggers",
      "Throwing Dagger, Hand-Crossbow",
      "Passive Traits\nNoktorian Venom: Every weapon the Night-Blade wields is coated in a debilitating subterranean neurotoxin. Any time they successfully deal Wounds to a target, that target automatically gains 1 Poisoned condition and takes an additional 5 Poison Wounds at the start of their next turn on a failed physique(5) test.\n\nCruel Opportunist: They thrive on the suffering and disadvantage of others. If a Night-Blade attacks a target that is currently Prone, Blinded, or Poisoned, the Night-Blade automatically gains Advantage on their To-Hit roll.\n\nLight-Absorbing Silk: While in dim light or darkness, the Dark Elf is functionally invisible. They automatically win Initiative ties if striking from the shadows, and any Ranged attacks made against them in dim light suffer Disadvantage.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nShadow-Slip (Cost: 1 Action): The Elf seemingly melts into the darkness. They instantly teleport up to 30 feet to any unoccupied space that is in shadow or dim light. This movement does not trigger attacks of opportunity and can be used to move vertically up walls.\n\nWhispers in the Dark (Cost: 1 Action): Weaponizing their 8 Charisma, the Elf projects cruel, terrifying whispers into the mind of a target within 40 feet. The target must pass a Willpower(5) test or become Frightened and Taunted (forced to attack wildly into the darkness rather than assisting their allies) for 1 round.\n\nSurgical Twin-Strike (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Elf steps out of the shadows for a rapid double-stab. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Piercing Wounds, applies the Noktorian Venom, and reduces the target's Movement by half on their next turn as the tendons are clipped."
