      "Deer(Stag): Ghost of the Deep Woods",
      "Medium",
      "Beast",
      "",
      "The Deer is the ghost of the deep woods. While often viewed as mere prey by the more aggressive inhabitants of the forest, the Deer is a master of evasion and sensory awareness. A mature Stag, with its crown of jagged antlers and powerful, spring-like musculature, can be quite formidable when cornered or during the \"rutting\" season. They are the first to know when danger enters the grove. Some druidic circles believe the eldest Stags act as vessels for the forest's own spirit, guiding travelers away from danger—or leading the unworthy into the heart of a briar patch.",
