      "None",
      "Hammering Hooves & Antlers",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nGhost of the Woods: The Stag leaves almost no tracks. It automatically gains Advantage on all Stealth checks while in a forest environment, and players suffer Disadvantage on any Awareness or Tracking checks trying to locate the herd.\n\nHyper-Sensory Alarm: The Deer is the first to know when danger approaches. It is completely immune to being ambushed or surprised. If combat breaks out, the Deer automatically wins all Initiative ties.\n\nSpring-Loaded Bound: The Stag ignores all Movement penalties associated with natural difficult terrain (like dense underbrush, mud, or shallow streams). It can leap up to 15 feet over obstacles or gaps without needing a running start.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nStartled Dash (Cost: 1 Action): The Deer's primary survival instinct. It instantly Disengages from melee combat without triggering any free attacks of opportunity and uses its full Movement (50 feet) to sprint away from the nearest threat.\n\nThe Desperate Kick (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): If cornered, the Stag rears up and uses its hooves like hammers. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Wounds, permanently shatters the target's equipped physical shield, and the target must pass a severe Physique test or suffer 1 Stunned condition from cracked ribs.\n\nRutting Charge (Cost: 2 Actions): The Stag lowers its crown of jagged antlers and charges. It moves up to 30 feet in a straight line and makes a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Piercing Wounds and violently knocks the target Prone."
