      "Bone-Crushing Jaws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nExecution Squad (Pack Tactics): The Dire Wolf fights with flawless, instinctual coordination. It automatically gains Advantage on all Melee attack rolls if at least one of its allies is adjacent to its target and isn't incapacitated.\n\nBattering Ram Momentum: The wolf uses its 800-lb mass as a weapon. If the Dire Wolf moves at least 20 feet in a straight line before making a Melee attack, the target must pass a severe Agility(7) test or be violently knocked Prone by the sheer kinetic impact.\n\nWinter's Stride: Born for the frozen wilds, the Dire Wolf completely ignores Movement penalties caused by ice, deep snow, or freezing mud. It also possesses natural resistance to Cold/Frost magic, taking exactly half Wounds from those sources.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBone-Crushing Bite (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The wolf snaps its massive jaws shut. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 25 normal Wounds. If this attack hits a target that is currently Prone, the sheer pressure of the bite shatters bone, inflicting 1 Stunned condition.\n\nThe Throat Pin (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The wolf attempts to end the fight instantly. It leaps onto a Prone target and locks its jaws onto their neck. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 2d10 + 35 Wounds, and the target is Grappled and Silenced (cannot speak or cast verbal spells). Until the target breaks the grapple, they automatically take 20 Wounds at the start of each of their turns. Make a Physique or Strength Conditioning  vs Physique test.\n\nPredator's Pivot (Cost: 1 Action): The wolf darts out of striking distance to circle its prey. It instantly Disengages from melee combat without triggering free attacks of opportunity and moves up to 30 feet, allowing it to set up another Battering Ram charge on its next turn."
    ],
