      "1-2",
      "None",
      "Barbed Tentacles & Claws",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Displacement Haze: The biological light-bending of its hide is always active. Any Melee or Ranged attack targeting the Displacer Beast automatically suffers Disadvantage. If the beast is inflicted with the Stunned or Unconscious conditions, this passive biological function shuts down until it recovers.\n\nPhantom Afterimage: If an attacker misses a Melee attack against the Displacer Beast (meaning they struck the illusion), the beast can instantly use its Reaction to shift up to 5 feet into an unoccupied space without triggering free attacks of opportunity.\n\nSix-Legged Stability: Its unnatural anatomy grants it perfect balance. It is completely immune to the Prone condition and ignores all Movement penalties associated with natural difficult terrain like thick mud or dense underbrush.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSpiked Tentacle Whip (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The beast lashes out with the heavy, barbed tentacles extending from its shoulders. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). This attack has a 10-foot reach, allowing the beast to strike from behind the safety of its illusion. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 20 Wounds and inflicts 1 Bleeding condition.\n\nPhase-Pounce (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The beast closes the gap in a terrifying blur. It moves up to 30 feet and makes a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 2d10 + 20 Wounds, and the target is automatically Grappled by the tentacles, dragged adjacent to the beast's gnashing jaws.\n\nShimmering Retreat (Cost: 1 Action): Knowing when to reposition, the beast instantly Disengages from melee combat. It moves up to 20 feet away, leaving a static, perfectly realistic illusion of itself in its former space. The next Ranged attack or single-target spell that passes through that space automatically hits the illusion instead of any actual targets, destroying the fake image."
    ],
