      "1-3",
      "Spiked Collar, Leather/Chain Barding",
      "Crushing Jaws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nUnwavering Morale: The War Dog is immune to fear, panic, and psychic rout effects as long as its designated Master (or an allied player) is conscious and within line of sight. It will gladly stand in a wall of fire if commanded to hold the line.\n\nThe Sensory Anchor: The dog cannot be ambushed. If an enemy attempts to use Stealth or magical Invisibility within 30 feet, the War Dog automatically pinpoints their exact location by scent, pointing them out to its allies and completely stripping the enemy of any unseen Advantage.\n\nTactical Partner: The War Dog understands flanking and crossfires instinctively. It automatically gains Advantage on its Melee attack rolls if its Master (or an ally) is engaged in melee combat with the same target.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nThe Lockdown (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The dog uses its sheer mass to pin an enemy, preventing them from reaching the backline casters. It lunges up to 15 feet and makes a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 10 Wounds, and the target is knocked Prone and securely Grappled. The target cannot move until they spend an Action to physically wrestle the dog off them. The target must be of medium size or less to be pinned.\n\nThroat Tear (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A vicious, finishing bite on a pinned target. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit), suffering 1d10 + 10 wounds. If this attack targets an enemy that is currently Prone or Grappled, it automatically inflicts 1 Bleeding condition and deals an additional +10 Wounds.\n\nIntercepting Lunge (Cost: 1 Action): Prioritizing its master's life above its own, the dog instantly Disengages from its current fight without triggering free attacks of opportunity. It moves up to 25 feet to place itself directly between an allied character and an approaching enemy, acting as a living shield."
    ],
