      "3-12",
      "Mining Pick, Blacksmith Hammer, Leather Apron, Iron Flask",
      "Heavy Work Tools",
      "Crossbow",
      "Passive Traits\nBlue-Collar Vigor: \"Iron Joe\" is used to 14-hour shifts in the mines. He is completely immune to the Exhausted condition, and cannot be forced to drop his equipped weapon by physical or magical means (his grip is like a vice).\n\nShield-Brother Rabble: They might not be trained soldiers, but they look out for each other. If a \n\"Iron-Joe\" Dwarf is standing adjacent to at least one other allied Dwarf, they automatically gain +1 to their Defense and Advantage on Willpower tests against Fear.\n\nStubborn as Stone: Despite his negative Agility, his low center of gravity makes him remarkably hard to topple. Any physical attack or ability that attempts to knock \"Iron Joe\" Prone automatically suffers Disadvantage if of equal size or smaller.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nThe Knee-Capper (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): A brutal, low-swinging chop with a pickaxe aimed at the shins. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 10 Wounds and the target's Movement is reduced by half on their next turn.\n\nTavern Haymaker (Cost: 2 Actions): A massive, telegraphed, wild swing. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 15 Bludgeoning Wounds and violently shoves the target 5 feet backward. If this attack misses, \"Iron Joe\" loses his balance and stumbles 5 feet forward.\n\nLiquid Courage (Cost: 1 Action): The Dwarf takes a massive swig from his iron hip-flask. He instantly recovers 5 Wounds and gains 1 temporary Focus point, but takes a -1 penalty to his Awareness for the rest of the encounter due to the inebriation."
    ],
