      "2-6",
      "Kel Thurum Forge-Hammer, Heavy Iron Shield, Runed Plate Armor",
      "Kel Thurum Forge-Hammer",
      "Crossbow",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Unshakable Anvil: As long as the Dwarf's feet are planted on solid stone or earth, they cannot be moved against their will. They are completely immune to being knocked Prone, pushed backward, by any creature its size or smaller.\n\nMaster of the Forge (Sundering): The Dwarf knows exactly where the structural weakness in an enemy's armor is. Any time the Dwarf successfully deals Wounds to a target with a Melee attack, they permanently reduce that target's Armor Mitigation by 3 as they crush joints and shatter plating.\n\nThe Hard Mind: The Dwarf’s stubbornness acts as a mental fortress. They automatically gain Advantage on all Willpower tests to resist being Charmed, Frightened, or magically manipulated.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nStructural Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A devastating, precise hammer blow aimed at equipment rather than flesh. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 13 Wounds. If the target is currently wielding a physical shield, the shield immediately loses 1 tier of effectiveness (or shatters completely if it is non-magical).\n\nHold the Doorway (Cost: 2 Actions): The Dwarf plants their feet, locks their shield, and becomes a living wall. Until the start of their next turn, their Defense becomes a 9 against frontal attacks. Furthermore, if an adjacent ally is targeted by a physical Melee attack, the Dwarf can automatically intercept the blow, forcing the attack to roll against the Dwarf's Defense instead.\n\nOath of Kel Thurum (Cost: 1 Action): The Dwarf touches a braided iron charm in their beard, swearing an oath against a specific enemy. For the remainder of the combat encounter, the Dwarf automatically gains Advantage on all Melee To-Hit rolls against that specific target, but suffers a -10 Movement penalty if they try to walk away from them."
    ],
