      "None",
      "Tectonic Fists",
      "Gravitational Debris",
      "Passive Traits\nGravitational Inescapability: The Mountain-Heart alters the gravity around it. The area within 40 feet of the elemental is considered extreme Difficult Terrain as loose rocks and debris float upward. Any flying creatures that enter this aura instantly have their flight speed reduced to 0 and crash to the ground. Furthermore, any enemy trying to move away from the elemental must spend 2 feet of Movement for every 1 foot traveled.\n\nBedrock Juggernaut: The elemental is completely immune to the Prone, Stunned, and Knockback conditions. It automatically destroys any environmental structures (trees, walls, towers) simply by walking through them, turning them to pulverized dust.\n\nGeothermal Rupture: The intense heat of its core makes it immune to Fire damage. If a player scores a Critical Hit against the elemental with a Melee weapon, they crack the obsidian shell, causing a sudden burst of liquid magma that deals 15 Fire Wounds directly back to the attacker.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTectonic Pulverize (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The titan brings a massive, obsidian fist down upon the earth. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 40 Bludgeoning Wounds. If the target is wielding a non-magical weapon or shield, it is instantly shattered by the impact.\n\nReverse Gravity (Cost: 3 Actions): The Mountain-Heart pulses with blinding emerald light, reversing gravity in a 30-foot cylinder anywhere within 60 feet. Every target in the cylinder must pass a Agility(10) test or \"fall\" 40 feet straight up into the air, hovering helplessly until the end of the elemental's next turn, at which point gravity normalizes and they slam back into the pulverized ground, taking massive falling damage (4d10 + 10) and landing Prone.\n\nGeode Pulse (Range Cost: 1 Action): The elemental fires a concentrated beam of gravitational and geothermal energy from its chest. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against a single target within 60 feet. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 20 Force/Fire Wounds and violently pulls the target 20 feet directly toward the elemental."
