      "8",
      "1",
      "Special",
      "Singularity Fists",
      "Gravitational Crush",
      "Passive Traits\nGravitational Law (Doubled Gravity): The World-Root dictates the physics around it. The area within 60 feet of the Lord is subjected to doubled gravity. Any enemy starting their turn in this aura instantly takes 10 Bludgeoning Wounds as their bones creak, and their Movement is permanently halved. Flying within this aura is completely impossible.\n\nAbsolute Stability: The Lord cannot be moved, altered, or debuffed against its will. It is completely immune to all forced movement, teleportation, Prone, Stunned, and polymorph/transmutation effects.\n\nSingularity Granite: Weapons that strike the World-Root are subjected to the intense gravitational pull of its hide. If a physical Melee attack fails to deal more than 10 Wounds (after mitigation is applied), the attacker's weapon is instantly caught in the gravitational field, requiring an Action and a severe Physique test to rip it free before it can be used again.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTectonic Obliteration (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Lord brings a molten-gold infused fist down upon the battlefield. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 60 Wounds, and the sheer force of the impact triggers a localized earthquake, forcing everyone within 20 feet of the target to pass an Agility(12) test or fall Prone.\n\nTransmute to Liquid Sand (Range Cost: 3 Actions): The Lord weaponizes its alchemical authority to swallow its enemies. It targets a 20-foot radius of ground within 60 feet. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against all enemies in the zone. On a hit, the ground turns to liquid sand; targets take 3d10 + 20 Wounds and are instantly Grappled and Restrained, buried up to their chests.\n\nGravitational Crush (Range Cost: 1 Action): The World-Root simply looks at a target and increases their personal gravity tenfold. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against a single target within 60 feet. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 30 Force/Bludgeoning Wounds, completely ignoring the target's equipped armor mitigation as the damage comes from the target's own collapsing weight."
