      "None",
      "Granite Fists",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Unstoppable Stride: The Vanguard's mass is absolute. It is completely immune to the Prone, Grappled, and Knockback conditions to creatures of similar size. Furthermore, it ignores all Difficult Terrain, simply pulverizing obstacles, traps, and underbrush into flat dust as it walks over them.\n\nSiege Construct: Built to break fortifications, the Vanguard deals double Wounds to any physical shields, environmental cover (walls, boulders, doors), and stationary structures.\n\nTremorsense: The geothermal core in its head allows it to perfectly track the vibrations of anything touching the ground. It completely ignores visual penalties from darkness, fog, or invisibility as long as its target is standing on the earth within 60 feet.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nPulverizing Slam (Cost: 1 Action): A deliberate, crushing blow from a granite fist. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 +20 Bludgeoning Wounds. If this attack targets an enemy wielding a shield, the shield immediately loses 1 tier of effectiveness.\n\nTectonic Stomp (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Vanguard brings its massive foot down, weaponizing its own weight. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit) against all targets within a 10-foot radius. On a hit, targets take 1d10 + 20 Wounds and are violently knocked Prone by the seismic shockwave.\n\nGeothermal Vent (Range Cost: 3 Actions): The Vanguard opens the plates on its \"face,\" venting the intense heat of its core. Make a Ranged attack (+2 To-Hit) in a 30-foot line. On a hit, targets take 2d10 + 20 Fire Wounds and their armor becomes superheated, causing them to take 5 Fire Wounds at the start of their next turn."
