      "Bedrock Scales (Natural Armor)",
      "Tri-Ring Crush (Treats as 2H)",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nGeologic Mass: Immune to all knockdown, push, or pull effects. Its sheer size means it takes no extra damage from standard Bleed conditions.\n\nSwallow Whole: Any successful melee hit that rolls an unmodified 10 automatically swallows a Medium or smaller target, inflicting 20 Acid Wounds per turn until the target cuts their way out.\n\nTremorsense: The Earth-Maw's Awareness of 10 allows it to detect the exact location of anything touching the ground within 500 feet, ignoring invisibility.\n\nActions\nTectonic Slam (Melee Cost: 2): Slams its body onto the battlefield. All creatures within 100 ft must make an Agility(12) Save or take half of its Melee Wounds (80) and be knocked Prone.\n\nDevour (Melee Cost: 1): Standard Melee attack using the 160 Wound damage profile.\n\nSubmerge (Cost: 3): Dives beneath the earth, gaining full cover and healing 3d10 Wounds while preparing to erupt beneath the party on the next turn."
