      "Sun-Gold Scimitar",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Smoldering Court (Aura of Smoke): The Efreeti commands the air itself. A 30-foot radius around the Sultan is perpetually filled with thick, choking volcanic smoke. This area counts as partial concealment (imposing Disadvantage on Ranged attacks targeting him). Any enemy starting their turn in the smoke takes 5 Fire Wounds and cannot regain Focus.\n\nLiquid Sun-Gold: His jewelry and weapons are forged of impossibly hot, liquid metal. Any time the Sultan successfully strikes a target with his Melee attack, or is struck by a non-magical Melee weapon, the liquid gold splashes. The target (or attacker) automatically gains 1 Burning condition (1d10 wounds).\n\nThe Cruel Contract: The Sultan does not kill; he collects. If a player is reduced to 0 Wounds by the Efreeti, they do not die. Instead, their soul is instantly bound by an infernal contract. They are stabilized at 1 Wound, but become permanently Charmed and must fight their allies until the Efreeti is defeated or the contract is magically broken.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTheatrical Cleave (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): A sweeping, arrogant strike with the massive scimitar. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) against up to two adjacent targets. If successful, it deals 1d10 +40 Wounds, and the sheer force of the blow knocks the targets 10 feet backward.\n\nAsh-Choke(TN11) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Efreeti clenches his fist, forcing the smoke in the air directly into his enemies' lungs. Make a Casting attack (+5 To-Hit) against all enemies within 30 feet. On a hit, it deals 2d10 + 20 Fire/Asphyxiation Wounds, and targets are completely Silenced (unable to speak or cast verbal spells) for 1 round as they violently cough up ash.\n\nKneel Before the Sultan(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): Weaponizing his 15 Willpower, he commands absolute submission. Make a Casting attack (+5 To-Hit) against one target within 50 feet. If successful, it deals no Wounds, but the target must instantly drop to the ground (Prone) and is completely Stunned for 1 round, overwhelmed by the genie's dominant aura. A Willpower(12) test is allowed to ignore the effects."
    ],
