      "Silverwood Hunting Bow, Ceremonial Dagger, Silk Tunic",
      "Ceremonial Dagger",
      "Hunting Bow",
      "Passive Traits\nFey Blood: Despite their lack of training, ancient magic still runs in their veins. They are completely immune to magical sleep.\n\nFleet-Footed Panic: Their natural instinct when hurt is to run. If the Conscript takes any Wounds during a round, they instantly gain a free, out-of-turn Reaction to move up to 15 feet directly away from the source of the damage, ignoring Difficult Terrain.\n\nUnconditioned Frame: Because their Physical stat is exactly 0, they struggle to absorb heavy kinetic impacts. If a Conscript is hit by a Melee attack that deals Bludgeoning Wounds (like a hammer or club), they automatically fail any test to remain standing and are knocked Prone.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTrembling Strike (Cost: 1 Action): A desperate, wild slash with a short blade. Make a Melee attack (+1 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 5 Slashing Wounds.\n\nHunting Volley (Cost: 1 Action): The Elf nocks an arrow and fires at the closest threat. Make a Ranged attack (+1 To-Hit) against a target up to 60 feet away. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 10 Piercing Wounds.\n\nDesperate Evasion (Cost: 1 Action): The Conscript focuses entirely on survival, ducking and weaving. Until the start of their next turn, their Defense is increased to a 6, but they cannot make free attacks of opportunity while cowering."
    ],
