      "Thalasien Curved Glaive, Silverwood Longbow, Gilded Leaf-Armor",
      "Thalasien Glaive.",
      "Silverwood Longbow",
      "Passive Traits\nUnearthly Grace: The Elf is a master of their environment. They completely ignore all Movement penalties from Difficult Terrain. Furthermore, any time they are subjected to an Agility test to avoid a trap or an area-of-effect spell (like a Fireball), they automatically take 0 Wounds on a success, rather than half.\n\nPerfect Parry: The Elf uses their enemy's momentum against them. If an attacker targets the Elf with a Melee attack and misses their 7 Defense, the Elf can immediately use a Reaction to take a free 5-foot step in any direction without triggering attacks of opportunity.\n\nFey Trance: Decades of mental discipline make their minds an impenetrable fortress. They are completely immune to magical sleep, and any attempt to inflict the Charmed or Taunted conditions on them automatically fails.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nFlurry of Leaves (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): A blindingly fast combination of strikes. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Slashing Wounds, and the Elf may immediately make a free Ranged attack (+3 To-Hit) with a throwing dagger against a secondary target within 15 feet for 10 Wounds.\n\nSilverwood Volley (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Elf draws and fires two arrows in the blink of an eye. Make two Ranged attacks (+3 To-Hit) against the same or different targets within 80 feet. Each successful hit deals 1d10 + 12 Piercing Wounds.\n\nFluid Posture (Cost: 1 Action): The Elf shifts into a purely defensive, evasive kata. Until the start of their next turn, their Defense becomes an 8, and all Ranged attacks made against them suffer Disadvantage as they blur out of the way of projectiles."
