      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nUnblinking Awareness: The Scryer has 360-degree vision. It cannot be flanked, and any Stealth checks made within 50Ft of the Scryer suffer a -5 penalty.\n\nPhase Blink: Once per turn, if a melee attack misses the Scryer, it may immediately teleport up to 15Ft in any direction as a free reaction.\n\nLogical Superiority: The Scryer’s attacks ignore all non-magical Wound Mitigation (Armor). It strikes at the \"essence,\" not the plate.\n\nActions\nGaze of Dissolution (2 Actions): Type: Ranged Attack (Range: 60Ft). Effect: d10 + range wound bonus. If the target has a magical item, the damage is increased by +5 as the beam \"feeds\" on the item’s energy.\n\nReality Anchor (2 Actions):Type: Debuff / Crowd Control. Contested Willpower check. Effect: On a success, the target is \"Anchored.\" Their Agility is treated as 1 for the next turn, and they cannot take any Movement actions.\n\nShatter Perception (4 Actions - Full Turn): Type: Area of Effect (25Ft Burst). Effect: Every creature in the burst takes 20 Mental Damage and must spend 1 extra Action for every move they make during their next turn (e.g., your Fighter’s sword swing would cost 3 Actions instead of 2)."
