      "Fey Nymph: The Grove-Warden",
      "Medium",
      "Fey / Spirit",
      "",
      "Hauntingly beautiful spirits bound to sacred pools, ancient glades, or deep forest springs. To look upon a Nymph is to feel a sudden, aching despair mixed with overwhelming devotion. They wear gowns of woven starlight, spun water, or autumn leaves, their forms possessing an unearthly, flawless grace. They are fiercely protective of their domain and view mortal trespassers as crude, destructive beasts. A Nymph does not fight with brute force; she fights with blinding beauty, elemental magic, and treacherous charms that turn a tightly-knit adventuring party against each other in seconds.\n\nElemental Wrath & Fey Charm",
