      "",
      "",
      "None",
      "None",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nUnearthly Grace (Sanctuary): The Nymph’s beauty is a weapon. Any enemy that attempts to target the Nymph with an attack or hostile spell must first pass a severe Willpower(8) test. On a failure, they are overcome by her beauty, their attack is completely canceled (wasting the Action), and they cannot target her until the start of their next turn.\n\nOne with the Grove: The Nymph can step through a living tree or a pool of water and instantly emerge from another tree or pool within 60 feet without spending an Action (once per turn). She completely ignores all natural Difficult Terrain.\n\nAura of Awe: The air around the Nymph is thick with fey magic. Any enemy that begins their turn within 30 feet of the Nymph must pass a Charisma(9) test or gain Disadvantage on all attacks for the round, their hands shaking with the desire to protect her rather than harm her.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBlinding Beauty (Cost: 2 Actions): The Nymph drops her magical veil, revealing the true, unfiltered magnitude of her fey nature. All enemies within a 40-foot radius that can see her must pass a severe Willpower(11) test. On a failure, they take 25 Psychic/Radiant Wounds and are permanently Blinded until magically cured, their mortal eyes burned out by her perfection.\n\nFey-Kissed Devotion(TN8) (Cost: 1 Action): She whispers a command wrapped in enchanting magic. Target one enemy within 60 feet. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, the target is Charmed. On their next turn, the Charmed target MUST use their Actions to move toward and attack their closest ally, shouting about how they must protect the Grove-Warden. A Willpower(12) test is allowed to resist the spell effects.\n\nGrasping Roots (Cost: 1 Action): The Nymph commands the earth to defend her. Target up to two enemies within 40 feet. They must pass an Agility(8) test or take 15 Bludgeoning Wounds and become Restrained as thick, thorny vines erupt from the soil to pin them in place."
