      "Gnarled Staff of Petrified Bog-Wood, Resonance Stones",
      "Petrified Bog-Wood Staff",
      "Hexes & Miasma",
      "Passive Traits\nSentient Shroud: The Witch Queen is constantly enveloped in a clinging, living mist. All Ranged physical attacks made against her suffer Disadvantage. Furthermore, any enemy that begins their turn adjacent to the Meargh takes 5 Cold Wounds as the mist actively tries to freeze their lungs.\n\nPower of Three (Resonance): The Fimir are bound to the sacred number three. At the start of the Witch Queen's turn, she generates 1 \"Resonance Point\" (up to a maximum of 3). She can spend these points to empower her Relics or her spells.\n\nBaleful Milk-White Eye: The Meargh's oversized eye grants her absolute True Sight up to 60 feet. She automatically succeeds on tests to see through illusions, invisibility, and magical obscuration.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBog-Wood Smite (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): She swings her gnarled, bone-adorned staff with immense hidden strength. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Bludgeoning Wounds, and she instantly generates 1 additional Resonance Point from the kinetic impact.\n\nCurse of the Drowning Lung(TN9) (Cost: 2 Actions): The Witch Queen locks her baleful eye onto a target and fills their lungs with swamp water. Make a Casting attack (+5 To-Hit) against a target within 40 feet. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 35 Magic/Cold Wounds, and the target is Silenced for 1 round. (Spend 3 Resonance: This spell hits up to 3 different targets simultaneously).\n\nCommand the Mist (Cost: 1 Action): The Meargh directs her sentient fog to violently reposition an enemy. Target one creature within 30 feet. They must pass a Physique(8) test or be physically dragged 15 feet in any direction by the living fog, potentially into hazardous terrain or the waiting clubs of her Fen-Ghul warriors."
