      "Heavy Driftwood Club",
      "Driftwood Club & Tail",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nSlippery Bile: The constant excretion of toxic slime makes them nearly impossible to hold. The Bog-Grunt is completely immune to the Grappled and Restrained conditions from physical sources (like nets or wrestling). Any player who attempts an unarmed strike against the Grunt takes 2 Poison Wounds from the skin contact.\n\nSwamp-Tread: They are perfectly adapted to their miserable homes. They completely ignore Movement penalties from mud, deep water, and swamp-based Difficult Terrain.\n\nMist-Parasite: While they cannot conjure the magical fog, they thrive in it. If a Bog-Grunt is standing within the Conjured Fog Bank of an allied Fen-Ghul (or natural heavy fog), they automatically gain Advantage on Willpower tests to resist Fear or Intimidation, emboldened by the concealment.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nCrude Bash (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): A heavy, overhead swing with a driftwood club or a sweeping tail strike. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 12 Bludgeoning Wounds.\n\nYellow Phlegm (Range Cost: 1 Action): The Grunt snorts and spits a concentrated glob of bile. Make a Ranged attack against a target within 15 feet. On a hit, it deals 5 Poison Wounds and the target must pass a Physique(5) test or gain the Blinded condition for 1 round as the slime burns their eyes.\n\nLumbering Charge (Cost: 2 Actions): The Grunt lowers its head and barrels forward. It moves up to 20 feet in a straight line and immediately makes a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If this attack hits, it deals 1d10 + 15 Bludgeoning Wounds and the target is knocked Prone."
