      "A massive, hunchbacked humanoid with a singular, baleful eye and a thick, saurian tail ending in a heavy bone club. Their skin is a sickly, jaundiced yellow or mossy green, always slick with a layer of toxic bile. Lacking noses, they possess a slit-like maw that exhales a constant, freezing yellow mist. Biologically tied to The Mists, they are rarely seen in direct sunlight, choosing instead to travel within magical fog banks they conjure themselves. To encounter a Fimir is to first lose your sense of direction, hear the wet thwump of a tail-club, and finally see a single, glowing eye peering through the haze just before the end.",
