      "Rusted Swamp-Blade (Optional), Bone Tail-Club",
      "Bone Tail-Club, Rusted Swamp-Blade(+25/2H)",
      "Throwing Weapon",
      "Passive Traits\nConjured Fog Bank: The Fimir is constantly surrounded by a 30-foot radius of thick, magical yellow fog. This area is considered Heavily Obscured (Total Concealment) to all non-Fimir, imposing Disadvantage on all Ranged attacks fired into or through the fog. The fog moves with the Fimir and extinguishes normal torches.\n\nToxic Bile Slick: The creature's skin is a weapon. Any enemy that attempts to Grapple the Fimir, or successfully hits it with an unarmed strike, automatically takes 5 Poison Wounds and gains 1 Poisoned condition. Furthermore, the Fimir automatically succeeds on checks to escape grapples or nets.\n\nBaleful Cyclops Eye: The Fimir's singular eye is adapted to The Mists. It completely ignores all visual penalties caused by fog, smoke, dim light, or magical darkness, allowing it to see its prey perfectly while remaining totally hidden.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTail-Club Thwump (Cost: 1 Action): The Fimir spins, bringing its heavy saurian tail around in a brutal arc. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Bludgeoning Wounds. The target must pass a Physique(8) test or be violently knocked Prone into the swamp water.\n\nFreezing Yellow Exhalation (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Fimir opens its slit-like maw, exhaling a concentrated blast of its toxic mist. Make a Ranged attack (+2 To-Hit) against a 15-foot cone. On a hit, targets take 2d10 + 15 Cold/Poison Wounds, and their Movement is reduced by half on their next turn as the freezing bile seizes their joints.\n\nMist-Gilde Ambush (Cost: 1 Action): The Fimir weaponizes its environment. As long as it is within its Conjured Fog Bank, it can move up to 20 feet completely silently, ignoring Difficult Terrain and never triggering attacks of opportunity."
