      "Random",
      "Celestial Flame-Whips",
      "Total Thermal Event",
      "Passive Traits\nAtmospheric Consumption: Sol-Invictus breathes the very oxygen out of the air. Any enemy starting their turn within 60 feet of the Lord must pass a severe Physique(10) test. On a failure, they suffer 15 Asphyxiation Wounds and are Silenced (unable to speak or cast verbal spells) as the air is ripped from their lungs to feed the supernova.\n\nVitrified Wake: Every step it takes melts the ground. The entire battlefield within 60 feet is permanently turned into cracked lava glass, treating it as extreme Difficult Terrain. Any non-flying character that moves more than 10 feet on their turn takes 10 Fire/Slashing Wounds from the jagged, superheated glass.\n\nPressurized Magma Armor: Standard weapons simply melt against its solid magma plating. Any physical Melee attack that fails to beat its 9 Defense or fails to overcome its 30 Armor Mitigation causes the attacker's weapon to instantly lose 1 tier of effectiveness (or shatter if non-magical) due to the intense, diamond-blue thermal heat.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nCelestial Flame-Whip (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Lord lashes out with voluminous extensions of orange, red, and blue fire. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) with a massive 30-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 60 Fire Wounds. The target is instantly pulled 15 feet closer to the Lord and gains 2 Burning conditions(2d10 wounds).\n\nTotal Thermal Event (Range Cost: 3 Actions): Sol-Invictus opens its blocky stone mask, unleashing the hyper-concentrated power of its blue geode core. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against a massive 80-foot cone. On a hit, targets take 4d10 + 50 Fire/Radiant Wounds. The blast completely vaporizes all non-magical cover, water sources, and environmental structures in its path.\n\nMaelstrom of Smoke (Cost: 1 Action): The Lord forcibly vents the dense black and gray smoke from its fissures. A 40-foot radius around the Lord becomes heavily obscured (Total Concealment). All enemies caught in the smoke are instantly Blinded until they can move out of the cloud, making them easy prey for the Flame-Whips."
    ],
