      "None",
      "Plasma Lashes",
      "Pyroclastic Flow",
      "Passive Traits\nGlass-Maker Aura: Every step the Cinder Lord takes turns stone to glass. Any ground within 40 feet of the Lord becomes severe Difficult Terrain. At the end of the Lord's turn, any non-flying enemy within this radius takes 15 Fire Wounds and their Armor Mitigation is reduced by 5 as their gear begins to melt and warp.\n\nShifting Volcanic Shell: The Lord is protected by brittle but superheated glass. If a physical Melee attack successfully deals Wounds to the Lord, the glass shatters, dealing 10 Fire/Slashing Wounds back to the attacker. Furthermore, the Lord is completely immune to the Grappled and Restrained conditions.\n\nSupernova Gaze: To look upon the Cinder Lord is to invite blindness. Any player character that starts their turn within 60 feet of the Lord and has line-of-sight must pass a Willpower(10) test. On a failure, they are Blinded for 1 round.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nPyroclastic Exhalation (Range Cost: 3 Actions): The Lord unhinges its silhouette, exhaling a 100-foot cone of white-hot ash and gas. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit). On a hit, targets take 1d10 + 40 Fire Wounds and 2 Burning conditions. This ash lingers for 3 rounds, creating a zone of total concealment that deals 10 Fire Wounds to anyone inside.\n\nCrystalline Whip (Cost: 1 Action): The Lord lashes out with an arm of semi-solid glass and plasma. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) against a single target within 30 feet. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 45 Wounds. If the target is reduced to 50% Health or less by this attack, they are Stunned as the glass shards embed in their flesh.\n\nMountain-Collapse Resonance (Cost: 1 Action): The Cinder Lord speaks with the voice of a dying mountain. All enemies within 50 feet must pass a Physique(9) test. On a failure, they take 30 Sonic/Fire Wounds and are knocked Prone and Deafened for 1 round by the overwhelming resonance."
    ],
