      "1-10",
      "None",
      "Scorching Touch",
      "Spitting a glob of plasma up to 50Ft",
      "Passive Traits\nHeat Mirage: The shimmering air around the sprite warps light and trajectory. All non-magical Ranged attacks made against the Ember-Sprite automatically suffer Disadvantage.\n\nInsubstantial Plasma: Because its Physical stat is exactly 0, normal weapons pass right through its flames. Any physical Melee or Ranged attack that successfully hits the sprite automatically has its Wounds halved. However, any Cold or Water-based attacks deal double Wounds to it.\n\nOrganic Fuel-Hunger: The sprite becomes exponentially more dangerous when it finds tinder. Any time the Ember-Sprite successfully deals Wounds to a target that is primarily organic (flesh, leather armor, wood, or plant-matter), the target automatically gains 1 Burning condition.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nScorching Touch (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The sprite lashes out to consume its prey. Make a Melee attack (+1 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 10 Fire Wounds.\n\nFrantic Flicker (Cost: 1 Action): The sprite instantly darts up to 20 feet without triggering attacks of opportunity. It leaves a trail of white-hot embers in every square it passes through. Any enemy stepping into these squares takes 5 Fire Wounds.\n\nFeed the Hearth (Cost: 2 Actions): The sprite latches onto a target to rapidly consume their organic gear. Make a Melee attack (+1 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 15 Fire Wounds and the sprite instantly heals 5 Wounds as it absorbs the heat of the burning material."
    ],
