      "Dripping Magma Lashes",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Glass-Walker: The elemental melts the ground it walks on. Any space the Fire Elemental occupies or moves through is instantly turned into superheated, molten glass. This creates severe Difficult Terrain. Any non-flying enemy that starts their turn on or moves through this glass takes 10 Fire Wounds and their movement speed is halved.\n\nBlinding Magma Shell: Striking the creature is inherently dangerous. If a player successfully hits the elemental with a physical Melee attack, the magma shell cracks, splashing the attacker with liquid fire for 5 Fire Wounds. Additionally, if the attacker rolls a Critical Hit, the blinding white light of the core flashes, instantly Blinding the attacker for 1 round.\n\nSearing Liquid Air: The ambient temperature around the elemental is lethal. Any enemy starting their turn within 15 feet of the elemental must pass a Physique(8) test or suffer 1 Exhausted condition from heatstroke and dehydration.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nMagma Lash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The elemental swings a dripping, whip-like arm of magma. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit) against a target up to 15 feet away. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 25 Fire/Slashing Wounds, and the target gains 1 Burning condition (1d10 wounds).\n\nSolar Flare Burst (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The elemental intentionally forces its spinning white core to vent. Make a Ranged attack (+3 To-Hit) against all targets in a 20-foot radius. On a hit, targets take 2d10 + 20 Fire/Radiant Wounds, and are pushed 10 feet backward by the concussive thermal shockwave.\n\nLava Current (Cost: 1 Action): The elemental momentarily collapses its humanoid shape into a rushing wave of magma, moving up to 30 feet in a straight line. It can freely pass through enemy spaces during this movement. Any enemy it passes through automatically takes 15 Fire Wounds and must pass an Agility(8) test or fall Prone."
    ],
