      "1-2",
      "Singe-Plate Armor, Magma-Forged Greatsword or Cinder-Maul",
      "Magma-Forged Weapon",
      "Hurling chunks of molten slag",
      "Passive Traits\nSinge-Plate Integration: The giant's armor is bolted into its flesh, making it impossible to disarm or sunder. Any melee attacker who successfully hits the Fire Giant with a non-reach weapon takes 10 Fire Wounds instantly from the radiating heat of the black iron plates.\n\nMaster Smith's Edge: The Forge-Father's weapons cut through stone like warm wax. All of the Fire Giant's Melee attacks completely ignore the first 5 points of a target's Armor Mitigation and deal double Wounds to environmental cover, shields, and structures.\n\nWall of Lava: The giant is built like a heavy-duty anvil. It is completely immune to the Knockback, Prone, and Grappled conditions from any creature smaller than Giant size, and it ignores all Difficult Terrain caused by rubble, fire, or magma.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nCinder-Maul Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A brutal, calculated overhead swing. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) with a 15-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 40 Bludgeoning/Fire Wounds, and the target's armor (if non-magical) loses 10 Wound Mitigation for the rest of the encounter as it melts and buckles.\n\nSlag Cleave (Melee Cost: 3 Actions): The Giant sweeps its Magma-Forged Greatsword in a massive horizontal arc. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) against up to three adjacent targets within its reach. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 70 Slashing/Fire Wounds and applies 2 Burning conditions to each struck target.\n\nEruption Stomp (Cost: 1 Action): The Giant brings its massive, iron-shod boot down with the force of a tectonic shift. All enemies within 30 feet must pass an Agility(12) test or be knocked Prone and take 20 Bludgeoning Wounds from the resulting localized earthquake."
    ],
