      "Fire Snake: The Ember-Viper",
      "Large",
      "Elemental / Beast",
      "",
      "An Ember-Viper looks like a river of liquid gold given form and hunger. Its scales are interlocking plates of cooling obsidian that glow with a fierce, internal orange light. Instead of a rattle, its tail ends in a cluster of porous volcanic stones that hiss and spark, filling the air with a sulfurous haze. They don't leave footprints—they leave scorch marks. They can \"melt\" into pools of lava or hide within the smoke of a campfire, waiting for the perfect moment to strike. When they do, they wrap their molten bodies around their prey, turning their victim’s own armor into a pressurized oven.",
