      "Obsidian Fangs & Molten Coils",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nSmoke & Magma Camouflage: The Ember-Viper can \"melt\" into its surroundings. While within smoke, fire, or lava, the Viper is considered Invisible. Furthermore, it leaves no tracks other than scorch marks, completely ignoring Movement penalties for rocky or volcanic Difficult Terrain.\n\nThe Pressurized Oven: The Viper turns a target's defense into a death trap. Any enemy that is currently Grappled by the Ember-Viper automatically takes 15 Fire Wounds at the start of their turn. If the target is wearing medium or heavy metal armor, this damage ignores Wound Mitigation as the armor itself cooks them alive.\n\nSulfurous Rattle: The porous volcanic stones on its tail constantly hiss and spark. The area within 10 feet of the Viper is filled with a choking, sulfurous haze. Any enemy starting their turn in this aura must pass a Physique(6) test or become Exhausted from the toxic fumes.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nObsidian Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The snake lunges with fangs of superheated glass. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 30 Piercing/Fire Wounds, and the target's Wound Mitigation from armor is temporarily reduced by 3 for the rest of the encounter as the metal warps.\n\nMolten Coil (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Viper attempts to wrap its liquid-gold body around its prey. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 20 Bludgeoning Wounds, and the target is instantly Grappled and Restrained, subjecting them to The Pressurized Oven passive on their next turn. Make a physique vs physique test on the next turn in an attempt to break free.\n\nCinder Spray (Cost: 1 Action): The Viper violently whips its tail, scattering the hissing volcanic stones. All enemies in a 15-foot cone must pass an Agility(8) test or take 15 Fire Wounds and be Blinded for 1 round by the sparking ash."
