      "Flesh Golem: The Galvanized Horror",
      "Large",
      "Construct",
      "",
      "A grotesque masterpiece of mismatched anatomy, the Flesh Golem is a mountain of stitched-together muscle and bone. Standing eight feet tall and nearly four feet wide, its skin is a patchwork of pale, grey, and sallow tones held together by thick black surgical thread and rusted iron rivets. Copper rods protrude from its neck and spine, acting as conductors for the lightning that serves as its soul. It smells of formaldehyde and ozone, its every movement accompanied by the audible groaning of over-strained muscle. It is not raised; it is assembled and galvanized.",
