      "None",
      "Hammer-like Fists",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nGalvanized Absorption: Lightning is its lifeblood. The Flesh Golem is completely immune to Lightning damage. Whenever it is hit by a Lightning attack, it instead heals 15 Wounds and instantly gains +1 Action on its next turn as the copper rods surge with energy.\n\nFormaldehyde Stench: The golem is saturated in preserving chemicals. Any living creature that starts its turn adjacent to the Golem must pass a Physique(8) test or gain the Nauseated condition (Disadvantage on all rolls) for 1 round.\n\nBerserk Fracture: If the Golem takes Fire damage or its Health drops below 30%, the binding energy becomes unstable. The Golem must pass a Willpower(11) test or enter a Berserk state, attacking the nearest living creature with Advantage on all Melee attacks but losing its ability to distinguish friend from foe.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nOverstrained Slam (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Golem brings its massive, stitched fists down with a sickening groan of muscle. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 30 Bludgeoning Wounds and the target must pass a severe Physique test or be knocked Prone.\n\nCopper-Rod Discharge (Cost: 2 Actions): The Golem vents excess electrical energy through its rivets. All enemies within a 10-foot radius must make an Agility(9) test. On a failure, they take 20 Lightning Wounds and are Stunned (Movement reduced to 0 and cannot take Reactions) until the start of their next turn.\n\nStitched Grip & Crush (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Golem grabs a target with its trunk-like arms. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, the target is Grappled and Restrained. The Golem can use its next Action to deal an automatic 30 Bludgeoning Wounds to the grabbed target as it crushes their ribs."
