      "Megafauna Pelts, Permafrost Armor, True-Ice Greataxe or Mammoth-Bone Club",
      "True-Ice Weapon",
      "Hurling permafrost boulders with siege-engine accuracy",
      "Passive Traits\nCloak of the Blizzard: The Frost Giant uses storms as camouflage. They are completely immune to vision penalties from snow, fog, or blizzards. Furthermore, if the Giant is fighting in a snowy environment, it constantly projects a 30-foot aura of freezing fog that grants it Concealment, imposing Disadvantage on all Ranged attacks directed at it.\n\nAvalanche Stride: The giant walks through mountains as easily as open fields. It completely ignores all Difficult Terrain caused by ice, deep snow, or rubble. Because of its massive footing, it is completely immune to the Prone and Knockback conditions from any creature smaller than Giant size.\n\nDiamond-Hard Permafrost: The ice armor is harder than steel and destroys lesser weapons. If a player strikes the Frost Giant with a non-magical melee weapon and fails to overcome its 25 Armor Mitigation, the weapon takes a permanent -1 penalty to its damage output as the metal becomes brittle and cracks from the supernatural cold.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nGlacial Cleave (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Giant swings a massive weapon of true-ice. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) with a 15-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 50 Slashing/Cold Wounds.\n\nPermafrost Shrapnel (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Giant hurls a massive boulder coated in unmelting ice. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against a primary target up to 80 feet away. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 40 Bludgeoning Wounds. Regardless of whether the attack hits or misses the primary target, the boulder shatters on impact into a 15-foot radius burst. All creatures in the burst must pass an Agility(11) test or take 30 Piercing/Cold Wounds from the flying shrapnel.\n\nBreath of the Megafauna (Cost: 1 Action): The Giant exhales the freezing fog from its lungs in a concentrated 30-foot cone. All enemies caught in the blast must pass a Physique(12) test. On a failure, they gain 1 Exhausted condition and have their Movement reduced by half on their next turn due to the biting cold seizing their joints."
