      "1",
      "Random Undigested Loot (1d6 Gold Coins, a rusty dagger, a dwarven skull).",
      "Acidic Pseudopod",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nTransparent Ambusher: The Cube is nearly invisible in dim light or darkness. If the Cube has not yet moved or attacked this round, any player entering its line of sight must pass a severe Awareness test. On a failure, the player doesn't see the Cube until they physically walk directly into it, automatically suffering the effects of the Engulf ability.\n\nAmorphous Hallway-Blocker: The Cube perfectly fills a standard 10x10 dungeon corridor. It is completely immune to the Prone, Knockback, Flanked, and Bleeding conditions. You cannot move past it or through it without being digested.\n\nAnesthetic Slime: The outer layer of the Cube is coated in a paralyzing numbing agent. Any target that takes Melee damage from the Cube must pass a Physique(8) test or have their Movement reduced to 0 on their next turn as their muscles seize.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nPseudopod Lash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Cube extrudes a wobbly tentacle of acid. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit) against an adjacent target. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 20 Acid/Bludgeoning Wounds.\n\nEngulf (Cost: 2 Actions): The Cube simply flows forward to occupy an enemy's space. Target one adjacent creature. That creature must make an Agility(9) test. On a failure, they are pulled inside the Cube. An engulfed target is Grappled, Restrained, and Silenced (cannot breathe or cast verbal spells). At the start of the Cube's turn, any engulfed targets automatically take 20 Acid Wounds.\n\nDigestive Pulse (Cost: 1 Action): The Cube churns its internal acids. It deals an immediate 15 Acid Wounds to any targets currently Engulfed within it."
    ],
