    "values": [
      "Ghast (The Bone-Snapper)",
      "Large",
      "Undead",
      "",
      "A Ghoul eats because it is hungry. A Ghast eats because it enjoys the sound of bone snapping. Towering over standard ghouls, this Large monstrosity is a cruel, calculated predator with elongated, muscular limbs and an unnaturally wide jaw. It doesn't just skitter; it stalks, watching your formation with wicked intelligence to find the one person who looks tired. It delights in psychological terror just as much as the physical kill, using its explosive leaping ability to bypass armored defenders and land directly on the party's most vulnerable member.",
