      "None",
      "Bone-Snapping Jaws & Rending Claws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nLeaper: The Ghast's leg muscles are coiled springs of necrotic energy. It can jump 20 feet horizontally as part of a Move action. This jump ignores all Difficult Terrain and allows it to pass directly over the heads of enemy frontline defenders without triggering free attacks of opportunity.\n\nStalker of the Tired: The Ghast instinctively targets weakness. It automatically gains Advantage on all Melee To-Hit rolls against targets that currently have the Exhausted, Prone, or Bleeding conditions, or any target below 50% of their maximum Health.\n\nGrave-Stench: The creature exudes a horrific, cloying aura of rot. Any living creature that begins its turn within 10 feet of the Ghast must pass a severe Physique(6) test. On a failure, they spend 1 Action violently retching and gain 1 Poisoned condition.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBone-Snapping Bite (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Ghast unhinges its jaw to crush a limb. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 20 Piercing/Bludgeoning Wounds. The target must pass a severe Physique test or suffer a broken bone, reducing their Movement by half until magically healed.\n\nParalyzing Slash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Ghast's claws are coated in a specialized, necrotizing venom. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 20 Slashing Wounds and the target must pass a Willpower(5) test or become Paralyzed (unable to move or take Actions) until the end of their next turn.\n\nSavor the Snap (Cost: 2 Actions): The Ghast targets a Paralyzed or Prone enemy. It automatically hits (no To-Hit roll required) and deals 40 Wounds. The sickening sound of the execution forces all allies of the target within 30 feet to make a Willpower test or gain 1 Frightened condition."
    ],
