      "0",
      "None",
      "7",
      "1-4",
      "None",
      "Spectral Touch",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nIncorporeal Form: The Ghost can pass freely through solid objects, walls, and other creatures. It is completely immune to the Grappled, Prone, and Restrained conditions. Furthermore, any non-magical physical attack that successfully hits the Ghost automatically has its total Wounds reduced to 0 (the weapon simply passes through the mist).\n\nLife-Sense: The Ghost does not see with eyes. It tracks the soul. It can perfectly detect living creatures through walls and solid cover up to 60 feet away, and it ignores all visual penalties from magical darkness or smoke.\n\nUnnatural Chill: The ambient temperature plummets in the Ghost's presence. Any living creature that starts its turn within 15 feet of the Ghost loses 1 Focus point and has its Movement reduced by 5 feet as the supernatural frost seeps into their joints.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nGrave Touch (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Ghost reaches its translucent hand directly into a target's chest. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 15 Cold/Necrotic Wounds. Because this attack targets the soul, it completely ignores the target's Armor Mitigation.\n\nPoltergeist Throw (Range Cost: 1 Action): The Ghost weaponizes its Willpower to violently hurl a loose object (a chair, a rock, a loose weapon). Make a Ranged attack (+3 To-Hit) against a target within 30 feet. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 10 Bludgeoning or Piercing Wounds, depending on the object.\n\nHorrifying Visage (Cost: 2 Actions): The Ghost drops its mundane appearance to reveal the gruesome, terrifying reality of its death. All living enemies within 30 feet that can see the Ghost must pass a severe Willpower(10) test. On a failure, they take 15 Psychic Wounds and gain the Frightened condition, forcing them to move away from the Ghost on their next turn."
    ],
    "imgSrc": ""
