    "values": [
      "Ghoul (The Grave-Feaster)",
      "Medium",
      "Undead",
      "",
      "A gaunt, wiry humanoid with skin like stretched, grey parchment. They are deceptively strong, their muscles corded and dense from a diet of mineral-rich marrow. Their most terrifying features are elongated, multi-jointed fingers ending in filth-encrusted claws, and a jaw that can unhinge to reveal rows of needle-like teeth. They carry the \"Stench of the Pit\"—a cloying, sweet smell of decay. Unlike mindless zombies, Ghouls are cunning; they won't charge a line of shields. They linger in the rafters of a tomb or the shadows of a sewer, waiting to paralyze a straggler and drag them into the darkness to be eaten alive.",
      "6",
      "4",
