      "4-20",
      "None",
      "Filth-Encrusted Claws & Needle-Teeth",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nClimber: The Ghoul's elongated fingers allow it to move across walls and ceilings at its full 30 Movement speed without needing to make Agility tests. It can freely hang upside down while making Melee attacks.\n\nStench of the Pit: A cloying, sweet smell of decay precedes them. Any living creature that starts its turn within 10 feet of one or more Ghouls must pass a Physique(5) test or suffer Disadvantage on all Awareness and Intelligence tests for the round as the smell induces severe nausea.\n\nCunning Opportunist: The Grave-Feaster knows how to exploit an isolated target. If the Ghoul attacks an enemy that has no conscious allies within 10 feet of them, or an enemy that is Prone or Paralyzed, the Ghoul automatically gains Advantage on its Melee To-Hit rolls.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nFilth-Encrusted Scratch (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A swipe with bacteria-ridden claws. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 10 Slashing Wounds and the target must pass a Physique(5) test or become Paralyzed (unable to move or take Actions) until the start of their next turn.\n\nUnhinged Bite (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Ghoul bites down with rows of needle-like teeth. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 10 Piercing Wounds. If the target is Paralyzed, this attack automatically hits (no roll required) and heals the Ghoul for 5 Wounds as it gorges on the fresh meat.\n\nDrag into the Dark (Cost: 1 Action): The Ghoul grabs a Paralyzed or Prone target and scuttles away. The Ghoul moves up to 15 feet (including up walls or ceilings), physically carrying the target into its space. The target remains in the Ghoul's grasp until they break free."
    ],
