      "None",
      "Colossal Fists",
      "Hurled Jungle Debris",
      "Passive Traits\nIron-Grey Pelage: The Titan's thick fur acts as natural armor against projectiles. All non-magical Ranged attacks (arrows, bolts, throwing axes) automatically suffer Disadvantage to wound.\n\nJungle Arsenal: The Titan can weaponize its environment. It can uproot trees or tear chunks of bedrock from the earth without spending an Action. Furthermore, its Ranged attacks deal \"Siege Damage,\" inflicting double Wounds to environmental structures, walls, or vehicles.\n\nApex Unstoppable: Due to its immense size and strength, the Silverback Titan is completely immune to the Prone, Grappled, and Restrained conditions from any creature smaller than Giant size. It also completely ignores all Movement penalties from jungle or forest Difficult Terrain.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTree-Shattering Slam (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Titan brings two massive fists crashing down. Make a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 2d10 + 60 Bludgeoning Wounds, and the target must pass a Physique(12) test or be violently knocked 20 feet backward and rendered Prone.\n\nColossal Hurl (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Ape rips a massive boulder or tree trunk from the ground and hurls it across the battlefield. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) targeting a 15-foot radius area up to 80 feet away. On a hit, all enemies in the zone take 3d10 + 20 Bludgeoning Wounds and are pinned under the debris (Movement reduced to 0 until they use an Action to free themselves).\n\nTerritorial Chest-Beat (Cost: 1 Action): The Titan rises to its full 20-foot height, unleashing a deafening, primordial roar while beating its chest. All enemies within 60 feet must pass a Willpower(10) test or become Frightened and Deafened for 1 round, suffering a -2 penalty to their Defense due to the sheer terror of the display."
    ],
