      "Giant Rat: The Sewer-Scourge",
      "Large",
      "Beast / Monstrosity",
      "",
      "A bloated, man-sized rodent that thrives in the darkest, dampest corners of civilization. The Giant Rat possesses coarse, wiry fur matted with sewer filth and blood, and a hairless, whip-like tail thick as a ship's mooring line. Driven by perpetual hunger and malice, their eyes reflect a sickly yellow in the torchlight, and their rusted-iron incisors can gnaw through solid oak and bone alike. The most dangerous aspect of a Giant Rat is its Tainted Blood. Their veins pulse with a black, viscous fluid that is a cocktail of every plague known to the underworld. When wounded, they don't just bleed; they spray a pressurized mist of infection that can rot leather and blister skin on contact.",
