      "2-10",
      "None",
      "Rusted-Iron Incisors",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nTainted Blood Spray: The rat's circulatory system is a pressurized biological weapon. Any time the Giant Rat takes Slashing or Piercing Wounds from a Melee attack, it sprays a mist of black, toxic fluid. The attacker must pass an Agility(8) test or take 10 Acid/Poison Wounds. If the attacker fails the test, their non-magical armor also loses 1 Wound Mitigation as the acidic blood rots the leather and rusts the iron.\n\nSewer-Skulker: The Scourge is perfectly adapted to its miserable environment. It completely ignores all Movement penalties from water, mud, or sludge, and its yellow eyes grant it perfect vision in total darkness.\n\nVermin Swarm Tactics: The Scourge knows how to overwhelm struggling prey. The Giant Rat automatically gains Advantage on its Melee To-Hit rolls against any target that is adjacent to another conscious Giant Rat, or any target that has the Prone condition.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nIron-Incisor Bite (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The rat lunges, sinking its rusted-iron teeth into the target. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 21 Piercing Wounds. If the target is wearing a shield, the rat can choose to deal 0 Wounds to the target and instead permanently destroy the shield by gnawing through the wood and metal.\n\nMooring-Line Tail Whip (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The rat spins, sweeping its thick, hairless tail across the ground. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit) against up to two adjacent enemies. On a hit, it deals 15 Bludgeoning Wounds and the targets must pass a Physique(8) test or be knocked Prone.\n\nRabid Gnaw (Cost: 2 Actions): The rat pins a Prone target and frenzies. It automatically hits (no To-Hit roll required) and deals 30 Piercing/Poison Wounds. The target immediately gains 1 Poisoned condition and 1 Bleeding condition from the filthy bites."
    ],
