      "Iron-Hard Fangs",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nWeb-Sense & Master Climber: The Grave-Weaver ignores all Movement penalties for climbing, allowing it to rest perfectly upside down on ceilings. Furthermore, while in contact with its web, it knows the exact, pinpoint location of any other creature touching the web, completely ignoring magical invisibility or darkness.\n\nBarbed Carapace: The spider is covered in jagged, irritating hairs. Any creature that successfully strikes the spider with an unarmed Melee attack, or attempts to Grapple it, automatically takes 5 Piercing/Poison Wounds and must pass a Physique test or become Blinded for 1 round by the loose hairs.\n\nAmbush Predator: If the Grave-Weaver attacks a target that has the Restrained, Prone, or Surprised condition, the spider's Melee attacks automatically deal Maximum Wounds (no rolling for damage) as it accurately strikes the vital organs.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nIron-Fang Lunge (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The spider sinks its dripping mandibles into its prey. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 21 Piercing/Poison Wounds. The target must pass a Physique((8) test or gain the Paralyzed condition for 1 round as the venom locks their muscles.\n\nEnsnaring Grave-Silk (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The spider rears back and sprays a thick, sticky net of silk. Make a Ranged attack (+3 To-Hit) against a target up to 40 feet away. On a hit, the target takes no Wounds but is instantly Restrained and anchored to the floor (Movement becomes 0). The target must use an Action and pass a Physical(9) test on their turn to tear the web apart.\n\nHoist the Kill (Cost: 1 Action): The spider grabs a Paralyzed or Restrained target and effortlessly drags them. The spider moves up to its full 24 Movement speed (including straight up a wall or tree), carrying the target into its space to separate them from their allies."
