      "Scavenged Rusted Cleaver, Patchwork Hide Armor",
      "Rusted Cleaver.",
      "Javelin or Short Bow",
      "Passive Traits\nBlood Scent: The Gnoll gains an immediate Advantage on Awareness tests when tracking or locating any creature that currently has the Bleeding condition or is below its maximum Wound Threshold.\n\nPack Tactics: When attacking a target currently engaged by at least one other allied creature, the Gnoll automatically gains +3 damage to successful Melee strikes sensing an easy kill.\n\nCarrion Gut: The creature’s physiology is adapted to the wastes. It is completely immune to the Poisoned condition if the source is ingested, and immune to all non-magical Diseases.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nScavenger's Cleave (Cost: 1 Action): The Gnoll hacks wildly with its rusted weapon. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 11 Slashing Wounds. If the Gnoll scores a Critical Hit, the target gains 1 Bleeding condition.\n\nSavage Bite (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Gnoll lunges with snapping jaws. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 15 Piercing Wounds. This attack ignores up to 3 points of the target's WM-Arm (Armor Mitigation) if the target is Grappled or Prone.\n\nUnnerving Cackle (Cost: 1 Action): The Gnoll unleashes a manic, echoing laugh that unsettles the soul. All enemies within 30 feet must pass a Willpower(6) test. On a failure, they gain the Stunned condition until the end of their next turn, overwhelmed by the disorienting noise."
