      "Ancestral Bone Charms, Ritual Dagger",
      "Bone Staff (2H) ",
      "Spiritual Venom",
      "Passive Traits\nOzone Aura: The air around the Shaman crackles with volatile magic. Any enemy that successfully strikes the Shaman with a Melee attack automatically takes 5 Lightning Wounds from the static backlash.\n\nHeart of the Swarm: As long as the Shaman is conscious and on the battlefield, all allied Goblins within 60 feet are completely immune to the Frightened and Charmed conditions.\n\nFrail but Guarded: The Shaman uses its metaphysical connection to protect its fragile body. The Shaman may use its Willpower stat (6) in place of its Physical stat (0) when making tests to resist being knocked Prone, Grappled, or Poisoned.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSpiritual Venom(TN6) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Shaman channels the malice of the cave spirits into a concentrated bolt of green energy. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit) against a target within 40 feet. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 185 Necrotic/Poison Wounds, and the target must pass a Willpower(9) test or gain 1 Poisoned condition as the venom attacks their soul.\n\nBlood-Drenched Totem(TN10)(Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Shaman hurls a cluster of bone charms that embed into the ground, creating a Blood-Totem with 10 Wounds. While the Totem is active, any allied Goblin within 30 feet of it gains the Frenzied condition (Advantage on all Melee attacks) and cannot be reduced below 1 Health. The players must physically destroy the Totem to break the unkillable state.\n\nToxic Mist Step (Cost: 1 Action): When threatened, the Shaman vanishes. The Shaman instantly teleports up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space it can see. The space the Shaman left behind is filled with a 10-foot cloud of toxic green mist for 1 round; any enemy entering or starting their turn in the mist takes 10 Poison Wounds."
