      "The accumulated knowledge and artifacts of a dozen fallen empires",
      "Feline Jaws & Golden Talons",
      "Sovereign's Incineration",
      "Passive Traits\nMortal Guise: The Sovereign can shapeshift into a medium-sized humanoid (usually a humble scholar or aged advisor) at will. While in this form, it retains its 15 Intelligence and 8 Willpower, but its Physical and Defense stats drop to mortal levels. It can revert to its Titanic true form as a free Reaction, instantly shattering the guise in a blinding flash of golden light.\n\nAura of the Arbiter: The dragon's presence enforces cosmic law. The area within 120 feet of the Sovereign is an absolute Zone of Truth; no creature can knowingly speak a lie. Furthermore, any enemy attempting to cast a hostile spell within this aura must pass a Willpower(10) test, or the spell instantly fizzles and their Action is wasted.\n\nOrganic Metal Carapace: The dragon's scales are harder than forged steel. The Sovereign is completely immune to all non-magical Slashing and Piercing damage. Any mundane weapon that strikes the dragon shatters on impact.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSovereign’s Strike (Cost: 1 Actions): The dragon sweeps its massive golden claws or snaps its feline jaws. Make a Melee attack (+7 To-Hit) with a 40-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 70 Slashing/Piercing Wounds, and the target is knocked Prone and Restrained beneath the titan's claws.\n\nStatic Whisker Lash (Cost: 3 Actions): The dragon whips its crackling, energy-infused whiskers across the battlefield. Target up to three enemies within 150 feet. They must pass a severe Agility(12) test or take 1d10 + 50 Lightning Wounds and become Stunned (lose their next Action) from the electrical shock to their nervous system.\n\nIncinerate the Imbalance (Range Cost: 4 Actions): The Sovereign opens its maw and unleashes a localized sun. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against a massive 90-foot cone. On a hit, all targets take 6d10 + 50 Radiant/Fire Wounds. This breath weapon instantly disintegrates any environmental cover, magical barriers, or structures, leaving behind only smooth, glowing glass."
