      "\"The Divider\" (Colossal Cleaver),",
      "Throwing Axes",
      "Passive Traits\nBoss Frenzy: When Grabzug drops below 30 Wounds, he enters a blood-mad frenzy. He gains +5 to all Damage but his Defense drops to 7.\n\nHeirloom Resonance: While Grabzug possesses the stolen relic, he gains Regeneration: 5. He heals 5 wounds at the start of every one of his turns.\n\nUnstoppable Momentum (Passive): Grabzug ignores movement penalties. He cannot be \"Pinned\" or \"Slowed\" by non-magical means.\n\n\nAction Based Abilities\nIron-Grip Toss (Melee Cost 1 Action)\nGrabzug drops one hand from his cleaver, seizes a nearby \"puny\" foe by the throat, and hurls them into their allies.Target must be Medium size or smaller and within 5 feet.Grabzug rolls Melee (+6) vs. the target’s Defense.On a success, the target is launched 15 feet in a direction of Grabzug's choosing. The thrown target takes 10 Wounds (flat damage) and is Prone. If the target is thrown into another player, that player must pass an Agility (Grabzug to-hit roll) Test. On a failure, they also take 10 Wounds and are knocked Prone.\n\nSkullsmasher’s Roar (Cost 1 Action): Grabzug lets out a deafening war cry. All enemies within 10 feet must pass a Willpower Test. On failure, they suffer a -2 penalty to accuracy for 1 round.\n\n"
