      "estments of the Third Order, Tri-Planar Focus Amulet",
      "Staff Strike",
      "Siege-Force Spells",
      "Passive Traits\nSiege-Weaver: The Arcanist's spells carry terrifying kinetic mass. All Casting attacks made by the Arcanist deal double Wounds to environmental cover, non-magical shields, and physical structures, shattering them into shrapnel.\n\nPlanar Synchronization: The Arcanist exists slightly out of phase with physical reality. Any non-magical Ranged attack (like arrows or bolts) has a flat 50% chance to pass harmlessly through them. Furthermore, they are completely immune to the Silenced condition, able to cast spells purely through thought.\n\nArchmage’s Rebuttal: The Arcanist casually dismantles rival magic. If targeted by a hostile spell, the Arcanist can use a free Reaction to make a Willpower(15) test. On a success, the hostile spell is instantly countered (negated), and the Arcanist absorbs the dissipated mana, granting them +1 Action on their next turn.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTri-Planar Lance(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Arcanist fires a concentrated beam of solid kinetic magic. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit) against a target within 80 feet. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 35 Force Wounds. The target must pass a severe Physique(8) test or be violently knocked 20 feet backward and rendered Prone.\n\nArcane Singularity(TN10) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Arcanist collapses the gravity in a specific zone. Target a 20-foot radius area up to 100 feet away. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, all targets inside take 3d10 + 35 Force Wounds. Any enemy within 15 feet of the outside edge of the zone must pass an Agility(6) test or be violently dragged into the center of the singularity.\n\nDimensional Fold(TN6) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): Rather than walking, the Arcanist folds space. They instantly teleport up to 60 feet to an unoccupied space they can see. The space they left behind detonates with a localized vacuum; any enemy adjacent to their starting position takes 10 Force Wounds and is Deafened for 1 round."
    ],
