      "1-6",
      "None",
      "Necrotic Fangs",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nGrave-Digger (Tremorsense): The Grave Wolf ignores Movement penalties when traveling through mud, loose earth, or graveyard soil. While burrowed, it possesses perfect Tremorsense up to 50 feet, allowing it to track moving targets above ground without needing to see them.\n\nCold-Blooded Pack Tactics: The hounds hunt with perfectly synchronized malice. A Grave Wolf automatically gains Advantage on its Melee To-Hit rolls if at least one allied Grave Wolf is adjacent to its target.\n\nBalefire Vision: The green flames in their sockets pierce the gloom. The wolf ignores all visual penalties from fog, non-magical darkness, and magical darkness.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nErupting Ambush (Melee Cost: 1 Action): Can only be used while Burrowed. The Grave Wolf bursts from the earth beneath a target's feet. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 10 Piercing Wounds, and the target must pass an Agility(5) test or be knocked Prone.\n\nLock-Jaw Lunge (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The wolf snaps its necrotic jaws shut on a limb. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 10 Piercing/Necrotic Wounds. If the target is Prone, this attack automatically applies the Grappled condition as the hound refuses to let go.\n\nDrag into the Dark (Cost: 1 Action): The wolf violently hauls a Grappled target away from their allies. The wolf moves up to 20 feet, physically dragging the target with it into an open grave or away from the party's defensive line."
