      "Abyssal Greatblade, Whip of Anguish",
      "Abyssal Greatblade",
      "Hellfire Orb",
      "Passive Traits\nAura of the Abyss: The Herald passively corrupts the world. The area within 60 feet of the Daemon is choked with sulfur and necrotic ash. Any living creature that starts its turn in this radius takes 10 Necrotic Wounds and cannot regain Wounds (healing magic completely fails) until they leave the aura.\n\nWings of the Apocalypse: The Daemon's massive, tattered wings generate hurricane-force winds. Any enemy smaller than Enormous that attempts to Move or Dash toward the Daemon must pass a severe Physique(12) test or be violently pushed 15 feet backward by the downdraft, ending their movement.\n\nSoul-Forged Carapace: The Daemon's hide is anathema to mortal steel. The Herald is completely immune to non-magical Melee attacks. Furthermore, any non-magical weapon that strikes the Daemon instantly melts into slag and is permanently destroyed.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nCleaver of the Damned (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Daemon swings its gargantuan, screaming blade. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) with a 30-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 90 Slashing/Necrotic Wounds. The target must pass a Willpower(10) test or gain 1 Frightened condition as the screaming souls trapped in the blade assault their mind.\n\nWord of Ruin (Cost: 3 Actions): The Herald speaks a single, forbidden syllable of Abyssal speech. All enemies within a 100-foot radius must pass a severe Willpower(11) test. On a failure, they take 4d10 + 20 Psychic Wounds, instantly drop any weapons they are holding, and fall Prone, physically forced to grovel before the Daemon's majesty.\n\nHellfire Eruption (Range Cost: 2 Action): The Daemon opens its maw and vomits a sphere of black fire. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against a 20-foot radius area up to 80 feet away. On a hit, all targets in the zone take 1d10 + 30 Fire/Necrotic Wounds, and the ground in that area becomes permanently ablaze, treating it as lethal Difficult Terrain for the rest of the encounter."
