      "Green Dragon: The Verdant Overlord",
      "Giant",
      "Dragon / Monstrosity",
      "",
      "A masterpiece of camouflage and serpentine grace. Its scales are a shifting mosaic of emerald, moss, and forest shadow, covered in actual lichen and ferns. A pervasive scent of pine resin and chlorine follows it like a shroud. Unlike their red cousins who burn what they cannot own, Green Dragons prefer to dominate. They are master gaslighters, keeping a court of \"servants\"—forest-folk, elves, or sprites—coerced into worshiping them. They don't just breathe poison; they breathe control. They use the forest as a weapon, leading adventurers into bogs and thickets before beginning the fight with honeyed words to sow discord among the party.\n\n(Always accompanied by 2 + 1d10 charmed \"Servants\" acting as meat shields)\n",
