      "The plundered magical artifacts of a hundred manipulated heroes.",
      "Serpentine Claws & Fangs",
      "Chlorine Gas Breath",
      "Passive Traits\nMaster of Terrain: The Green Dragon's domain is an extension of its will. It completely ignores all Movement penalties associated with dense forests, bogs, and magical thorns. Furthermore, any player moving more than 10 feet on their turn within the dragon's lair must pass an Agility test or become Restrained by suddenly shifting vines and roots.\n\nThe Verdant Court (Meat Shields): The dragon is never truly alone. If a player targets the dragon with a successful Melee or Ranged attack, the dragon can use its Reaction to force one of its charmed \"Servants\" to step into the attack's path, taking all the Wounds and effects instead.\n\nScent of Pine and Chlorine: The dragon constantly exhales a localized toxic haze. Any enemy that ends its turn within 15 feet of the dragon automatically loses 1 Focus point and suffers 5 Poison Wounds as the fumes slowly burn their lungs and cloud their mind.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSow Discord(TN11) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The dragon speaks a honeyed, deeply personal lie to a target within 60 feet. Make a Casting attack (+5 To-Hit). If successful, it deals no Wounds, but the target is Charmed into a paranoid frenzy. On their next turn, the target must use their first Action to make a basic Melee or Ranged attack against their nearest ally. A Willpower(13) test is allowed to resist the spell effects.\n\nChlorine Exhalation (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The dragon exhales a dense, rolling cloud of toxic green mist. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against all targets in a 40-foot cone. On a hit, targets take 3d10 + 30 Poison/Acid Wounds and instantly gain the Blinded and Poisoned conditions as the gas melts their eyes and floods their bloodstream.\n\nSerpentine Drag (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The dragon slithers out of the canopy to snatch a victim. It moves up to 20 feet, bypassing all terrain, and makes a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 40 Wounds, and the target is Grappled and dragged directly into a nearby environmental hazard (like a briar patch or deep bog water)."
