      "Random",
      "Rending Talons & Beak",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nDeath from Above: The Griffon uses gravity as a weapon. If the Griffon spends its movement flying at least 30 feet straight down toward a target before making a Melee attack, that attack automatically gains Advantage and ignores the target's first 3 points of Armor Mitigation due to the sheer kinetic force of the dive.\n\nSun-Blind Ascent: The Griffon instinctively positions itself with the sun behind it. Any enemy attempting to target the Griffon with a Ranged or Casting attack while it is flying above them suffers Disadvantage due to the blinding glare.\n\nUnbroken Pride: The Griffon refuses to be cowed by lesser creatures. It is completely immune to the Frightened and Taunted conditions from any creature that is not Giant or Titanic in size.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSwooping Pounce (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Griffon crashes into its prey, claws first. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 21 Slashing Wounds. If the target is Medium or smaller, they are instantly Grappled and knocked Prone beneath the beast's paws.\n\nExecutioner’s Beak (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Griffon snaps its razor-sharp beak down on a helpless target. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If this attack targets an enemy that is Grappled by the Griffon, it automatically hits (no roll required) and deals 1d10 + 21 Piercing Wounds as it tears through armor and flesh.\n\nGale Buffet (Cost: 2 Actions): The Griffon aggressively beats its massive wings, creating a localized hurricane. All enemies in a 20-foot cone must pass a severe Agility(7) test. On a failure, they take 15 Bludgeoning Wounds, are violently pushed 15 feet backward, and are knocked Prone."
