      "Grizzly Bear: The Forest Monarch",
      "Large",
      "Beast",
      "",
      "A mountain of fur, muscle, and territorial rage. Standing nearly ten feet tall when reared on its hind legs, the Grizzly Bear is the ultimate terrestrial predator. They are not mindless killers, but they are possessive of their domain and settle every dispute with overwhelming violence. A Grizzly doesn't just bite; it crushes. Their claws are like iron spikes, and their hide is thick enough to turn away all but the most determined strikes. To encounter \"Old Mossback\" in the wild is to realize that humans are very low on the local food chain.",
