      "Claws & Jaws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nTerritorial Berserker: The Grizzly grows more dangerous as it bleeds. For every 20 Wounds the Bear has lost, it gains a cumulative +1 to its Melee Wounds (damage), representing its desperate, adrenaline-fueled rage.\n\nThick-Skulled Resilience: The Bear’s physiology is built for brawling. It is completely immune to the Stunned and Dazed conditions. Furthermore, any Critical Hit against the Bear is treated as a normal hit unless the attacker uses a Piercing weapon.\n\nCrushing Weight: The Grizzly is a master of the \"Bear Hug.\" The Bear automatically gains Advantage on any check to maintain or escape a Grapple.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nMaul (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Bear swipes with claws like iron harrows. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 22 Slashing Wounds. If the Bear has Advantage on this roll, the target also gains 1 Bleeding condition.\n\nBone-Crusher Bite (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Bear sinks its teeth into a limb and shakes. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 40 Piercing/Bludgeoning Wounds. If the target is Medium or smaller, they are instantly Grappled and Restrained in the Bear’s jaws.\n\nIntimidating Roar (Cost: 1 Action): The Bear rears onto its hind legs and unleashes a deafening, chest-shaking roar. All enemies within 30 feet must pass a Willpower(7) test. On a failure, they gain the Frightened condition and must use their next Action to move away from the Bear."
