      "Iron-Banded Greatclub, Scavenged Scrap-Plate, Signature Iron Gut-Plate",
      "Iron-Banded Greatclub",
      "Rock Thrower",
      "Passive Traits\nUnyielding Mass: Because of its Large size and immense density, the Half-Ogre cannot be physically pushed, Grappled, or knocked Prone by Melee attacks from Medium or smaller creatures.\n\nPit-Hardened: The Bruiser is used to taking a beating. It possesses a natural resistance to blunt trauma, taking half damage from all non-magical Bludgeoning weapons.\n\nReach of the Brute: The Half-Ogre's elongated arms and massive weapon grant it a natural 10-foot reach in melee combat, allowing it to strike over the heads of standard human infantry.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSkull-Cracker Swing (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A straightforward, brutal overhead slam. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 18 Bludgeoning Wounds. If this attack rolls a Critical Hit(10), the target's helmet (or shield) is shattered, and they gain the Dazed condition.\n\nGut-Check Shove (Cost: 1 Action): The Half-Ogre lowers its shoulder and drives its iron gut-plate directly into an enemy. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 12 Bludgeoning Wounds, and the target is violently pushed 15 feet backward.\n\nThe Ragdoll Toss (Cost: 2 Actions): The brute reaches out to grab a compromised target. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit) against a Medium or smaller creature. On a hit, the target takes 10 Bludgeoning Wounds as they are hoisted into the air, and the Half-Ogre throws them up to 20 feet in any direction. The target takes standard fall 2d10 damage upon landing and gains the Prone condition."
