      "Filth-crusted talons, jagged bone daggers.",
      "Filthy Talons.",
      "Sonic Shriek",
      "Passive Traits\nHollow Bones: The Harpy is incredibly light, allowing for flight, but highly vulnerable to crushing blows. Any Bludgeoning damage dealt to the Harpy automatically gains a positive modifier to the final damage total.\n\nHit and Run: If the Harpy moves at least 20 feet in the air before making a melee attack, it does not trigger any defensive counter-attacks or reactions from the target when it flies away.\n\nGravity's Ally: The Harpy gains Advantage on checks made to grapple, push, or drag a target if they are currently adjacent to a cliff, pit, or deadly drop.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSiren's Lullaby (Cost: 2 Actions): The Harpy sings its tragic melody, utilizing its massive Charisma. All enemies within 60 feet must pass a Willpower(6) test against the Harpy's Casting To-Hit (+3). On a failure, they are Charmed and must use their movement on their next turn to walk toward the Harpy, even if it leads them into danger.\n\nSwooping Talons (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Harpy dives and slashes. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 6 Slashing Wounds and inflicts a Bleeding condition as the filthy claws rake the flesh.\n\nSnatch and Drop (Melee Cost: 1 Action): If the Harpy has a target Grappled, it attempts to lift them into the air (contested Physique vs. Agility(6) check). If successful, it ascends and immediately releases the target, inflicting falling damage based on the height."
