      "4-10",
      "Havenspire Tabard, Chain Shirt, Wooden Shield, City Spear, Brass Signal Whistle",
      "City Spear",
      "light crossbow",
      "Passive Traits\nThe City's Eyes: The Watchman's Awareness peak makes them difficult to ambush. They automatically gain Advantage on any check made to spot hidden enemies or detect traps in an urban environment.\n\nBasic Shield Wall: While standing adjacent to at least one other allied City Watchman, both guards gain a +1 modifier to their Defense.\n\nUrban Tracker: The Watchman knows the capital's streets intimately. They ignore all movement penalties caused by difficult urban terrain, such as thick crowds, narrow alleys, or market stalls.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSpear Thrust (Cost: 1 Action): A basic, textbook thrust with their polearm. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 8 Piercing Wounds.\n\nSubdue / Pommel Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Guard attempts to arrest rather than kill. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals only 3 Bludgeoning Wounds, but the target must pass a Physical(4) test or gain the Dazed condition.\n\nSound the Alarm! (Cost: 1 Action): The Watchman blows their brass signal whistle. The piercing sound echoes for blocks. All allies within earshot immediately gain a positive modifier to their Initiative/Awareness. If the encounter lasts for more than 3 rounds after the whistle is blown, 1+1d4 additional Watchmen will arrive as reinforcements."
