      "2-5",
      "Havenspire Full Plate, Tower Shield, Capital Longsword, Heavy Crossbow",
      "Capital Longsword",
      "Short Bow or Crossbow",
      "Passive Traits\nSworn Protector: The Elite Guard is trained to be an unyielding barrier. If an adjacent ally (or VIP) is targeted by a physical attack, the Guard can automatically redirect the attack to themselves, forcing the attacker to roll against the Guard's massive Defense (9) instead.\n\nCapital Forged: The metallurgy of Havenspire is legendary. The Guard's armor and weapons are immune to being shattered, sundered, or degraded by standard, non-magical abilities or corrosive slimes.\n\nPhalanx Wall: While standing adjacent to another Elite Guard, both guards gain immunity to being flanked and cannot be physically pushed or knocked Prone by creatures Size Large or smaller.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSentinel's Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A clean, textbook swing with the longsword. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 14 Slashing Wounds.\n\nShield Bash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Guard steps forward and slams their heavy tower shield into the target. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 10 Bludgeoning Wounds and the target must pass a Physical(6) test or be knocked Prone.\n\nHold the Gate (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Guard digs their heels in and raises their shield into a perfect defensive posture(+1). Until the start of their next turn, any enemy that makes a Melee attack against the Guard and misses immediately triggers a free, automatic counter-attack from the Guard's longsword."
