    "values": [
      "Hill Giant: The Ravenous Mountain",
      "Giant",
      "Giant / Humanoid",
      "",
      "Standing around 16 feet tall, the Hill Giant is a lumbering, gluttonous force of nature. What they lack in the refined elemental majesty of their kin, they make up for in sheer, brutish mass. Draped in \"Trophy-Garbs\"—crude patchwork clothing made from wagon canvases, farmhouse thatch, and animal hides—they are driven by an endless, ravenous hunger. Smelling of sweat, dirt, and raw meat, they bring the terrifying, unpredictable violence of a starving predator to the battlefield. Their primary weapon is a \"Great-Thumper\": a whole uprooted tree or a massive boulder lashed to a log, swung with a primal, earth-shaking momentum that can turn a fortified village into a crater in minutes.",
