      "1-2",
      "Trophy-Garbs, Great-Thumper (Uprooted Tree)",
      "Great-Thumper",
      "Hurling unshaped rocks or dead livestock",
      "Passive Traits\nGluttonous Rage: The Hill Giant fights with the desperate violence of a starving animal. If the Giant's Health drops below 50%, it instantly enters a rage. While enraged, it gains Advantage on all Melee To-Hit rolls, but all attacks made against the Giant also gain Advantage as it completely Abandons its defense to secure a meal.\n\nStarving Momentum: If the Hill Giant is moving toward an enemy that has the Bleeding condition, or an enemy that is visibly carrying rations or livestock, the Giant completely ignores all Difficult Terrain penalties and gains +30Ft to its Movement speed for that turn.\n\nUnstoppable Mass: Due to its immense 16-foot height and weight, the Giant is completely immune to being knocked Prone, Grappled, or physically displaced by creatures of Medium size or smaller.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nGreat-Thumper Sweep (Melee Cost: 3 Action): The Giant swings its massive uprooted tree like a baseball bat. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) with a 15-foot reach against up to two adjacent targets. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 80 Bludgeoning Wounds, and targets must pass a Physique(10) test or be hurled 15 feet backward.\n\nCrater Smash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): An overhead, earth-shattering strike against a single target. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 40 Bludgeoning Wounds. If the Giant rolls a Critical Hit, the target is Stunned until the end of their next turn from the sheer kinetic impact.\n\nCrude Bombardment (Range Cost: 1 Action): The Giant rips a chunk of earth, a boulder, or a piece of a ruined building from the ground and hurls it. Make a Ranged attack (+3 To-Hit) against a target up to 60 feet away. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 30 Bludgeoning Wounds.\n\nMid-Battle Snack (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Giant attempts to grab a weakened target and stuff them into its mouth. Target one Prone or Grappled enemy within 10 feet. The Giant makes a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If it hits, it deals 80 Piercing Wounds from its massive, crooked teeth, and the Giant instantly heals 40 Wounds as it consumes the flesh."
    ],
