      "Hippogryph: The Crag-Steed",
      "Large",
      "Monstrosity (Avian/Equine)",
      "",
      "The Hippogryph commands the skies with the unblinking, predatory gaze of a giant raptor and the muscular, tearing power of a warhorse's hindquarters. Feared by travelers and knights alike, it is a master of the skies that plummets from the clouds like a feathered anvil. It tears through armor as easily as aged parchment and possesses a wild, unbroken spirit that refuses to be tamed by anything short of legendary magic. A Hippogryph features the head, wings, and foreclaws of a giant hawk, seamlessly transitioning into the powerful hindquarters and tail of a horse. In the wild, they are known for their \"Storm-Gallop\"—a behavior where herds race along the edge of mountain thunderstorms to catch the updrafts. Their feathers favor earthy tones like chestnut, steel-grey, or dapple-white, allowing them to blend into the rocky high-altitude terrain they call home.",
