      "3-8",
      "Random",
      "Raking Foreclaws & Beak",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nFeathered Anvil: The Hippogryph turns gravity into a weapon. If the Hippogryph dives or moves at least 30 feet downward toward a target before making a melee attack, that attack automatically gains the Armor-Piercing(+3WM) quality, tearing through steel like parchment.\n\nUnbroken Spirit: The creature's mind is wildly independent. It is completely immune to the Charmed or Frightened conditions unless the source is of a Legendary or Master-level magical tier.\n\nStorm-Gallop: The Hippogryph treats severe weather (high winds, heavy rain, snow) as an advantage rather than a hindrance, completely ignoring any movement penalties associated with difficult atmospheric terrain.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nPlummeting Strike (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Hippogryph folds its wings and drops from the sky. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 40 Piercing Wounds. If this attack benefits from Feathered Anvil, the target must also pass a Physical(6) test or be knocked Prone from the sheer kinetic impact.\n\nRaptor's Rake (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The creature lashes out with its front talons. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 +27 Slashing Wounds.\n\nEquine Kick (Melee Cost: 1 Action): If a target is behind or flanking the Hippogryph, it can unleash a brutal kick with its powerful hindquarters. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 27 Bludgeoning Wounds and physically pushes the target 10 feet back."
    ],
