      "5-20",
      "Well-Oiled Banded Mail, 2-Handed Serrated Halberd, Unit Standard/Banner",
      "Serrated Halberd, Short Sword",
      "Short Bow, Javelin",
      "Passive Traits\nPhalanx Discipline: The Hobgoblin gains a permanent Advantage on Defense(+1) as long as it is standing adjacent to at least one allied creature. Furthermore, it is completely immune to the Frightened condition as long as its unit remains unbroken.\n\nReach Mastery: The Halberd allows the Hobgoblin to strike from the second rank. It can make melee attacks against targets up to 10 feet away. Attacks made at this distance do not trigger defensive reactions or counter-attacks from targets armed with standard (5-foot) weapons.\n\nArmor Conditioning: Accustomed to the weight and joints of their kit, critical Hits scored against the Hobgoblin do not bypass its WM-Arm (Armor Mitigation) unless the attacker is specifically using an Armor-Piercing weapon.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSerrated Sweep (Cost: 2 Actions): A wide, knee-level swing with the halberd. The Hobgoblin may target up to two adjacent enemies within its 10-foot reach. Make a separate Melee attack (+3 To-Hit) for each. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 14 Slashing Wounds and inflicts 1 Bleeding condition.\n\nHold the Line! (Cost: 1 Action): The Leader barks a brutal, guttural command. All allies within 30 feet immediately gain a positive modifier to their WM-Arm(+2) until the start of the Leader's next turn.\n\nPunishing Thrust (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A brutal forward thrust with the halberd's top spike. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit) with a 10-foot reach. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 14 Piercing Wounds. If the target moved toward the Hobgoblin on their last turn (charging), this attack deals double damage(+28) by using the enemy's momentum against them."
