      "Human Cultist: The Fractured Soul",
      "Medium",
      "Humanoid (Chaos-Touched)",
      "",
      "A Cultist rarely looks like a monster at first glance. They wear heavy, layered robes of deep crimson or soot-black to hide the \"Chaos-Marks\" blooming across their skin—veins that pulse with violet light or patches of scales that feel like cold iron. Their eyes are often bloodshot and wide, dilated by a constant state of religious euphoria or shivering terror. They are tactical fanatics. Unlike disciplined soldiers, a Cultist fights with a terrifying disregard for their own safety. They view their bodies as mere vessels to be used and discarded. In battle, they carry jagged, ritual daggers and \"Censer-Flails\" that leak hallucinogenic smoke, preferring to die in a burst of chaotic energy rather than face the silence of a world without their dark patrons.",
