      "3-30",
      "Heavy Robes, Jagged Ritual Dagger, Censer-Flail.",
      "Censer-Flail / Jagged Dagger",
      "Throwing Daggers",
      "Passive Traits\nReckless Abandon: The Cultist completely ignores self-preservation. When attacking this way, they automatically gain Advantage on their Melee To-Hit rolls, but any attack directed at the Cultist also gains Advantage, reflecting their refusal to defend themselves.\n\nVessel of Chaos: The Cultist's body is barely containing the dark magic within. When the Cultist is reduced to 0 Wounds, their Chaos-Marks violently rupture. All creatures within 10 feet must pass an Agility(5) test or take 10 points of unmitigable magical damage from the bursting violet energy.\n\nFanatical Mind: Driven by pure religious ecstasy, the Cultist is entirely immune to the Frightened, Charmed, and Dazed conditions.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nCenser-Flail Sweep (Cost: 1 Action): The Cultist swings their heavy, smoking flail. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 12 Bludgeoning Wounds.\n\nHallucinogenic Cloud (Cost: 2 Actions): The Cultist violently spins their Censer-Flail, filling a 15-foot radius with thick, noxious smoke. All non-cultists in the area must pass a Willpower(6) test. On a failure, they suffer the Confused condition, struggling to distinguish friend from foe through the mind-altering haze.\n\nBlood Sacrifice (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Cultist drags their jagged dagger across their own arm or chest. The Cultist immediately takes 5 Wounds of unmitigable damage, but their next Melee or Casting attack automatically results in a Critical Hit if it connects, fueled by the blood magic."
    ],
