      "Snapping Jaws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nRegenerative Mutagens: At the start of the Hydra's turn, it automatically heals 15 Wounds. If the Hydra takes Fire or Acid damage, this regeneration is paused until the end of its next turn.\n\nCut One, Two Shall Rise: When the Hydra suffers a Critical Hit from a Slashing weapon, one of its heads is severed. The stump immediately cauterizes and sprouts two new heads. For every head severed, the Hydra gains +1 Action to its maximum Act stat.\n\nSwamp Stench: The creature radiates a thick musk of rot and stagnant water. Any enemy that starts its turn within 15 feet must pass a Willpower(7) test or suffer the Nauseated condition, applying a negative modifier to their physical and combat rolls.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nCobra Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): One of the heads darts forward with blinding speed. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 20 Piercing Wounds. (With 9 Actions, the Hydra can distribute these strikes across the entire party).\n\nRend and Tear (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): Two heads coordinate to rip a single target apart. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 24 Slashing Wounds, and the target gains 1 Bleeding condition.\n\nDevour (Cost: 3 Actions): A head attempts to swallow a Medium or smaller target whole. Make a contested Physical vs. Agility check. If the Hydra wins, the target is swallowed, taking 10 points of unmitigable Acid damage each round until they deal 20 Wounds to the gullet from the inside, forcing the head to regurgitate them."
    ],
