      "None. Relies on its environment and physical form",
      "rue-Ice Claws",
      "Hurled Ice Boulders",
      "Passive Traits\nGlacial Regeneration: At the start of the Troll's turn, it heals 10 Wounds by pulling ambient moisture into its injuries. Every time this happens, the newly formed ice grants the Troll a permanent, cumulative +2 to its WM-Arm (Armor Mitigation) for the rest of the encounter. If the Troll takes Fire damage, this regeneration (and the armor boost) is paused until the end of its next turn.\n\nFlash-Freeze Blood: When the Troll suffers a Critical Hit from a Melee weapon, its sub-zero slush blood erupts. The attacker must pass an Agility(7) test or have their weapon temporarily frozen to the Troll's body, requiring an Action and a Physical(9) test to wrench it free.\n\nJagged Carapace: Any creature that successfully Grapples the Troll, or hits it with an Unarmed strike, immediately takes 10 Piercing/Cold Wounds from the true-ice shards protruding from its bones.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nShattering Swipe (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A brutal backhand with an ice-crusted fist. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 25 Slashing/Cold Wounds.\n\nImpale and Freeze (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Troll attempts to grab a target and crush them against its jagged chest. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 40 Piercing Wounds, and the target is Grappled. While Grappled, the target takes 10 unmitigable Cold Wounds at the start of their turn.\n\nSub-Zero Bellow (Cost: 1 Action): The Troll unleashes a roaring blast of freezing air and icy spittle. All enemies within a 15-foot cone must pass a Physical(9) test. On a failure, they suffer the Slowed condition, halving their movement speed and Agility on their next turn due to the biting cold."
