    "values": [
      "Iron Golem: The Vault-Warden",
      "Large",
      "Construct / Elemental",
      "",
      "A masterwork of both metallurgy and high-level sorcery. Unlike shifting clay or stitched flesh, the Iron Golem is a singular, rigid object given life by a bound elemental spirit. It is often used to guard the inner sanctums of archmages or the treasure vaults of lost civilizations. Standing ten feet tall and weighing several tons, the golem is a hulking humanoid shape of polished, dark-iron plates. Its joints hiss with steam and arcane pressure as it moves, and its featureless iron face is set in a permanent, stoic mask. It carries no weapons, for its fists are heavy enough to crush a horse, and it exudes a constant, metallic tang of ozone and heated metal.",
