      "1-2",
      "None",
      "Iron Fists",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nFurnace Absorption: The elemental spirit bound within the golem thrives on extreme heat. The Iron Golem is completely immune to Fire damage. Whenever it is subjected to a Fire attack, it absorbs the energy, healing 15 Wounds and instantly curing itself of any Slowed or Exhausted conditions.\n\nUnstoppable Mass: Weighing several tons, the Iron Golem cannot be moved against its will. It is completely immune to the Knockback, Prone, Grappled, and Restrained conditions from any creature smaller than Giant size.\n\nArcane Iron Carapace: Normal weapons simply bounce off its chassis. All non-magical Melee attacks that deal Slashing or Piercing damage have their Wounds reduced to 0 before Armor Mitigation is even calculated.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nHorse-Crushing Slam (Cost: 1 Action): The Golem steps forward and delivers a piston-driven punch. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 28 Bludgeoning Wounds. If the target is wearing heavy armor, the sheer force of the blow dents the metal, reducing the target's Wound Mitigation by 3 for the rest of the encounter.\n\nToxic Arcane Vent (Cost: 2 Actions): The Golem releases the built-up ozone and arcane pressure from its internal furnace. It exhales a 15-foot cone of blinding, poisonous gas. All enemies in the cone must pass a severe Physique(8) test or take 25 Poison/Fire Wounds and become Poisoned for 1 round.\n\nJuggernaut Stride (Cost: 1 Action): The Golem simply walks through its enemies. It moves up to its full 20 Movement speed in a straight line, freely entering the spaces of smaller creatures. Any creature whose space it enters must pass an Agility(7) test or take 15 Bludgeoning Wounds and be pushed 5 feet out of the Golem's path."
