      "1",
      "",
      "Crude Chain-Linked Flail",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nRune-Forged Carapace: The cursed iron plates bolted into the creature's flesh by the smiths of Birn Uluhm offer near-impenetrable defense. The Iron-Minotaur possesses an innate 15 points of WM-Arm (Armor Mitigation). However, attackers can choose to target the exposed joints by taking a -3 penalty to their To-Hit roll; a successful hit in this manner ignores all WM-Arm.\n\nFurnace Blood: The creature is kept alive by a literal furnace of dark magic burning within its chest. It is completely immune to Fire and Heat-based damage. Furthermore, any enemy that starts its turn adjacent to the Iron-Minotaur takes 5 Fire Wounds from the radiating heat and scalding steam.\n\nUnstoppable Momentum: Pain is a distant memory, replaced entirely by the agonizing drive of its dark machinery. The Iron-Minotaur is immune to the Staggered, Stunned, and Frightened conditions. Attempts to Grapple or knock the creature Prone are automatically resisted unless the attacker passes a Physique test against the Iron-Minotaur's 9 Physique.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nQuake Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): Raising its massive, jagged iron weapon, the beast brings its full unnatural weight crashing down onto the ground. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 30 Bludgeoning Wounds. Additionally, the ground shatters in a 10-foot radius around the target, turning the area into difficult terrain.\n\nVent Slag (Cost: 1 Action): The Iron-Minotaur violently purges toxic buildup from its internal furnace. It targets a 15-foot cone in front of it. All targets within the cone must pass a Physique(9) test against the beast's 9 Physique. On a failure, they take 1d10 + 12 Fire Wounds and gain the Blinded and Choking conditions (suffering a -2 to all tests) for one turn. On a success, they take half Wounds and avoid the conditions.\n\nEngine-Buster Charge (Cost: 2 Actions): The beast lowers its horns and barrels forward in a straight line up to 40 feet. It makes a single Melee attack (+4 To-Hit) against the first target in its path. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 30 Piercing/Bludgeoning Wounds, and the target is violently pushed back 10 feet and gains the Prone condition. If the charge hits a solid structure, the structure takes double Wounds."
