    "values": [
      "Jabberslythe: The Unmaking Gaze",
      "Giant",
      "Aberration / Monstrosity",
      "",
      "A Jabberslythe is a massive, bloated creature with skin that looks like wet, warty leather. It possesses a pair of tattered, moth-like wings that shouldn't be able to lift its bulk, yet it moves with a sickening, twitchy grace. Its face is a nightmare of cluster-eyes and a long, prehensile tongue that drips with paralytic slime. What makes the Jabberslythe truly unique is its \"Aura of Insanity.\" To look upon the creature is to feel one’s mind fracture. It doesn't roar; it emits a constant, wet burbling and a series of high-pitched clicks that sound like a thousand insects dying at once. Animals flee in terror, and even the bravest knights often find themselves weeping or laughing hysterically instead of drawing their swords when the beast nears.",
