      "Prehensile Slime-Tongue & Crushing Bulk",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nAura of Insanity: The Jabberslythe’s primary weapon is its presence. Any enemy that starts its turn within 40 feet of the beast must pass a Willpower test against a punishing difficulty based on the beast's 15 Charisma. On a failure, the target suffers the Madness condition: they must roll a d10. (1-5: They fall Prone, weeping uncontrollably and losing their turn; 6-10: They laugh hysterically and must make a melee attack against the nearest creature, friend or foe).\n\nSickening Grace: Because the creature moves in unpredictable, jittery bursts, it gains a permanent Advantage on Defense(+2) against Ranged attacks.\n\nToxic Biology: The creature's blood and saliva are highly corrosive. Any creature that successfully damages the Jabberslythe with an Unarmed strike or a Grapple automatically takes 5 Wounds of Acid/Poison damage.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nParalytic Tongue Lash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The beast whips out its long, dripping tongue. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit) with a 15-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 18 Bludgeoning Wounds. The target must also pass a Physical(9) test or gain the Paralyzed condition until the end of their next turn due to the slime.\n\nThe Unmaking Gaze (Cost: 2 Actions): The beast focuses its cluster-eyes on a single target whose mind is already fracturing. Target one enemy suffering from the Madness condition. Make a Charisma vs. Willpower check. On a success, the target takes 30 unmitigable Psychic Wounds as their mind begins to physically hemorrhage.\n\nTwitchy Trample (Cost: 1 Action): The Jabberslythe surges forward with its bloated bulk. The creature moves up to its full Ground speed. Any creature Size Medium or smaller in its path must pass an Agility(8) test or be knocked Prone and take 20 Bludgeoning Wounds."
    ],
