    "values": [
      "Knight of the Ruined Order (Dread Knight)",
      "Medium",
      "Undead (Hero)",
      "",
      "Dread Knights were once heroic crusaders who fell to corruption, their souls bound to their armor by dark necromancy long after their bodies turned to dust. They do not feel pain, fatigue, or pity. They are a vanguard of terror, projecting an aura of unnatural cold and soul-crushing dread. A Dread Knight rarely rushes into combat; it walks with slow, inevitable purpose, letting the sheer psychological weight of its presence break the minds of its enemies before its blade ever swings. It is a towering, imposing figure entirely encased in blackened, heavily pitted plate armor. There is no flesh visible beneath the visor—only a swirling vortex of freezing, spectral-blue mist and two piercing points of hateful light. Its armor is draped in the tattered, frost-rimed remnants of a once-noble tabard. In its gauntlets, it wields a massive, two-handed executioner's sword that trails a freezing black vapor.",
