      "6",
      "1",
      "Pitted Black Plate, Tattered Frost-Rimed Tabard, Executioner's Sword",
      "Frost-Rimed Executioner's Sword",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nHollow Armor: The Knight has no physical body beneath its armor, only a swirling vortex of spectral-blue mist. It is completely immune to the Bleeding and Poisoned conditions. Furthermore, critical hits from Piercing weapons deal only normal damage, as the weapon simply passes through the mist inside the plate.\n\nAura of the Grave: The ground freezes around its sabatons, and the air grows thick with the chill of the grave. Any living creature that starts its turn within 20 feet of the Knight must pass a Willpower test against the Knight's staggering Charisma. On a failure, they gain the Frightened condition and their Movement speed is halved by the unnatural cold.\n\nInevitable Advance: The Dread Knight cannot be rushed or staggered. It is completely immune to being knocked Prone, physically pushed, or having its Movement speed reduced by any effect other than its own slow gait.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nExecutioner's Toll (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): A devastating, textbook swing of the massive sword. Make a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 +35 Slashing/Cold Wounds. If this attack reduces a target to 0 Wounds, the Knight immediately regains 1 Action as the target's life force is snuffed out.\n\nVaporous Cleave (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Knight drags its blade along the frozen ground before unleashing a wide, upward sweeping arc. Make a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit) against up to three adjacent enemies. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 35 Slashing Wounds and inflicts the Slowed condition as the freezing black vapor clings to their armor.\n\nGaze of the Ruined (Cost: 1 Action): The Knight stops and focuses the two piercing points of hateful light directly on a target's eyes. Make a Charisma vs. Willpower check. On a success, the target's mind momentarily breaks; they drop whatever they are holding and lose their next Action, overwhelmed by despair."
    ],
