      "Colossal Tentacles",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nSiege Monster: The Kraken's attacks bypass all standard Armor Mitigation when striking ships, buildings, or fortifications. It deals double damage to any inanimate structure. Due to its Titanic mass, it is entirely immune to being Grappled, pushed, or knocked Prone by anything smaller than another Titan.\n\nImpossible Reach: The Kraken's massive tentacles allow it to make melee attacks against any target up to 100 feet away from its central body.\n\nLord of the Depths: The Kraken is immune to Cold damage and the effects of crushing deep-water pressure. It breathes water natively and treats underwater combat as normal terrain, while most mortals suffer severe penalties.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSweeping Tentacle (Cost: 3 Actions): A massive tentacle sweeps across the deck of a ship. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 2d10 + 60 Bludgeoning Wounds. (With 12 Actions, the Kraken can unleash a horrifying barrage of these strikes across the entire party).\n\nCrush and Drag (Cost: 2 Actions): A tentacle attempts to wrap around a target. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 40 Bludgeoning Wounds and the target is automatically Grappled. The Kraken immediately pulls the target 50 feet closer to its gaping beak.\n\nGalleon-Crusher Beak (Melee Cost: 3 Actions): The Kraken bites down on a target currently Grappled by a tentacle. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals a staggering 3d10 + 80 Piercing Wounds, instantly shattering armor and bone."
