      "Crude Stone Maul, Massive Shackles/Chains.",
      "Crude Stone Maul",
      "Hurl debris and rock",
      "Passive Traits\nSiege Juggernaut: The Krox is a living siege engine. Its melee attacks bypass standard Armor Mitigation when striking inanimate structures, gates, or fortifications, dealing double damage. It is completely immune to being physically pushed, Grappled, or knocked Prone by creatures of Large size or smaller.\n\nMindless Bloodlust: Without a Skink handler within 30 feet to direct it, the Krox automatically gains the Frenzied condition. It becomes immune to Fear and Charm, but must use its actions to attack the nearest creature (friend or foe) to the best of its ability.\n\nAquatic Behemoth: The Krox treats water and deep mud as normal terrain, completely ignoring movement penalties in swamp environments.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nShattering Sweep (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Krox swings its massive stone maul in a wide, horizontal arc. All creatures within a 20-foot cone must pass an Agility(d10+to-hit) test. On a failure, they take 1d10 + 40 Bludgeoning Wounds and are violently knocked Prone.\n\nThrashing Tail (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The creature violently spins, slamming its heavy tail into a target behind or beside it. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 25 Bludgeoning Wounds and physically pushes the target 15 feet away.\n\nJaws of the Behemoth (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Krox drops its weapon or attacks with its free hand, lunging forward to snap its massive crocodilian jaws. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 35 Piercing Wounds, and the target is automatically Grappled."
