    "values": [
      "Ledger-Devil: The Soul-Contractor",
      "Giant",
      "Fiend / Devil",
      "",
      "A Ledger-Devil is a tall, unnervingly thin Giant dressed in robes made of layered, yellowed parchment—each sheet a contract signed in blood. They have long, multi-jointed fingers perpetually stained with ink, and carry a massive, iron-bound book known as the \"Tome of Arrears.\" Their eyes are replaced by two magnifying lenses fused to their skull, allowing them to see the \"debt-weight\" of any soul. They find physical combat vile and inefficient. Instead, they fight by imposing metaphysical rules, using verbal traps and \"The Fine Print\" to paralyze heroes and turn the party's own abilities into liabilities. To them, your life is a loan, and they have come to collect.",
