      "he Tome of Arrears, Robes of the Damned",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Verbal Traps & Fines",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Fine Print (Aura of Liability): The Ledger-Devil dictates the rules of engagement. Any time a player within 60 feet attempts to cast a spell, use a magical item, or trigger a special combat ability, they must first pass a Willpower(9) test or pay a \"tax.\" If they fail, they instantly take 1d10 Psychic Wounds before the ability activates, as the Devil cites a breach of universal contract.\n\nVile Inefficiency: The Devil despises physical altercations. Any non-magical Melee attack made against the Ledger-Devil has its Wounds halved automatically, as the kinetic energy is absorbed by the dense, blood-signed parchment of his robes.\n\nDebt-Weight Vision: The magnifying lenses fused to his skull see the exact sins and weaknesses of the party. The Ledger-Devil completely ignores any defensive buffs (like magical shields, evasive stances, or cover) when making a Casting attack.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nCease and Desist(TN6) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Devil speaks a binding legal injunction. Make a Casting attack (+6 To-Hit) against a target within 50 feet. If successful, it deals no Wounds, but the target is Silenced and Stunned for 1 round—metaphysically paralyzed by the weight of infernal bureaucracy. A Willpower(15) test is allowed to resist the effects.\n\nForeclosure of the Soul(TN13) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Devil reads an extraction clause from the Tome of Arrears. Make a Casting attack (+6 To-Hit) against a target. On a hit, it deals 2d10 + 40 Necrotic Wounds. If this attack reduces a player to 0 Wounds, their soul is instantly bound to a page in the Tome, preventing any form of resurrection until the book is destroyed.\n\nRedistribution of Assets(TN7) (Cost: 1 Action): The Devil exploits a loophole in the party's healing magic. He targets one player who has received healing or a buff this combat. That player must pass a severe Willpower(12) test; on a failure, the healing/buff is instantly stripped from them and granted to the Ledger-Devil or one of his summoned minions instead."
