      "agged Limbs & Mismatched Mouths",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nPsychic Static (Aura): Their constant gibbering and the way they warp light makes it incredibly difficult for mortals to aim. Any Ranged attack or Casting roll made by a player within 15 feet of a Warp-Skitterer automatically suffers Disadvantage.\n\nThe Muttering Swarm: They feed off the chaotic energy of their kin. If a Warp-Skitterer makes a Melee attack against a target that is currently engaged with at least one other Daemon, the Skitterer gains Advantage on the attack roll and deals an additional +10 Wounds on a hit.\n\nHysterical Aggression: They will gladly impale themselves just to get close enough to bite. If a player successfully hits the Daemon with a Melee weapon, the Daemon may use its Reaction to violently pull itself further down the weapon's shaft. The Daemon takes the Wounds, but instantly makes a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit) against the attacker in return.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nGlitch-Step (Cost: 1 Action): The Daemon does not walk; it stutters through reality. It instantly Disengages from melee combat without triggering free attacks of opportunity and teleports up to 20 feet to an unoccupied space it can see.\n\nFrantic Rend (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A hysterical flurry of claws and teeth. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Wounds and the target gains 1 Bleeding condition as the jagged limbs tear flesh.\n\nSensory Overload(TN10) (Cost: 2 Actions): The assorted mouths on the Daemon's body all scream in unison, broadcasting raw void-static. Make a Casting attack (+3 To-Hit) against all enemies within 10 feet. On a hit, targets take 1d10 + 10 Psychic Wounds and must pass a Willpower(6) test or drop any weapons they are currently holding as their hands instinctively fly to their ears."
