      "Lesser Treant: The Grove-Warden",
      "Large",
      "Plant / Elemental",
      "",
      "Long before a Treant grows to the towering, earth-shaking heights of the ancient forest lords, they serve as Grove-Wardens. These young, ambulatory trees are roughly the size and shape of a mature oak or weeping willow. They lack the complex, slow-spoken wisdom of their elders, operating instead on a primal, instinctual drive to protect the borders of their sacred groves. When at rest, they are indistinguishable from standard flora. But when an intruder brings an axe or a torch into their domain, the roots tear free from the earth, and the heavy branches swing with the crushing force of a falling timber.",
