    "values": [
      "Lich: The Eternal Weaver",
      "Medium",
      "Undead (Hero / Boss)",
      "",
      "A Lich is a skeletal figure of terrifying elegance. They do not shuffle or groan; they glide with a predatory, cold grace. Their bones are often reinforced with gold filigree or etched with thousands of microscopic runes. They dress in the finery of a long-dead age—heavy silks and furs that have turned to grey cobwebs over the centuries. The air around a Lich is physically heavy, tasting of ozone and old dust. They don't just \"cast\" spells; they weave the ambient energy of the graveyard into physical reality. A single gesture from a Lich can command a hundred corpses to rise, or cause the blood in a living man's veins to turn to ice. They are patient, calculating, and utterly devoid of empathy, viewing the living as nothing more than raw materials for their eternal experiments.",
