      "Rune-etched Phylactery Jewelry, Ancient Silks, Staff of the Weaver",
      "Quarterstaff or other weapon",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nAura of the Heavy Grave: The air within 30 feet of the Lich is choked with ozone, dust, and supernatural gravity. Any living creature that starts its turn in this aura has its Movement speed halved and cannot utilize any Agility-based evasive abilities.\n\nMaster of the Lair: A Lich is a supreme summoner of the dead. A Lich automatically doubles the number of raised unhallow if residing in their lair.\n\nUndead Constitution: Being an animated corpse, the Lich is entirely immune to the Bleeding, Disease, and Poison conditions.\n\nUnholy Aura: The Lich constantly radiates an aura of dread. Any living creature that begins its turn within 30 feet of the Lich must pass a Willpower vs Willpower test or suffer a -2 penalty to their next action.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nArise, My Materials(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Lich weaves ambient energy into the soil. It instantly summons 1d4+1 Lesser Skeletons or Zombies from the surrounding earth in unoccupied spaces within 40 feet. These summons act immediately on the Lich's initiative.\n\nBone Shrapnel Detonation(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Lich points a bony finger at a fallen corpse or one of its own skeletal minions, infusing it with unstable dark magic until it violently explodes in a 15-foot area. Any creature caught in the blast suffers 1d10 + 38 piercing wounds. If they fail an Agility(9) test, the jagged bone fragments cause 1 Bleeding condition.\n\nGaze of the Endless Void(TN12) (Casting Cost: 3 Actions): The Lich channels the absolute nothingness of the grave into a single, terrifying glare. This is a heavy, concentrated spell that rips into the target's mind. The victim suffers 4d10 + 38 absolute wounds. Furthermore, the target must pass a Willpower(12) test or suffer 2 Stunned conditions as their mind is temporarily shattered by a glimpse into the abyss.\n\nOzone Singularity(TN13) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Lich condenses the heavy, static air into a collapsing void. Target a 20-foot radius anywhere within 80 feet. All creatures in the area must make a Physique test against the Lich's Casting To-Hit total. On a failure, they take 4d10 +38 Bludgeoning/Necrotic Wounds and are violently pulled 10 feet toward the center of the singularity. On a success, they take half damage and are not moved.\n\nSoul-Seer's Siphon(TN12) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): A tether of crackling, necrotic green energy connects the Lich to its victim, aggressively draining their life force. The target suffers 2d10 + 38 wounds. The Lich then absorbs the stolen vitality, healing itself for half of the total wounds dealt. The victim must pass a Physique(9) test or have their movement speed halved on their next turn due to sheer lethargy."
    ],
