  {
    "values": [
      "Lizardman",
      "Medium",
      "LIzardman",
      "",
      "Standing roughly seven feet tall and built like a brick wall of muscle and scales, the Lizardman is a terrifying apex predator of the marshlands. Classified as a Medium (Med) creature, they rely on pure, unadulterated Physique rather than magical size multipliers. Their thick, crocodilian hides deflect glancing blows, and their powerful tails and jaws make them deadly even if disarmed. They fight with a primal, rhythmic brutality that easily overwhelms lighter infantry.\n\nIn combat, they are \"patient predators.\" They can stand perfectly still for hours in a swamp, appearing as nothing more than a mossy log, before exploding into a blur of bronze-tipped spears and crushing jaws. They favor weapons made from obsidian, bone, and \"Great-Croc\" leather—materials that do not rust in the humid rot of their homes. To a Lizardman, honor is found in the efficiency of the kill; they do not waste breath on threats or boasts.",
