      "3-12",
      "Chain Armor with Shield",
      "1H Ax or Mace",
      "Throwing - Javelin/Spear",
      "Passive Traits\nCold-Blooded: The Lizardman thrives in sweltering jungles and murky swamps, ignoring all difficult terrain penalties in these environments. However, if struck by Ice magic or exposed to freezing environments, they suffer a -2 penalty to their Agility characteristic.\n\nPredator's Lungs: They can hold their breath underwater for up to an hour and suffer absolutely no penalties to their movement speed or melee To-Hit rolls while fighting fully submerged in water.\n\nThick Scaled Hide: Their natural crocodilian scales function as built-in armor, providing a permanent +3 to their Defense and significant base physical wound mitigation before any shields or skills are even applied.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSavage Bite (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Lizardman snaps its massive, tooth-filled maw shut on an enemy. This brutal 1-Handed strike deals an automatic +16 wounds. If the attack roll is an unmodified 10, the target's flesh is torn, causing 1 Bleeding condition.\n\nBrutal Tail Sweep (Melee Cost: 3 Actions): Pivoting sharply, the Lizardman uses its thick, muscular tail as a massive bludgeoning weapon. Because this acts as a 2-Handed heavy impact attack, the damage is doubled. It hits a tight arc, dealing 2d10 + 32 wounds to the target. The victim must pass an Agility test or instantly suffer the Prone condition.\n\nSwamp Hunter's Javelin (Range Cost: 1 Action): Rearing back, the Lizardman hurls a heavy, barbed spear. As a thrown weapon, it combines half of their Agility and half of their Physique for the damage calculation, resulting in a heavy +14 wounds on impact."
    ],
    "imgSrc": ""
  },
