      "Skulls of the Fallen, Massive Obsidian Macuahuitl (Serrated Club), Bone Harpoons",
      "Obsidian Macuahuitl",
      "Bone Harpoon",
      "Passive Traits\nApex Command: The sheer presence of the Chieftain bolsters its kin. Any friendly Lizardmen within 50 feet gain a +1 bonus to their +To-Hit rolls and become completely immune to Fear.\n\nCold-Blooded: The Chieftain thrives in sweltering jungles and murky swamps, ignoring all difficult terrain penalties in these environments. If struck by Ice magic or exposed to freezing environments, they suffer a -2 penalty to their Agility characteristic.\n\nPredator's Lungs: They can hold their breath underwater for up to an hour and suffer absolutely no penalties to their movement speed or melee To-Hit rolls while fighting fully submerged.\n\nSwamp Ambush: The Chieftain treats water, deep mud, and thick underbrush as normal terrain. If the Chieftain begins its turn submerged in water, its first attack that round automatically gains Advantage and deals additional Wounds.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBlood-Curdling Bellow (Tactical Cost: 1 Action): The Chieftain unleashes a primal, guttural roar. All enemy creatures within 60 feet must pass a Willpower(8) test or suffer 1 Stunned condition as terror grips them.\n\nDeath Roll (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Chieftain drops its weapon, lunges, and attempts to bite and twist a target. Make a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 25 Piercing Wounds and the target is automatically Grappled and knocked Prone. If this is performed in water, the target also begins drowning. Make a Physique vs Physique test in order to break free in your turn.\n\nTyrant's Halberd (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Chieftain swings a massive, two-handed Obsidian Macuahuitl (+5 To-Hit). Powered by its immense Physique and magnified by its Large size, this devastating sweep hits a wide arc and deals a crushing 1d10 + 60 wounds. If the attack roll is an unmodified 10, the target must pass a Physique(9) test or suffer the Prone condition.\n\nSpined Behemoth Javelin (Range Cost: 1 Action): Heaving a massive spear carved from the rib of a swamp beast, the Chieftain hurls it with terrifying velocity. This heavy thrown weapon deals 1d10 + 22 wounds on impact, pinning smaller enemies to the ground on a natural 10."
    ],
