      "Wizardry",
      "",
      "1",
      "Woven Asbestos Robes, Core-Staff (Primordial Spark)",
      "Core-Staff Strike (+2)",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Living Hearth: The Magma-Caller is the spiritual and literal fire of her people. Allied Pyreborn within 30 ft gain +2 to their WM-B/S (Wounds Mitigation - Bless/Spell) and add +2 to their Melee Wounds from the ambient, empowering heat. She is completely immune to Fire and Heat damage.\n\nSun-Blood Spatter: Her translucent skin barely contains her superheated copper-gold blood. Anytime she suffers Melee Wounds, her skin ruptures, spraying the attacker with boiling fluid. The attacker instantly takes 6 Fire Wounds and gains 1 Bleeding (Burn) condition.\n\nSmelt the Impurity: Her pyromancy burns so intensely that it melts physical defenses. Her spells automatically ignore the first 5 points of a target's WM-Blessing/Spells.\n\nActions\nPrimordial Spark(TN7) - (Casting Cost: 1): Points her Core-Staff, unleashing a concentrated beam of white-hot energy. Deals normal 1d10 + 37 Casting Wounds. On an unmodified 9 or 10 on the To-Cast roll, the target's armor fuses, permanently reducing their WM-Arm by 1 for the remainder of the battle.\n\nFissure of Toxic Slag(TN10) - (Casting/Area Cost: 2): Tears the ground open in a 30 ft line directly in front of her. Enemies caught in the path must make an Agility(8) Test or take 1d10 + 37 Casting Wounds and become trapped in the rapidly cooling slag, reducing their Movement to 0 for 1 turn. The fissure remains as a permanent line of impassable difficult terrain.\n\nVent the Core(TN11) - (Area Cost: 2): Releases a massive, hissing cloud of toxic, superheated volcanic gas in a 20 ft radius around herself. All enemies in the cloud must make a Physique(12) Test or take half her Casting Wounds 1d10 + 19 and gain the Poisoned condition, suffering 1d10 Wounds at the start of their next 2 turns from scorched lungs."
    ],
