      "Wizardry",
      "9",
      "1",
      "Crown of Cold Starlight (Cosmic Artifact)",
      "Obsidian Needle Fingers (Six Arms). Strikes deal a base of 160 wounds.",
      "Cold Starlight Shards. Can project beams of freezing void energy up to 100ft.",
      "Passive Traits\nDistance is a Lie: Malakor does not physically walk, run, or trigger attacks of opportunity when moving. Whenever he uses his Movement, he simply ceases to be in his current location and \"is\" in his new location, stepping through the shadows. He completely ignores all difficult terrain, walls, and magical barriers unless they explicitly block teleportation.\n\nFrozen Liquid Telepathy: Malakor constantly broadcasts his oppressive, alien will into the minds of his enemies. Any hostile creature starting its turn within 80 feet of Malakor must pass a Willpower test. On a failure, the sheer mental agony causes them to lose 1 Action for that turn and suffer Disadvantage on any spellcasting attempts.\n\nCrown of Cold Starlight: The shards of the dead sun upon his head cast a pale, rhythmic light that snuffs out warmth and life. Within a 120-foot radius of Malakor, all healing effects (potions, blessings, regenerative traits) are reduced by half. Furthermore, any Fire-based attacks directed at him have their total wounds halved as the cold starlight devours the heat.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nObsidian Flurry (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): Utilizing his six slender arms, Malakor unleashes a terrifying barrage of needle-like strikes. He makes three separate melee attacks that can be divided among any targets within his reach. These strikes seek the absolute weakest points in physical matter; they completely ignore all Wound Mitigation from worn armor (using only the target's natural mitigation) and inflict 1 Bleeding condition per successful hit.\n\nSnuff the Candle (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): Malakor points a single obsidian finger at a target within 100 feet, attempting to extinguish their life force like a flickering flame. The target must pass a severe Physique(15) test. On a failure, they take 5d10 + 60 cosmic wounds, and their immediate 15-foot radius is plunged into absolute, magical Blackout for 1 turn, blinding them to the outside world.\n\nMonarch's Eclipse (Cost: 4 Actions): Malakor expands his shifting body, causing the column of darkness to violently explode outward and consume the battlefield. A 100-foot radius around him is plunged into suffocating, crushing shadows for 2 turns. While the Eclipse is active, Malakor heals 3d10 + 40 wounds at the start of his turn, and all enemies caught inside the darkness suffer 2d10 wounds at the start of their turns as the shadows actively try to tear their physical forms apart."
    ],
