      "Bite, Claw, Tail, Special Abilities",
      "Special Abilities",
      "Passive Traits\nWinged Terror: The Manticore is a natural flyer. While airborne, it ignores all ground-based difficult terrain and gains a +1 bonus to its Defense against standard melee attacks from ground-bound enemies.\n\nScent of Blood: It can smell open wounds from up to a mile away. If any creature within 100 feet is suffering from a Bleeding condition, the Manticore gains advantage on all Awareness tests to track or locate them.\n\nFrightful Presence: The grotesque, human-like face and unnatural roars of the Manticore are deeply unsettling. Any living creature that begins its turn within 40 feet must pass a Willpower test or suffer a -1 penalty to their +To-Hit rolls due to fear.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTriple-Rowed Maw (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Manticore lunges forward, sinking its three rows of jagged teeth into its prey. Fueled by its high Physique and magnified by its Large size, this bite deals a devastating +24 wounds. On an unmodified 10, it tears the flesh, inflicting 2 Bleeding conditions.\n\nCaustic Tail Sting (Melee Cost: 1 Action): Whipping its scorpion tail overhead in a blindingly fast strike, it pierces armor with ease, dealing +24 wounds. The victim must pass a Physique test or instantly suffer 1 Poison condition, taking additional damage each turn.\n\nVolley of Spikes (Range Cost: 2 Actions): With a violent snap of its tail, the Manticore launches a spread of heavy, venomous chitin spikes. Treating this as a thrown weapon, it combines half its Agility and half its Physique, multiplied by its size, to deal +22 piercing wounds."
