      "1d8+2",
      "None",
      "Jagged Maw. Strikes deal a base of 60 Wounds ",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nSoul-Scent & Tremorsense: Because the Hound has no eyes, it is completely immune to all visual illusions, blinding effects, and gaze attacks. Instead, it tracks the heat of a soul and the thumping of a heartbeat. Invisibility and magical darkness are completely useless against it. The only way to hide from a Midnight-Hound is to magically stop your own heart or suppress your soul's signature.\n\nLiquid Pack-Tactics: The hounds move with synchronized, hive-mind-like precision. If a Midnight-Hound is adjacent to an ally Hound, they both gain Advantage on their To-Hit rolls. Furthermore, they can move through each other's spaces without colliding or suffering movement penalties, weaving around prey like black water.\n\nBone-Plated Skull: The top and front of the Hound's head is a solid, sloped plate of armored bone. Any physical ranged attacks (arrows, bolts) targeting the Hound from the front have a 50% chance to seamlessly glance off the armor plate, dealing exactly 0 Wounds.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nThe Bleed (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A specialized, darting bite aimed explicitly at the hamstrings and heels of fleeing prey. Make a melee attack at +2 To-Hit. Instead of dealing full damage, this attack deals half wounds (+10 Wounds), but instantly inflicts 2 Bleeding conditions. Additionally, the target's Movement speed is halved on their next turn.\n\nMarrow Hum (Cost: 2 Actions): The Hound vibrates its throat and chest cavity, emitting a low-frequency hum that bypasses hearing and directly shakes the bones of nearby prey. All enemies within a 30-foot radius must pass a Physique(9) test. On a failure, the vibrating agony causes them to suffer 1 Exhausted condition, and they lose 1 Action on their next turn as their muscles violently cramp.\n\nDrag Down (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Hound leaps, attempting to clamp its jaws onto a target's limb or throat to pin them for the rest of the pack. Make a melee attack; if successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 60 Melee Wounds and the target must immediately pass a severe Physique(8) test. If the target fails, they are violently pulled to the ground, gaining the Prone condition, and are considered Grappled by the Hound, unable to use movement actions until they break the Hound's grip."
    ],
