      "Mimic: The False-Object",
      "Medium",
      "Aberration / Shapeshifter",
      "",
      "In the Power of Three, Mimics are not just monsters; they are highly specialized subterranean shapeshifters that have evolved to prey specifically on the greed of adventurers. Composed of a dense, muscle-like matter, they perfectly mimic the texture, temperature, and appearance of wood, stone, or metal. In its resting state, a Mimic is indistinguishable from a mundane object—a treasure chest, a heavy door, or a section of floor. When it strikes, the \"wood\" splits into a jagged, tooth-lined maw and a long, adhesive tongue lashes out. Its surface is coated in a natural adhesive called \"Limb-Glue,\" making it nearly impossible to pull away once you've made contact.",
