      "None",
      "Splintering Maw.",
      "Adhesive Tongue. Shoots up to 30ft",
      "Passive Traits\nPerfect False-Object: While the Mimic remains motionless, its disguise is absolute. It is completely immune to visual detection or any Awareness tests meant to spot hidden creatures. The only way to reveal a Mimic without touching it is through magical detection of life/aberrations, or by damaging it. If a player touches the Mimic while unaware, the Mimic automatically gains a free Surprise round before Initiative is rolled.\n\nLimb-Glue Anatomy: The Mimic secretes a powerful, magical adhesive. Any creature that touches the Mimic with their bare hands (such as trying to open a chest or door) is instantly Grappled (Movement reduced to 0). Furthermore, any Melee attacks made against the Mimic with a physical weapon require the attacker to pass a Physique test after damage is resolved; on a failure, the weapon becomes stuck to the Mimic and cannot be used until the attacker spends an Action to rip it free.\n\nAmorphous Density: Because it lacks a true skeletal structure, the Mimic is immune to the Prone condition and takes half damage from falling or crushing traps.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nGreed's Punishment (Cost: 1 Action): This action can only be used as a reaction when a target physically touches the Mimic's disguised form. The Mimic instantly snaps open its jagged maw, automatically hitting the touching target for normal Wounds (30) and inflicting 1 Bleeding condition as the \"wood\" splinters into their flesh. The target remains stuck via Limb-Glue.\n\nAdhesive Tongue Lash (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Mimic spits out a long, muscular tongue coated in glue. Make a Ranged attack (+4 To-Hit) against a target within 30 feet. If successful, it deals 25 Wounds, and the target is Grappled. The Mimic can then immediately pull the target up to 15 feet directly toward its waiting maw.\n\nThe Masticator (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Mimic attempts to chew on a target currently stuck to it via Limb-Glue or its tongue. Make a Melee attack with Advantage (+8 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 2d10 + 30 Wounds. If the target is wearing armor, the Mimic's acidic saliva and grinding wooden teeth permanently reduce the target's Armor Mitigation by 2."
    ],
