      "Massive Rust-Pitted Greataxe, Iron Nose Ring",
      "Massive Greataxe / Horns",
      "Throwing Weapon",
      "Passive Traits\nClaustrophobic Hunter: The Minotaur excels in tight spaces. While fighting in indoor corridors, catacombs, or alleys no wider than 15 feet, it gains a permanent +1 to its Defense as it uses its massive bulk to completely block the passage.\n\nLabyrinthine Recall: The Minotaur possesses a supernatural sense of direction. It can perfectly recall any path it has traveled and is completely immune to magical effects that cause confusion, spatial displacement, or maze-like entrapment.\n\nUnstoppable Momentum: If the Minotaur moves at least 15 feet in a straight line before making a melee attack, it gains a +2 bonus to its +To-Hit roll and ignores the first 3 points of the target's physical armor mitigation.\n\nThick-Hided Brute: The dense muscle and matted fur covering the Minotaur grant it an exceptional resistance to pain. It is completely immune to the Bleeding condition from standard slashing weapons.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nShattering Greataxe (Melee - Cost: 2 Actions): Wielding a monstrous, rusted iron greataxe, the Minotaur delivers a horrific, sweeping blow. As a 2-Handed weapon multiplied by its Large size, this devastating strike deals a massive +54 wounds. If the target attempts to block with a shield, the shield is shattered on an unmodified 9 or 10.\n\nGore and Toss (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Minotaur lowers its head and drives its thick horns upward into a target. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 40 Piercing Wounds, and the target must pass a Physique(9) test or be violently tossed 15 feet backward and knocked Prone.\n\nGoring Charge (Melee - Cost: 1 Action): Lowering its head, the Minotaur rams its blood-stained horns into a target. This natural attack deals a brutal 1d10 +27 wounds. The sheer force of the impact requires the victim to pass a Physique(10) test or immediately suffer the Prone and Stunned conditions.\n\nDeafening Bellow (Tactical - Cost: 1 Action): Beating its chest, the Minotaur unleashes a guttural, terrifying roar that echoes through the corridors. All enemy creatures within a 40-foot radius must pass a Willpower(12) test or suffer a -2 penalty to their Defense and Agility until the end of their next turn as panic sets in."
    ],
