      "Rusted chain/Plate Armor",
      "1H BroadSword & Shield",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nUndead Flora: As an animated fusion of corpse and plant, the Revenant is entirely immune to the Bleeding, Disease, and Poison conditions.\n\nVerdant Regeneration: The parasitic moss constantly knits severed limbs and crushed bone back together. The Revenant regenerates D10 wounds at the start of its turn as long as it is standing on natural soil or swamp water. Taking Fire damage halts this regeneration for one turn.\n\nTinder-Dry Vulnerability: Despite its damp environment, the necrotic moss reacts violently to high heat. The Revenant takes double damage from all Fire-based magic and weaponry.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nWaterlogged Broadsword (Melee - Cost: 1 Action): The Revenant swings a heavily rusted, notched blade with single-minded, mechanical force. Relying on the pure, unyielding strength of its vine-muscles, this 1-Handed attack deals a flat +16 wounds. If the attack roll is an unmodified 10, the rusted blade shatters non-magical shields.\n\nStrangling Vines (Melee - Cost: 2 Actions): Extending a thick cluster of thorny vines from its chest and forearms, the Revenant attempts to crush its prey. This heavy grapple deals +16 wounds, and the target must pass an Agility(7) test or immediately suffer the Prone and Stunned conditions as the vines anchor them to the earth.\n\nNecrotic Spore Cough (Tactical / AoE - Cost: 1 Action): The creature's jaw unhinges, releasing a 15-foot cloud of choking, glowing green spores. Any living creature caught in the cloud must pass a Physique(10) test or suffer 1 Poison condition and have their line of sight heavily obscured for their next turn."
    ],
