      "Mountain Giant: The Earth-Shaker",
      "Enormous",
      "Giant / Elemental",
      "",
      "Dwarfing their Hill Giant kin, Mountain Giants are walking geographical features. Standing upwards of 40 feet tall, their skin is heavily calcified, resembling jagged granite crags interwoven with thick, root-like veins. They do not wear armor; they simply allow the earth and stone to fuse with their flesh. Sluggish but apocalyptically powerful, they smell of ozone, crushed minerals, and deep-earth dampness, wielding uprooted monoliths as casually as a man wields a club.",
