      "Uprooted Stone Monolith",
      "Stone Monolith",
      "Hurled Crag",
      "Passive Traits\nTectonic Footing: The Mountain Giant is quite literally rooted to the earth. It is completely immune to the Prone, Knockback, Grappled, and Restrained conditions. Furthermore, any ground within 60 feet of the giant becomes severe Difficult Terrain as the earth splinters and shifts under its sheer weight.\n\nGranite Carapace: Blades simply chip against its calcified flesh. Any physical Melee attack that deals Slashing or Piercing Wounds has its damage halved before it even reaches the Giant's massive 30 Armor Mitigation.\n\nGranite Hide: Non-magical weapons that roll a Critical Failure (1 on the d10) when striking the Giant's Defense immediately shatter against its stone-like flesh.\n\nTremorsense: Smelling of ozone and deep-earth dampness, the Giant tracks its prey through the soil. It completely ignores visibility penalties from darkness, fog, or invisibility as long as the target is touching the ground within 120 feet.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nAvalanche Stomp (Cost: 1 Action): The Giant raises a massive, rocky foot and brings it down on a specific target area. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) targeting a 10-foot radius. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 40 Bludgeoning Wounds to anyone caught underneath.\n\nMonolith Sweep (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Giant casually swings its massive stone pillar. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) with a 30-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 100 Bludgeoning Wounds. Targets struck must pass a severe Agility(10) test or be launched 30 feet through the air, taking additional falling damage.\n\nGeological Upheaval (Cost: 2 Actions): The Giant slams both fists into the earth, triggering a catastrophic shockwave. All ground-bound enemies within a 60-foot radius must pass a Physique(11) test. On a failure, they take 4d10 + 40 Bludgeoning Wounds, are knocked Prone, and become Deafened by the booming thunder of cracking bedrock.\n\nCrag Bombardment (Range Cost: 2 Action): The Giant rips a massive chunk of granite from its own calcified body or the surrounding earth and hurls it. Make a Ranged attack (+2 To-Hit) against a 20-foot radius area up to 100 feet away. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 40 Bludgeoning Wounds to all targets in the zone."
    ],
