    "values": [
      "Mummy High Priest: The Scroll-Keeper",
      "Medium",
      "Undead (Caster)",
      "",
      "While the sovereign mummies act as unstoppable juggernauts of physical force, the High Priests were the architects of the ancient burial rites. In undeath, they are physically frail, their bones brittle and their linens turning to dust. However, their minds remain perfectly preserved libraries of forbidden necromancy. They do not wield heavy khopeshes; they hover slightly above the tomb floor, surrounded by orbiting, glowing papyrus scrolls. A Mummy High Priest rarely engages in melee, preferring to summon scarab swarms, resurrect fallen tomb robbers, and utter words of withering that turn flesh to ash from across the room.",
