      "Staff of the Jackal, Orbiting Papyrus Scrolls",
      "Staff of the Jackal",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nAegis of the Scrolls: The High Priest is surrounded by ancient papyrus scrolls that automatically intercept incoming fire. The first Ranged attack that successfully hits the High Priest each round is automatically negated, turning the intercepting scroll to ash.\n\nFunerary Wards: Any enemy that successfully deals Melee damage to the High Priest immediately takes 5 unmitigable Necrotic Wounds as the dark magic holding the mummy's bones together lashes out at the attacker.\n\nTinder-Dry: Without the heavy, hardened resin of the brute mummies, this frail caster is incredibly flammable. The High Priest possesses a severe vulnerability to Fire, taking double damage from all flame-based attacks.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nPharaoh's Decree(TN8) (Cast - Cost: 2 Actions): The creature unhinges its jaw, releasing a soundless, terrifying magical scream that reverberates directly in the minds of its enemies. This heavy cast deals 1d10 + +25 wounds of pure necrotic energy to a single target. The victim must pass a Willpower(9) test or suffer 2 Stunned conditions as their mind is temporarily trapped in total darkness.\n\nWord of Withering(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Priest utters a single, guttural syllable of an ancient language. Target one creature within 60 feet. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 25 Necrotic Wounds, and the target must pass a Willpower(8) test or gain the Weakened condition(1/2 damage dealt) until the end of their next turn.\n\nScarab Swarm(TN10) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Priest points its staff, summoning a localized plague. A 15-foot radius area within 40 feet instantly fills with flesh-eating scarabs. All enemies in the zone must pass an Agility(10) test or take 20 Piercing Wounds and suffer the Blinded condition for 1 round.\n\nCommand the Dust(TN6) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The High Priest weaves magic into the tomb floor. It instantly resurrects 1 + 1d6 fallen Lesser Undead (such as skeletons or zombies) within 30 feet, or it heals a single allied Brute Mummy for 15 Wounds."
    ],
