      "1-3",
      "Tarnished Gold Adornments, Cursed Khopesh (Hooked Sword)",
      "Supernatural Slam / Cursed Khopesh",
      "Breath",
      "Passive Traits\nUndead Constitution: As an animated, preserved corpse devoid of blood or organs, the Mummy is entirely immune to the Bleeding, Disease, and Poison conditions.\n\nDesiccated Form: The centuries-old, dried linens and alchemical resins that preserve the creature make it incredibly flammable. The Mummy takes double damage from all Fire-based magic and weaponry.\n\nRotting Aura (The Millennial Curse): The Mummy’s 9 Charisma radiates a lethal curse. Any living creature that ends its turn within 10 feet of the Mummy must pass a Willpower test or suffer the Weakened condition, instantly halving their Physical stat and Melee Wounds for their next turn as their muscles temporarily wither.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBreath of the Tomb (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Mummy unhinges its jaw and exhales a 15-foot cone of choking tomb dust and flesh-eating scarabs. All enemies in the area must pass a Physique(7) test or take 1d10 + 20 Piercing/Necrotic Wounds and gain the Blinded condition for 1 round as their eyes and lungs fill with grit.\n\nDesiccating Slam (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A brutal, heavy-handed strike. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 18 Bludgeoning Wounds. If this attack deals damage, the Mummy heals 5 Wounds as it siphons the moisture and vitality from the target's flesh.\n\nGaze of the Sovereign (Cost: 1 Action): The Mummy locks its hollow, glowing eye sockets onto a target within 30 feet. Make a Charisma vs. Willpower check. On a success, the target's mind is overwhelmed by millennial dread; they drop whatever they are holding and gain the Paralyzed condition until the end of their next turn.\n\nKhopesh of the Sands (Melee - Cost: 2 Actions): Drawing a massive, crescent-shaped ceremonial blade, the Mummy executes a heavy, two-handed executioner's swing. This devastating strike doubles its unnatural strength to deal an uncompromising 1d10 + 32 wounds. The target must pass a Physique(9) test or be knocked Prone by the sheer force of the blow.\n\nRotting Grasp (Melee - Cost: 1 Action): The Mummy reaches out with a decaying, heavily bandaged hand, channeling the physical weight of centuries. This relentless 1-Handed strike crushes armor and bone, dealing a +18 wounds. If the attack roll is an unmodified 10, the dark magic clinging to its hands inflicts 1 Disease condition, bypassing normal immunities."
    ],
