      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nHallucinogenic Cloud: A passive 10ft aura; any non-Mycelian must fail a Willpower (7) test or become Confused (+1 AP cost for all actions).\n\nVibrational Sense: The creature senses movement through the mycelial network and ignores all penalties from Darkness or Blindness.\n\nFungal Regrowth: While standing on natural soil, the Veil-Stalker regains 5 Wounds at the start of its turn.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nPsychedelic Touch (1 Action): Melee +6. On a hit, the target's mind is scrambled. They must swap their Agility and Intellect stats for 1 turn.\n\nSpore-Step (1 Action): The stalker melts into the ground and emerges 30ft away near any other visible mushrooms.\n\nInfest (TN 7 - 2 Actions): Releases spores into a target's lungs. Target takes 1d10 Poison damage each turn until they pass a Resist test."
