      "6",
      "1-3",
      "Twin Rusted Cleavers / Pitted Axes.",
      "Cleaver Chop. Strikes",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nScent of Copper & The Thumping Drum: The Butcher has no eyes, rendering it completely immune to visual illusions, magical darkness, and blinding effects. It \"sees\" through tremorsense and the smell of blood. If a creature has a beating heart or is currently suffering from a Bleeding condition, they cannot gain the benefits of Stealth or Invisibility against the Butcher within 100 feet.\n\nAbyssal Stealth (Spilled Oil): Despite its towering bulk, the Butcher makes absolutely no sound when it moves. It can slide seamlessly through the shadows, allowing it to move through spaces occupied by other creatures without penalty. If it initiates combat from darkness, enemies suffer Disadvantage on their Initiative rolls.\n\nAsymmetrical Anatomy: Because its secondary rib-tentacles operate independently of its primary cleaver-wielding arms, the Butcher does not suffer any penalties for fighting multiple opponents. It can maintain a grapple on up to two different targets while still swinging its cleavers at full strength.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTentacle Snare (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Butcher lashes out with the fluid, prehensile appendages. Make a melee attack (+3 To-Hit) with a 10-foot reach. If successful, this deals no Wounds, but the target is instantly Grappled. A grappled target has their Movement reduced to 0, and the Butcher can freely drag them along as it moves.\n\nThe Silent Chop (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Butcher brings its rusted cleavers down in a brutal, quiet arc. Make a melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 25 Wounds. If the target is currently Grappled by the Butcher's tentacles, the Butcher gains Advantage on this attack and automatically inflicts 1 Bleeding condition as it saws into the pinned meat.\n\nMeat-Grinder Maelstrom (Melee Cost: 3 Actions): The Butcher spins its massive frame, lashing out with rusted axes, cleavers, and grasping tentacles in a whirlwind of gore. The Butcher makes a single +3 To-Hit roll, applying the result against the Defense of all enemies within 10 feet. Any enemy hit suffers 2d10 + 60 Wounds, is pushed 5 feet away, and suffers 1 Bleeding condition. This violently severs any grapples it currently holds, tossing the carved victims aside."
    ],
