      "1",
      "Light-Eater Armor (Provides stealth and spell mitigation).",
      "Ethereal Fangs",
      "Psychic Piano-Wire Silk. Shoots razor-thin strands up to 60ft",
      "Passive Traits\nEthereal Sight: The Nightmare Spider's vision naturally overlaps the Material and Ethereal planes. It can see perfectly through solid walls, doors, and obstacles up to 60 feet away. It is completely immune to Invisibility, illusions, and magical darkness, making it the ultimate tracker.\n\nLight-Eater Plating: The void-forged armor it wears actively drinks in ambient light. In dim light or darkness, the spider and its rider practically cease to exist visually, granting them automatic Advantage on all Stealth tests and imposing Disadvantage on any Ranged attacks made against them.\n\nSilent Skitter: Despite its massive size and heavy armor, its specialized padded feet make absolutely zero sound. It never triggers sound-based traps, tremorsense, or alarms. It can carry a rider at full Movement speed across ceilings and vertical walls without making a single click or scraping noise.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nPiano-Wire Snare (Range Cost: 1 Action): The spider shoots a strand of razor-thin, psychically charged silk at a target within 60 feet. Make a Ranged attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 25 range Wounds. The wire wraps around the target's limbs; if the target moves more than 5 feet on their next turn, the wire slices into them, immediately inflicting 2 Bleeding conditions and 1d10 Wounds before snapping.\n\nEthereal Lunge (Cost: 2 Actions): The spider shifts its fangs partially into the Ethereal Plane right before it strikes, bypassing physical matter entirely. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 20 melee Wounds and completely ignores all of the target's Wound Mitigation from physical armor or shields (using only their natural/magical mitigation).\n\nPsychic Resonance Hum (Cost: 1 Action): The spider vibrates the void-metal plates of its armor, emitting a concentrated burst of psychic feedback. All enemies within a 20-foot radius must pass a Willpower(10) test. On a failure, they suffer 1 Stunned condition and take 2d10 psychic Wounds as the high-frequency hum scrambles their senses and disrupts their balance."
