      "1-5",
      "Uprooted Tree Trunk / Massive Splintered Club",
      "Massive Club",
      "Throwing Debris/Rocks",
      "Passive Traits\nFrenzied Hunger: The scent of fresh blood drives the Ogre into a feeding frenzy. If an enemy within 30 feet suffers a Bleeding condition, the Ogre gains a +2 bonus to its Movement and +To-Hit rolls as it recklessly charges toward its next meal.\n\nIron Stomach: An Ogre will eat absolutely anything, from rotting carrion to rusted metal armor. Because of this horrific diet, they are completely immune to ingested poisons and any Disease conditions.\n\nMomentum of the Maw: The Ogre treats all characters of Size Medium or smaller as difficult terrain, meaning it can simply walk through their spaces by making an opposed Physical check to shove them aside.\n\nThick Blubber: The dense layers of fat and gristle beneath the Ogre's skin act as exceptional natural mitigation. They ignore the first 3 points of damage from any standard piercing or blunt weapon attack.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBelly Slam (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Ogre surges forward and weaponizes its own grotesque mass. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 20 Bludgeoning Wounds and the target must pass an Agility(7) test or be violently knocked Prone and flattened under its weight.\n\nDevour (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Ogre grabs a Prone or Grappled target and attempts to take a massive bite out of them. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 35 Piercing Wounds. If this deals damage, the Ogre immediately heals 15 Wounds as it consumes the fresh meat.\n\nUprooted Tree (Melee - Cost: 2 Actions): Wielding a massive, splintered log or a crude club made of stone and iron bands, the Ogre brings it down with devastating, uncontrolled force. As a 2-Handed weapon multiplied by its Large size, this catastrophic slam deals 1d10 + 54 wounds. Any target struck by this must pass a Physique(10) test or instantly be knocked Prone and suffer 1 Stunned condition.\n\nBone-Snapping Bite (Melee - Cost: 1 Action): Dropping its weapon or grabbing a target with one massive hand, the Ogre attempts to take a massive bite out of its prey. This natural attack deals 1d10 + 20 wounds. If the attack roll is an unmodified 10, the sheer trauma of the bite inflicts 2 Bleeding conditions.\n\nHeave Debris (Range - Cost: 1 Action): Digging its massive, filth-caked fingers into the earth, the Ogre rips up a boulder or a chunk of masonry and hurls it. Calculating its half-Agility and half-Physique, multiplied by its Large size, this heavy projectile deals 1d10 +21 wounds on impact."
    ],
