      "",
      "Skull-Topped Fetish Staff, Bone Armor, Pouches of Reagents (Teeth, Blood, Ash)",
      "Fetish Staff",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nGuttural Casting: The Witch-Doctor does not use delicate incantations. Their Casting attacks cannot be prevented by the Silenced condition, and they do not provoke counter-attacks when casting a spell while engaged in melee combat.\n\nBone Wards: The skulls hanging from the Ogre's armor are bound with protective spirits. Any Ranged attack made against the Witch-Doctor suffers Disadvantage, as the skulls animate to chatter and bite at incoming arrows.\n\nUnyielding Mass: Because of its Large size and immense density, the Witch-Doctor cannot be physically pushed, Grappled, or knocked Prone by Melee attacks from Medium or smaller creatures.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBlood-Boil Hex(TN7) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Witch-Doctor locks eyes with a target and crushes a handful of raw meat. Target one enemy within 60 feet. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, the target takes 1d10 + 25 Fire/Necrotic Wounds as their blood literally cooks in their veins, and they gain the Weakened condition.\n\nSpirits of the Maw (Cost: 1 Action): The Ogre opens its mouth unnaturally wide and exhales a cloud of screaming, spectral jaws. All enemies in a 30-foot cone must pass an Agility(7) test or take 15 Necrotic Wounds and lose 5 points of WM-B/S (Spell Mitigation) for the remainder of the encounter as the spirits tear away their magical defenses.\n\nCrushing Staff (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A brutal, straightforward slam with the massive iron-shod fetish staff. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 20 Bludgeoning/Necrotic Wounds."
