      "Passive Traits\nForesight: The Oracle's third eye glimpses attacks before they happen. It forces any attacker rolling a natural 10 on a To-Hit against it to reroll the attack once per turn.\n\nAura of the Triad: Any ally within 15 ft of the Oracle gains +1 to their Willpower characteristic and +1 to their WM-B/S (Wounds Mitigation - Bless/Spell).\n\nEthereal Float: The Oracle ignores all ground-based hazards, traps, and difficult terrain, hovering silently above the battlefield.\n\nActions\nMind Fracture(TN5) (Casting Cost: 1): Targets one enemy within 60 ft. The target must make a Willpower Save (vs Int 7). On a failure, they take 10 Wounds and gain the Confused condition, forcing them to move in a random direction on their next turn.\n\nThree-Fold Ward(TN8) (Casting Cost: 2): The Oracle places a glowing triangular ward on an ally. The next three times that ally takes damage, the damage is reduced by 10.\n\nGlimpse of the Void (Area Cost: 3): The Oracle opens its third eye fully, projecting a 30 ft cone of psychic agony. All enemies in the cone take 3d10 + Casting Wounds (10) and lose 1 Action on their next turn due to mental shock."
    ],
