      "1",
      "+2 Bolted Steel Armor, The Anvil-Axe (Heavy 2H Melee), Jagged Javelins",
      "The Anvil-Axe (Massive Executioner's Cleaver)",
      "Jagged Javelins. Hurled from the Wyvern's back up to 60ft",
      "Passive Traits\nAura of the Warlord: The Chieftain's roaring presence dominates the battlefield. All allied Orcs within 60 feet are completely immune to the Frightened and Charmed conditions. Furthermore, any Orc that starts its turn in this aura gains a +2 bonus to their Melee Wounds.\n\nBloodlust Aura: The Chieftain’s very presence drives his war-host into a frenzy. All allied Orcs and beasts (including the Wyvern) within 40 feet of the Chieftain gain a permanent +10 to their Melee Wounds and become completely immune to the Fear and Charmed conditions as long as the Chieftain is alive.\n\nDeath Before Dishonor: If the Chieftain is reduced to 0 Wounds, his unbreakable Willpower kicks in. Instead of dying immediately, he remains at 1 Wound and instantly gains 1 free Action to make a final, desperate melee swing against the nearest enemy before collapsing.\n\nSky-Warlord's Bond: While mounted on the Wyvern, the Chieftain and the beast share their Initiative turn. The Chieftain cannot be forcefully dismounted or knocked Prone by any attack unless the attack specifically targets the saddle's rigging. Additionally, any Melee attacks made by the Chieftain against targets below him (while mounted) automatically gain Advantage.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nExecutioner's Cleave (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Chieftain brings his massive anvil-axe down in a devastating, sweeping arc. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 2d10 + 45 Wounds and instantly sunders the target's defenses, permanently reducing their Armor Mitigation by 5. If this attack kills the target, all enemies within 30 feet must pass a Willpower(6) test or suffer 1 Exhausted condition from sheer terror.\n\nCommanding Bellow (Cost: 1 Action): The Chieftain roars a guttural command, dictating the flow of the battlefield. The Chieftain chooses one allied creature within 60 feet (often his Wyvern or an Orc lieutenant). That ally immediately gets to use its Reaction to make one free Melee attack or move up to half its Movement speed.\n\nLeap of the Iron-Breaker (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): Designed for when the Wyvern dive-bombs into the enemy ranks. The Chieftain leaps from the saddle directly into the fray. He can dismount as a free action and immediately make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) against an adjacent enemy. If this attack hits a target that is currently Prone or Stunned (like from the Wyvern's Sky-Crush), it deals an automatic 2 Bleeding conditions.\n\nShatter the Line (Cost: 2 Actions): The Chieftain lowers his shoulder and surges into the enemy ranks. He moves up to 30 feet in a straight line. Any enemy in his path must make an Agility(11) test against his Physical To-Hit. On a failure, they take 25 Bludgeoning Wounds, are violently pushed 10 feet to the side, and are knocked Prone."
    ],
