      "5-20",
      "Rusted Chopper, Splintered Wood Shield, Stolen Trinkets.",
      "Rusted Chopper",
      "Crude Spear or Rock",
      "Passive Traits\nMob Bravery: The Grunt is a coward when isolated. If it is not standing within 15 feet of at least one other allied Orc, it suffers a negative modifier to its Willpower(-1) tests. However, when adjacent to an allied Orc, it automatically gains Advantage on checks made to resist the Frightened condition.\n\nExpendable Fodder: The Grunt is completely worthless to the warband's hierarchy. When a Grunt is killed, it does not trigger any morale checks or panic in allied Orcs. In fact, larger Orcs can move freely through a Grunt's space by physically shoving them aside.\n\nReckless Charge: When the Grunt uses a Movement action to move at least 15 feet directly toward a target, its first Melee attack that turn deals an additional 3 Slashing Wounds due to its wild momentum.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nWild Hack (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A sloppy, wide swing with its rusted chopper. Make a Melee attack (+1 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 8 Slashing Wounds.\n\nShield Bash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Grunt thrusts its splintered wooden shield forward to create space. Make a Melee attack (+1 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 3 Bludgeoning Wounds and physically pushes the target 5 feet away.\n\nScavenger's Throw (Range Cost: 1 Action): The Grunt hurls whatever is handy—a jagged rock, a broken spear, or a handful of dirt. Make a Ranged attack (+1 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 4 Bludgeoning Wounds and the target is mildly distracted, giving the next allied Orc to attack them Advantage on their To-Hit roll."
    ],
