      "2-6",
      "Battered Iron Cleaver, Spiked Knuckles, Scrap Armor",
      "Iron Cleaver",
      "Bows",
      "Passive Traits\nBare-Knuckle Brawler: If the Orc is disarmed or its weapon is broken, it does not suffer the standard penalties for fighting unarmed. Its Unarmed strikes deal 1d10 + 12 Bludgeoning Wounds due to its spiked knuckles and raw 9 Physical strength.\n\nBattle-Hardened: The Orc’s thick skin and dense bone structure grant them a natural resistance to physical trauma. They gain a +2 bonus to their Physical Armor mitigation against any non-magical bludgeoning or slashing attacks.\n\nRelentless Fury: When an Orc is reduced to below 15 of its Total Wounds, it enters a state of primal rage. It ignores the effects of the Stunned condition and gains a +2 bonus to all Melee +To-Hit rolls until it is slain.\n\nGreen Tide Synergy: Orcs fight better in a frenzy of their own kind. For every other friendly Orc within 10 feet, the Orc gains a cumulative +1 bonus to its Willpower (up to a maximum of +4) as the collective bloodlust drowns out fear.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBrutal Headbutt (Melee - Cost: 1 Action): Often used when locked in close quarters, the Orc slams its thick skull into the opponent’s face. This attack deals +14 wounds and requires the target to pass a Physique(9) test or suffer 1 Stunned condition.\n\nBlack-Iron Great Ax (Melee - Cost: 2 Actions): Reaching for the massive blade strapped to its back, the Orc delivers a crushing overhead split. Because this is a 2-Handed weapon, dealing a massive 1d10 +30 wounds.\n\nGuttural Roar (Cost: 1 Action): The Orc beats its chest and unleashes a deafening war cry. All enemies within 15 feet must pass a Willpower(6) test or suffer the Dazed condition for 1 round, their ears ringing from the sheer volume.\n\nJagged Cleaver (Melee - Cost: 1 Action): The Orc swings a heavy, single-edged blade made of crude pig-iron. This 1-Handed strike leverages the Orc's high Physique to deal 1d10 + 14 wounds. On an unmodified 10, the jagged edge inflicts 1 Bleeding condition."
    ],
