      "Armor-Rending Claws / Bone-Crushing Beak",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits:\nArmor-Rending: The Owlbear's claws are designed to peel bark and bone. Any time it rolls a Critical Hit with a Melee attack, it permanently reduces the target’s WM-Arm (Armor Mitigation) by 3 as it shreds through their protection.\n\nFrenzied Bloodlust: When the Owlbear is reduced below half of its total Wounds (45), it flies into a rage. Its Melee To-Hit increases to +1, and it ignores 1 point of Armor Mitigation on all targets it strikes.\n\nSilent Approach: Despite its massive size, its owl-like feathers absorb sound. The Owlbear's first attack in any combat encounter gains a +3 To-Hit bonus if it moved at least 20 ft from a flanking or hidden position.\n\nAction Based Abilities\nCrushing Beak (Cost: 1 Action): A devastating bite aimed at a vital area. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 24 Piercing Wounds and ignores 5 points of the target's WM-Arm.\n\nTearing Flurry (Melee Cost: 2): A coordinated assault of swiping claws and a snapping beak. Deals normal 1d10 + 24 Melee Wounds and forces the target to make a Physique(8) Test. On a failure, the target gains 1 Bleeding condition.\n\nCrushing Bear Hug - (Melee Cost: 1): Can only be used on a target struck by the Tearing Flurry in the same turn. The Owlbear grapples the target, automatically dealing 2x Physique Wounds (18) and rendering the target Prone and Grappled.\n\nPiercing Screech - (Area Cost: 1): Unleashes a deafening, terrifying hoot-roar. All enemies within 30 ft must make a Willpower(7) Test or suffer 1 Stunned condition and be Deafened (Disadvantage on communication/awareness) for 2 turns."
