      "Pearlescent Coat, (or Celestial Barding if equipped by a rider)",
      "Flashing Hooves",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nWind Rider: If the Pegasus flies at least 40 ft before attacking, its Melee To-Hit increases by +1 and its Defense increases by +2 against all Ranged attacks for the remainder of the round.\n\nAura of Purity: As a celestial being, it naturally wards off darkness. Allies (and its rider) within 30 feet of the Pegasus gain a +2 bonus to their WM-B/S (Wounds Mitigation - Bless/Spell) and are immune to Fear conditions.\n\nEthereal Grace: The Pegasus is immune to all falling damage, ignores all difficult ground terrain, and does not trigger ground-based traps or pressure plates even when walking.\n\nAction Based Abilities\nFlashing Hooves (Cost: 1 Action): A rapid, rearing strike with its front hooves. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 18 Bludgeoning Wounds.\n\nGalopping Escape - (Movement Cost: 1): The Pegasus instantly disengages from melee combat without triggering free strikes from enemies. It immediately flies up to 45 ft away, carrying its rider safely out of the fray.\n\nSoaring Dive (Movement/Melee Cost: 2): The Pegasus folds its wings and drops like a stone, striking with its front hooves. Deals normal 1d10 + 18 Melee Wounds. If the target is Medium or smaller, they must make a Physique(12) Test or take 1 Stunned condition and be knocked Prone.\n\nStar-Fire Flare (Cost: 1 Action): The Pegasus rears back and flares its wings, emitting a blinding flash of celestial light. All enemies within a 15-foot radius must pass an Agility(9) test to cover their eyes or suffer the Blinded condition for 1 round."
