      "Hell-Forged Plate, The Scourge Mace, Cloak of Hellfire",
      "Scourge Mace Strike (+3)",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nAura of the Inferno: The air around the Pit Fiend is superheated. Any enemy that ends its turn within 15 feet of the Fiend automatically takes 10 Fire Wounds. The Fiend itself is completely immune to Fire and Poison damage.\n\nCloak of Hellfire (Aura): The Pit Fiend is wreathed in literal, roaring hellfire. Any creature that ends its turn within 15 feet of the Fiend, or successfully strikes it with a Melee weapon, automatically takes 10 Fire Wounds.\n\nDiabolical Mind: With a 18 Intellect and 9 Willpower, the Pit Fiend is immune to all Charm, Fear, and Mind-Altering conditions. Furthermore, any spell cast at it with a To-Cast roll of less than 5 automatically fizzles out.\n\nLord of the Pit: Allied Fiends or Cultists within 60 feet gain a +2 bonus to their Melee To-Hit and share the Pit Fiend's Fear immunity, driven by their absolute terror of their master.\n\nAction Based Abilities\nExecutioner's Toll (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A brutal, calculated swing with its massive mace. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 40 Bludgeoning/Necrotic Wounds. If this attack drops a target to 0 Wounds, their soul is instantly pulled into the mace, healing the Fiend for 20 Wounds.\n\nHellfire Mace (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): A crushing blow with its massive weapon. Deals normal 1d10 + 90 Melee Wounds. On an unmodified To-Hit roll of 9 or 10, the target must make a Physique(10) Save or gain 1 Stunned condition and 1 Bleeding condition.\n\nWord of Damnation(TN10) (Casting Cost: Actions 2): Speaks a word of pure dark magic at a target within 100 feet. The target must make a Willpower(13) Test. On a failure, they take 2d10 + 36 Casting Wounds, and the Pit Fiend heals for 5 Wounds as it leeches their life force.\n\nInfernal Command - (Area/Summon Cost: 3): Tears open a momentary rift to the hellscape. The Pit Fiend summons 1d4 Lesser Devils (use standard Imp or Cultist stats) to immediate adjacent spaces. These summoned creatures can act on the next turn."
