      "1",
      "A grotesque mountain of scarred muscle and iron chains bred exclusively for the infernal fighting arenas. To truly showcase the devastating impact of the Enormous size class, this creature trades the magical utility of the Pit Fiend for raw, unadulterated physical obliteration. A bloated, lumbering engine of violence. Its skin is a patchwork of thick scar tissue and embedded iron. It swings lengths of shattered arena chains like whips, pulverizing anything stupid enough to stand in its shadow. It knows no strategy, no magic, and no mercy—only the roar of the arena and the crunch of bone",
      "Massive Chain Whips",
      "",
      "Passive Traits\nNumb to the Pain: The Pit Hulk has endured so much punishment that it ignores all secondary damage from Bleeding, Disease, or Poison conditions.\n\nUnstoppable Colossus: Because of its Enormous size, it completely ignores Prone, Stunned, and Knockback effects from any creature of size Large or smaller.\n\nMeat Hooked: Whenever the Pit Hulk rolls an unmodified 8, 9, or 10 on a Melee To-Hit, its heavy chains wrap around the target. The target is instantly Grappled and pulled into an adjacent square.\n\nAction Based Abilities\nChain Sweep (Area Cost: 1): Swings its massive chains in a 30 ft arc. All enemies in the arc must make an Agility(1d10 + to-hit) Test or take 70 Wounds and be knocked Prone.\n\nLumbering Stomp (Cost: 1 Action): The bloated fiend raises a massive, iron-shod foot and slams it into the earth. All enemies within 15 feet of the Hulk must pass an Agility(1d10 + to-hit) test or take 20 Bludgeoning Wounds and fall Prone from the localized earthquake.\n\nPulverizing Slam (Melee Cost: 3): Brings both massive chained fists down on a single target. Make a single To-Hit roll. If it connects, it deals double its massive Melee Wounds 1d10 + 100 Wounds and permanently shatters the target's equipped shield or weapon, if non-magical.\n\nRoar of the Blood Pit (Area Cost: 1): Beats its own chest and releases a guttural, terrifying roar. All enemies within 40 ft must make a Willpower(8) Test. On a failure, they are Frightened (Disadvantage on all To-Hit and Casting rolls) for 2 turns."
    ],
