      "Plague Rat Swarm",
      "Large",
      "Swarms",
      "",
      "A seething, biting, chittering carpet of diseased rodents. They do not fight with tactics or strategy; they simply overwhelm by sheer numbers, tearing at armor gaps, climbing up legs, and spreading infectious filth.\n\n\"Individually weak, but collectively a nightmare. A Rat Swarm moves as a single, fluid entity. Weapons that pierce or slash are largely ineffective against a tide of a thousand bodies. They must be burned, blasted, or crushed to be truly destroyed.\"\n\n",
