      "100+",
      "None",
      "Swarming Bites (+2)",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nSwarm Anatomy: The Swarm operates by completely different physical rules. It is utterly immune to the Grappled, Prone, and Paralyzed conditions. It takes half damage from all single-target Piercing or Slashing attacks, but possesses a severe vulnerability to Area-of-Effect attacks (like a fire spell or explosive), taking double damage from those sources.\n\nAmorphous Mass: The swarm can move through any gap or space large enough for a single rat. It completely ignores the Prone, Stunned, and Grappled conditions, and it cannot be flanked.\n\nSuffocating Presence: Any enemy that starts its turn sharing a space with the Rat Swarm automatically takes 5 Piercing Wounds and suffers Disadvantage on all Ranged and Casting attacks due to rats constantly climbing up their legs.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nDevouring Wash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Swarm thrashes violently. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit) against every creature currently sharing a space with the Swarm. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 10 Piercing Wounds, and the target must pass a Physique(5) test or gain the Infected condition.\n\nSurge (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Swarm moves up to its full Movement speed in a straight line, rolling directly through enemy spaces. Any creature it passes through must pass an Agility(6) test or be knocked Prone and take 1d10 + 20 Piercing Wounds as the rats scramble over them.\n\nCling and Gnaw (Cost: 1 Action): The rats attempt to physically weigh down a target. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit) against one target sharing its space. On a hit, the target becomes Slowed (halving their movement speed) until they use an Action to physically brush the biting vermin off their armor."
