      "A spectacular fusion of Pyreborn metallurgy and raw elemental fury. By permanently binding their soul to the 'Loom' of fire, these warriors sacrifice their lower body to become a hovering pillar of sentient magma and flame. Its upper half is built of thick, corded muscle and charred-obsidian skin, adorned with heavy bronze bracers and collars. Its lower half tapers into a roaring cyclone of pure, surging flame that allows it to glide effortlessly across the battlefield. In its hands, it wields two impossibly huge, glowing-hot scimitars that slice through armor like butter. A Cinder-Djinn does not march to war; it flows, turning the battlefield into an inescapable oven.",
