      "Oversized Scimitars",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nMagma Cyclone: Because it hovers on a pillar of flame, the Cinder-Djinn completely ignores difficult terrain, ground-based traps, and the effects of deep water (though water produces blinding steam). Any creature that starts its turn adjacent to the Djinn takes 5 Fire Wounds from the ambient heat.\n\nDual-Wielding Deflection: While wielding both of its oversized scimitars, the Cinder-Djinn can use its weapons to actively parry. It gains a permanent +1 to its Defense against all Melee attacks.\n\nElemental Core: The Djinn is completely immune to Fire damage and the Burning condition. However, it possesses a severe vulnerability to Cold damage, taking double Wounds from all frost or ice-based attacks as its obsidian skin fractures under thermal shock.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSearing Slash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A brutal, sweeping strike with one of its glowing scimitars. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 23 Slashing/Fire Wounds.\n\nScissor Cleave (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Djinn crosses both massive blades and shears them outward in a devastating executioner's strike. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 45 Slashing/Fire Wounds, and the target's WM-Arm is ignored by 5 points as the molten metal melts through their plate.\n\nCyclone Dash (Cost: 1 Action): The Djinn surges forward on its pillar of flame. It moves up to 30 feet in a straight line without triggering defensive counter-attacks. Any enemy the Djinn passes adjacent to during this movement must pass an Agility(8) test or gain the Burning condition(1d10 wounds)."
    ],
