      "2-5",
      "Heat-Treated Bronze Armor, Obsidian Macem, Pyromancer's Focus",
      "Obsidian Mace",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nSun-Forged: The Pyreborn Warrior is completely immune to all Fire and Heat-based damage. Furthermore, any spell or attack that utilizes Fire heals the Warrior for half the Wounds it would normally deal.\n\nMomentum of the Magma: Slow to start, but impossible to stop. The Warrior is immune to the Knockback and Prone conditions from any creature of Large size or smaller.\n\nTempered Weapons: The Pyreborn's mastery of the Loom means their weapons are always kept at a super-heated threshold. Their Melee attacks ignore 2 points of the target's WM-Arm (Armor Mitigation) as the heated obsidian melts through standard mail.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBreath of the Loom (Cost: 2 Actions): The Sun-Forged channels their innate pyromancy, unleashing a wave of roaring flame from their gauntlet. All enemies within a 15-foot cone must pass an Agility(d10+4) test or take 1d10 + 20 Fire Wounds and gain the Burning condition.\n\nObsidian Greathammer (Melee Cost: 2): A devastating, heavy swing with a two-handed weapon. Deals normal 1d10 + 25 Melee Wounds. If the Warrior rolls an unmodified 9 or 10 on the To-Hit, the immense weight of the blow forces the target to make a Physique(6) Save or gain 1 Stunned condition.\n\nSearing Grasp (Melee Cost: 1): The Warrior drops one hand from its hammer and grabs the target with its superheated bronze gauntlet. Deals 1d10 Fire Wounds. The target must make an Agility(6) Test or be Grappled, taking an additional 1d10 Fire Wounds at the start of each of the Warrior's turns until they break free with a Physique vs Physique Test.\n\nIgnite the Loom(TN7) (Casting/Area Cost: 1): The Warrior drags its obsidian hammer across its bronze armor, showering the area in a wave of pyromantic sparks. All enemies in a 15 ft cone must make an Agility Save or take 1d10 + 12 Fire Wounds and gain 1 Bleeding (Burn) condition."
