      "Pyreborn Thrall: The Living Supernova",
      "Medium",
      "Humanoid (Pyreborn)",
      "",
      "The Ember-Thralls are Pyreborn who have undergone the \"Ritual of the Great Burn.\" Their skin has been systematically charred until it is as hard and brittle as anthracite, and their internal heat is so intense that they are perpetually wreathed in flickering, orange-red flames. They carry no shields and wear no armor, for they believe that to cover their burning spirit is a sin. In battle, they move with a frantic, twitchy energy, often lashing themselves with chains of heated bronze to keep their \"inner fire\" stoked. They don't seek to survive; they seek to be consumed. When an Ember-Thrall charges, they aren't just looking for a kill—they are looking to turn themselves into a human supernova.",
