      "Heated Bronze Chains",
      "Thrashing Bronze Chains",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Human Supernova: When the Ember-Thrall is reduced to 0 Wounds by any means (or by its own Action), it instantly detonates. All creatures within a 15-foot radius must pass an Agility(6) test or take 20 Fire Wounds and be violently knocked Prone. On a success, they take half damage and remain standing.\n\nWreathed in Flame: The Thrall's body is dangerously hot. Any creature that hits the Ember-Thrall with an Unarmed strike, or Grapples it, automatically takes 5 Fire Wounds.\n\nMasochistic Zeal: The Ember-Thrall is completely immune to the Frightened and Charmed conditions. Furthermore, any time the Thrall takes Wounds but is not killed, its Movement speed increases by 10 feet for its next turn as the pain fuels its sprint.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nScorched Lash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A wild, frantic swing with its heated bronze chains. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit) with a 10-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 7 Fire Wounds.\n\nStoke the Fire (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Thrall violently whips its own back with the heated chains, voluntarily taking 2 Wounds. In exchange, its inner fire surges, granting it Advantage on its next Melee attack and expanding its \"Human Supernova\" detonation radius by 5 feet.\n\nThe Great Burn (Cost: 2 Actions): The Ember-Thrall actively forces its own core to go critical. The Thrall instantly dies, automatically triggering its \"Human Supernova\" passive trait exactly where it stands."
