      "Scavenged Chainmail, Heavy Rusted Halberd",
      "Heavy Rusted Halberd",
      "",
      "Passive Traits\nFilth-Born: The Vanguard is completely immune to all Disease and Poison conditions. Any creature that successfully hits the Vanguard with an unarmed strike or natural weapon must make a Physique(6) Save or gain 1 Disease condition.\n\nPhalanx of the Depths: When standing adjacent to at least one other Ratman Vanguard, their interlocking halberds create a defensive wall. They gain a +2 bonus to their Defense against Melee attacks and cannot be flanked.\n\nPolearm Reach: Because of their long halberds, the Vanguard can make Melee attacks against targets up to 10 feet away. If an enemy moves into this 10-foot reach, the Vanguard may use a Reaction to immediately make one free Melee attack against them to halt their advance\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBrace the Line (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Vanguard locks its boots into the earth and points its halberd forward. Until the start of its next turn, its Defense increases by 2. Any enemy that successfully damages the Vanguard with a Melee attack from within 5 feet automatically takes 8 Piercing Wounds from the braced blade.\n\nImpaling Thrust - (Melee Cost: 2): A focused, brutal thrust designed to punch through armor. Deals normal 1d10 + 13 Melee Wounds. If the To-Hit roll is an unmodified 9 or 10, the jagged blade tears on the way out, inflicting 2 Bleeding conditions on the target.\n\nSweeping Cleave - (Area Cost: 1): Swings the heavy halberd in a wide, knee-high arc. All enemies in a 10 ft frontal arc must make an Agility(8) Test or take half Melee Wounds (7) and be knocked Prone.\n\nCommand the Vermin - (Area Cost: 1): Barks a harsh, chittering order. All lesser Ratmen (Scavengers) or Rat Swarms within 30 ft gain a +1 bonus to their next To-Hit roll, emboldened by the Vanguard's presence."
