      "4-15",
      "Stitched Leather, Rusted Shiv, Pouch of Filth",
      "Rusted Shiv",
      "Throwing Darts",
      "Passive Traits\nFilth-Born: The Ratman is completely immune to all Disease and Poison conditions. Any creature that successfully hits the Ratman with an unarmed strike or natural weapon (like a bite) must make a Physique(6) Test or gain 1 Disease condition.\n\nPack Cowardice: A Ratman's bravery is tied entirely to its swarm. While adjacent to at least one allied Ratman, it gains Advantage on all Melee To-Hit rolls. However, if a Ratman starts its turn without an ally within 15 feet, it must pass a Willpower(7) test or use its turn to immediately flee\n\nSwarm Tactics: If two or more Ratmen are engaged in melee with the same target, they all gain Advantage on their Melee To-Hit rolls and bypass 2 points of the target's Armor Mitigation (WM-Arm) by finding gaps in the plating.\n\nSkittering Evasion: The Ratman can move through the spaces of enemy creatures without penalty, provided the enemy is at least Medium size. They ignore difficult terrain penalties in subterranean environments.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTetanus Shank (Cost: 1 Action): The Ratman lunges with its filth-encrusted blade. Make a Melee attack (+1 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 4 Piercing Wounds, and the target must pass a Physique(5) test or gain the Infected condition, suffering 5 unmitigable Wounds at the start of their next 2 turns\n\nShatter-Vial - (Ranged/Area) Cost: 2 Actions): Throws a stolen, haphazardly crafted alchemical vial up to 40 ft. It bursts in a 10 ft radius. All creatures in the area must make an Agility(6) Test or take 2d10 Acid Wounds and gain 1 Blind condition, gaining disadvantage for all actions for 1 turn as the noxious fumes burn their eyes.\n\nCoward's Retreat - (Movement Cost: 1): The Ratman instantly disengages from melee combat, taking no free strikes from adjacent enemies, and moves its full Move speed (50 ft) toward the nearest shadows, grating, or cover."
