      "The greatest hoard of gold and magical artifacts in the known world",
      "Obsidian Horns & Titanic Claws",
      "Liquid Flame",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Heat Shimmer (Mirage): The constant, rippling heat surrounding the dragon bends light and warps trajectories. Any Ranged attack (arrows, bolts, thrown weapons) made against the dragon automatically suffers Disadvantage. Furthermore, any enemy starting their turn within 30 feet of the dragon takes 10 Fire Wounds just from the ambient, suffocating heat.\n\nCastle-Wall Scales: The dragon's hide is practically impenetrable to mundane weapons. If a physical Melee attack fails to deal more than 10 Wounds (after mitigation is applied), the weapon simply bounces off the crimson scales, dealing 0 Wounds instead.\n\nSupreme Arrogance: The dragon views mortals as mere snacks. It is completely immune to the Charmed, Frightened, and Taunted conditions. However, its greed dictates its targeting: it will always prioritize attacking the player carrying the highest-tier magical item or the most gold, aiming to reclaim its \"rightful hoard.\"\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nLiquid Flame Exhalation (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The dragon unleashes a 100-foot cone of sulfurous, sticky liquid fire. Make a Ranged attack (+6 To-Hit). On a hit, targets take 1d10 + 50 Fire Wounds and gain 2 Burning conditions. The liquid flame sticks to the environment, turning the entire blast zone into severe Difficult Terrain that deals 20 Fire Wounds to anyone walking through it for the rest of the combat.\n\nMeteor Dive (Melee Cost: 3 Action): The dragon takes to the blood-red sky and crashes down on a target like a comet. It moves up to 60 feet (ignoring terrain) and makes a Melee attack (+7 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 2d10 + 130 Wounds, and the sheer seismic impact knocks every other enemy within a 20-foot radius Prone.\n\nObsidian Crown Sweep (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): A brutal, dismissive swipe with its jagged horns. Make a Melee attack (+7 To-Hit) against all targets in a 20-foot frontal arc. If successful, targets take half Wounds, 1d10 + 30 and are violently thrown 30 feet backward, potentially taking environmental collision damage."
