      "Riding Saddle, Bit & Bridle, Saddlebags",
      "Panicked Hooves",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nPrey's Vision: Because a horse's eyes are set on the sides of its head, it has a massive field of vision. The Riding Horse cannot be flanked or surprised by mundane stealth unless the attacker is directly underneath or directly behind it in its small blind spot.\n\nFlight Response: When the horse takes any damage or fails a Willpower test against a Fear effect, it immediately gains a positive modifier to its Agility checks and Movement speed for the remainder of the encounter as adrenaline floods its system.\n\nBeast of Burden: The horse's Physical stat is perfectly tuned for hauling. It ignores Movement penalties from carrying heavy loads or encumbered riders, making it the perfect pack animal.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBolt! (Cost: 2 Actions): The horse gives into panic and focuses entirely on escape. It immediately moves up to double its normal Movement speed of 70 away from the nearest source of danger.\n\nPanicked Kick (Melee Cost: 1 Action): If cornered, the horse lashes out blindly with its rear hooves. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 20 Bludgeoning Wounds and physically pushes the target 5 feet back.\n\nRearing Hooves (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The horse rears up on its hind legs and strikes downward with its front hooves. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 12 Bludgeoning Wounds. If this attack scores a Critical Hit, the target is knocked Prone."
