      "he Star-Forged Greatsword, Seamless Celestial Plate",
      "Star-Forged Greatsword",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nArbiter of Destruction: The Seraphim naturally disrupts dark magic. Its Melee and Casting attacks completely ignore the WM-Arm and WM-B/S of any Undead, Fiend, or heavily mutated target, carving through their unnatural defenses as if they weren't there.\n\nBlinding Radiance (Aura): The Seraphim is a living sun. Any creature that ends its turn within 20 feet of the Seraphim takes 10 Radiant Wounds. If the creature is Undead or a Fiend, it takes 20 Radiant Wounds instead and must pass an Agility(9) test or gain the Blinded condition.\n\nFirmament Wings: The Seraphim’s six wings are semi-ethereal constructs of force and light. When the Seraphim is successfully struck by a ranged or spell attack, the wings reflexively pulse, reflecting half of the mitigated wounds back at the attacker as a beam of searing light.\n\nSupernova Martyrdom: A Seraphim leaves no corpse. If reduced to 0 wounds, its celestial core instantly destabilizes. All gravity in a 60-foot radius reverses, pulling all enemies 10 feet toward the Seraphim. At the start of the next turn, the Seraphim detonates, dealing 10d10 + 50 absolute damage to everything in the radius and leaving only a crater of scorched, permanently consecrated earth.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSever the Veil (Cost: 3 Actions): The Seraphim strikes the very fabric of reality with its greatsword, tearing open a temporary rift to the celestial plane. This releases a devastating shockwave of holy fire in a 60-foot cone. All enemies in the cone suffer 4d10 + 60 wounds and must pass a Physique(9) test or be knocked prone. Daemons and Undead caught in the blast take double damage and are pulled 20 feet toward the rift.\n\nJudgment's Gaze (Cost: 2 Actions): The Seraphim locks eyes with a single target within 100 feet, forcing them to experience the cosmic weight of all their past sins simultaneously. The target must pass a severe Willpower(9) test. If they fail, they immediately suffer 3 Stunned conditions (paralyzing them) and take d10 wounds for every sentient creature they have killed in the past month (or a flat 5d10 + 30 wounds if tracking kills is too difficult).\n\nMeteor Strike (Cost: 3 Actions): The Seraphim launches itself high into the air and crashes down at a target location up to 150 feet away like a falling star. Any enemy within a 20-foot radius of the impact takes 3d10 + 40 wounds and catches fire. Any friendly creature within the impact zone is instead infused with celestial haste, gaining +1 Action on their next turn and being instantly cured of any Bleed or Poison conditions.\n\nSupernova Cleave (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): A flawless, devastating arc with the star-forged greatsword. Make a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit) with a 15-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 90 Slashing/Radiant Wounds.\n\nWord of Salvation(TN10) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Seraphim speaks a single, resonant note of divine law. Target up to three allied creatures within 60 feet. Make a Casting attack (+5 To-Hit). On a hit, all negative conditions (Bleeding, Poisoned, Paralyzed, Frightened) are instantly purged from the targets, and they heal 20 Wounds."
