      "Multi-Jointed Spiny Fingers",
      "Can hurl splintered shards of its own blackened wood body up to 40ft for 15 Wounds.",
      "Passive Traits\nArmor Threading: The Shade Crow’s multi-jointed fingers are perfectly adapted to bypass defenses. All of its melee attacks ignore 2 points of Wound Mitigation provided by worn armor (target uses only natural mitigation).\n\nHollow Anatomy: Because its body is a hollow cage of dry vines and wood, it does not have vital organs. It is immune to the Bleeding condition, and piercing weapons deal half damage to it. However, because of its brittle, dry nature, it takes double wounds from all bludgeoning and Fire-based attacks.\n\nShadow-Meld: When in dim light, darkness, or heavy foliage, the blackened vines of its body absorb light. It becomes nearly invisible, granting enemies Disadvantage on To-Hit rolls against it until it makes an attack or enters a brightly lit area.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nGourd-Seed Spite (Cost: 2 Actions): The creature's \"head\" splits open, expelling a cloud of jagged, cursed seeds in a 15-foot cone. All enemies in the cone take 2d10 + 10 wounds. Those damaged must pass a Willpower(7) test; on a failure, the seeds burrow into their skin, causing agonizing hallucinations and inflicting 1 level of Exhaustion as shadow-magic floods their nervous system.\n\nTendon Snare (Range Cost: 1 Action): The Shade Crow detaches a long, whip-like tendon of blackened vine from its own body and lashes it at a target's legs up to 20 feet away. If it hits, the target takes no damage but their Movement is immediately reduced to 0 until the end of their next turn unless they spend an action to physically cut or tear the vine away.\n\nSiphoning Grapple (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Crow threads its fingers deep into the target's armor and attempts to lock them in place. Make an Agility vs. Agility check against a target. On a success, the target is Grappled, and the Crow siphons their vitality, dealing 15 unmitigable Piercing Wounds and healing itself for 10 Wounds.\n\nVisor Pierce (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A lightning-fast strike aimed at an exposed gap. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 10 Piercing Wounds. If this attack rolls a 10, it strikes an eye or vital artery, dealing double damage and applying the Blinded condition for 1 round."
    ],
