      "Siberian Tiger: The Ghost of the Taiga",
      "Large",
      "Beast / Animal",
      "",
      "A titan among felines, stretching up to 11 feet in length. Its fur is a thick, luxurious coat of orange-gold, broken by obsidian stripes that act as perfect camouflage against the vertical shadows of a winter forest. Despite its massive size, it moves with a terrifying, liquid silence, its paws acting like natural snowshoes. Often revered as a forest spirit or guardian, it hunts with cold, calculated efficiency. An encounter usually begins and ends before the prey realizes they are hunted—a sudden blur of orange, a paralyzing roar, and claws that effortlessly shear through chainmail.",
