      "Surgical Talons",
      "The Chill of Justice",
      "Passive Traits\nPacifying Aura (Winter & Ozone): The permanent chill surrounding the dragon acts as a natural de-escalator. Any enemy starting their turn within 30 feet of the Dragon must pass a Willpower(9) test. On a failure, they lose any Enraged or Frenzied conditions and gain the Lethargic condition, reducing their Movement and Agility by half.\n\nMaster of the Arcane: The Silver Dragon requires no somatic or material components to cast spells, utilizing its massive 18 Intelligence. Furthermore, when the Dragon casts a spell, it may freely choose to deal non-lethal Wounds, instantly rendering targets unconscious at 0 Wounds rather than killing them.\n\nSurgical Evasion: Because of its immense 12 Agility, any Ranged or Melee attack that misses the Dragon triggers an immediate, free Movement action for the Dragon to reposition up to 30 feet in the air without triggering counter-attacks.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBreath Weapon: Sub-Zero Mist (Cost: 2 Actions): The Dragon exhales a billowing, 60-foot cone of freezing mist and ozone. All targets in the area must pass a Physical(10) test against the Dragon's Casting To-Hit (+4). On a failure, they take 1d10 + 45 Cold Wounds and are Frozen (Stunned) in a layer of thick ice until they are broken out. On a success, they take half damage and are not frozen.\n\nArcane Severance(TN7) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Dragon utilizes a surgical strike of pure magic to disarm a conflict. Target one creature within 60 feet. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, the target's weapon is telekinetically thrown 20 feet away, or their active magical buffs are instantly dispelled.\n\nGale-Force Buffet (Cost: 1 Action): The Dragon snaps its massive wings, generating a localized hurricane. All enemies within 20 feet must pass an Agility(12) test or take 15 Bludgeoning Wounds and be violently knocked Prone, effectively ending a melee skirmish without shedding blood."
