      "Rusted Shortsword or Spear, Rotting Wooden Shield, Rusted Shortbow.",
      "Rusted Weapons.",
      "Decaying Shortbow. Fires brittle arrows up to 60ft",
      "Passive Traits\nMarrowless Frame: Being nothing but animated bone, the Skeleton is completely immune to the Bleeding, Disease, and Poison conditions. Furthermore, Piercing weapons (like spears, rapiers, or arrows) simply pass through the gaps in their ribs, dealing only half Wounds. However, Blunt/Crushing weapons (like maces or warhammers) shatter their fragile frames, dealing double Wounds.\n\nMindless Automaton: The Skeleton has no nervous system, brain, or sense of self-preservation. It is completely immune to all psychological effects, including Fear, Charm, and Mind-Control. It also cannot be inflicted with the Stunned condition from physical pain or trauma.\n\nNecromantic Resonance: When a Skeleton is reduced to 0 Wounds and shatters, the dark magic binding it is violently released. Any allied Undead spellcaster (like a Necromancer or Lich) within 30 feet immediately absorbs this residual magic, healing for 1d10 Wounds.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSwarm the Living (Cost: 1 Action): Skeletons are programmed to drag down their prey through sheer numbers. If the Skeleton makes a melee attack against a target that is currently engaged in melee with at least one other allied Skeleton, it gains Advantage and +1 on its To-Hit roll.\n\nGrasping Bone (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Skeleton drops its weapon and lunges forward with both bony hands, attempting to grab onto the armor or limbs of its target. Make a melee attack (+1 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 0 Wounds, but the target is Grappled, reducing their Movement to 0. A target must spend 1 Action to physically shatter or pry the skeletal hands off to break free. Make a Physique vs Physique test to break fee.\n\nShatter-Spike (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Skeleton violently snaps off one of its own ribs or arm bones to use as an improvised, jagged dagger. It makes a desperate melee lunge (+1 To-Hit). If successful, the jagged bone splinters inside the target, dealing 2d10 + 10 Wounds and causing 1 Bleeding condition. Using this ability permanently reduces the Skeleton's own maximum Wounds by 5."
