      "Blowgun, Venom-Dipped Darts, Barbed Javelin",
      "Barbed Javelin (Used in melee)",
      "Blowpipe",
      "Passive Traits\nCanopy Crawler: The Skink possesses a climbing speed equal to its normal Movement speed. They can move freely across branches, sheer walls, and ceilings without penalty, automatically gaining Advantage on stealth checks when elevated.\n\nSwamp Skirmisher: The Skink treats deep water and thick underbrush as normal terrain. Furthermore, if a Skink makes a Ranged attack while obscured by foliage, its position is not automatically revealed.\n\nHit and Fade: If the Skink successfully damages an enemy with a Melee or Ranged attack, its Movement speed is increased by 10 feet until the end of its turn, allowing it to easily retreat out of counter-attack range.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nVenom-Dipped Dart (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Skink fires a dart from the shadows. Make a Ranged attack (+3 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals only 1d10 + 6 Piercing Wounds, but the target must pass a Physique(6) test or gain the Poisoned condition, taking 5 unmitigable Wounds at the start of their next 2 turns.\n\nJavelin Toss (Range Cost: 1 Action): A swift throw of a light spear. Make a Ranged attack (+3 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 6 Piercing Wounds.\n\nDarting Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): If cornered, the Skink stabs frantically with its javelin. Make a Melee attack (+0 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 4 Piercing Wounds and the Skink immediately shifts 5 feet backward without triggering a defensive reaction."
