      "8",
      "",
      "None",
      "Mythical Lion Claws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nThreads of Foresight: Because the Sphinx can see the immediate future, it cannot be Surprised or Flanked. Furthermore, any enemy attacking the Sphinx with a physical Melee or Ranged weapon must roll their To-Hit with Disadvantage, as the Sphinx has already seen the trajectory of the blow and adjusted its stance.\n\nThe Psychic Lock: Any enemy that starts its turn within 60 feet of the Sphinx must pass a Willpower(9) test. On a failure, their reality is anchored; they cannot use any Movement actions this turn, forced to stand entirely still while their mind fights the lock.\n\nRiddle's Resonance: The Sphinx's voice is a magical conduit. Any time the Sphinx speaks or asks a riddle, its Charisma modifier acts as a passive aura. Any enemy within 60 feet cannot benefit from Inspire, Focus, or any Morale-boosting effects while in its presence, as their minds are weighed down by its sovereign authority.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nPounce of the Sovereign (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Sphinx leaps up to 40 feet to crash into a target with its massive lion body. Make a melee attack (+5 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 90 Wounds and the target must pass a Physique(10) test or gain the Prone and Grappled conditions. If this attack is used against a target that is currently suffering from The Psychic Lock, the attack automatically hits and deals an additional 2d10 Wounds as they are ripped from their time-loop by the physical trauma.\n\nThe Psychic Lock (Cost: 2 Actions): The Sphinx fixes its sovereign gaze on a target within 80 feet and speaks a riddle of their own timeline. The target must pass a severe Willpower(11) test. If they fail, they are psychically locked in a time-loop: they immediately suffer 4 Stunned conditions (losing their next turn). Furthermore, the Sphinx literally \"unwrites\" the target's timeline—any Wounds that the target inflicted upon the Sphinx during the previous round are instantly healed by the Sphinx.\n\nTemporal Displacement Buffet(TN13) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Sphinx beats its expansive eagle wings, unleashing a 40-foot cone of chronal wind and golden sand. Make a Casting roll (+8 To-Cast) against all enemies in the cone. On a success, they take 3d10 + 40 temporal Wounds. In addition, time slows down drastically for them: affected targets lose 1 Action on their next turn and have their Movement halved.\n\nThe Chronos Riddle(TN9) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Sphinx projects a reality-warping paradox directly into the minds of its enemies. A 40-foot radius area within 80 feet becomes a zone of fractured time. All enemies in the zone must pass an Intelligence(10) test or take 40 Psychic Wounds and gain the Dazed and Slowed conditions as they are forced to mentally relive their most painful failures."
    ],
