      "Stone Golem: The Monolith Warden",
      "Giant",
      "Construct / Elemental",
      "",
      "Forged not in a foundry, but carved directly from the heart of a mountain or the pillars of a forgotten temple, the Stone Golem is a towering, 20-foot-tall humanoid shape composed of solid, rune-carved granite. It does not hiss with steam; instead, its joints grind with the deafening sound of shifting tectonic plates. Overgrown with centuries of moss and creeping vines, it acts as a silent, eternal sentinel. It has no need for weapons; its fists are heavy enough to cave in a fortress gate. Its featureless stone face is set in a permanent, stoic mask that never shows fatigue, pain, or mercy.",
