      "None",
      "Granite Fists",
      "Hurled Rubble",
      "Passive Traits\nImmutable Form: The magic that binds the Stone Golem is absolute. It is completely immune to any spell or effect that would alter its form (such as Petrification or Polymorph) and cannot be magically teleported against its will.\n\nMagical Inertia: The Golem's ancient stone acts as a grounding rod for hostile magic. Any spell cast directly at the Golem that deals Fire, Cold, or Lightning damage automatically has its total Wounds halved before applying to Wound Mitigation.\n\nTectonic Mass: The Giant-sized Monolith Warden is completely immune to the Knockback, Prone, Grappled, and Restrained conditions from any creature smaller than Giant size. It ignores all Movement penalties for moving through non-magical Difficult Terrain, crushing obstacles into dust as it walks.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nFortress-Breaker Slam (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Golem brings down a fist the size of a wagon. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) with a 15-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 40 Bludgeoning Wounds. If this attack targets a door, wall, or environmental cover, it deals double Wounds, instantly obliterating it.\n\nRune of Slowing (Cost: 2 Actions): The ancient glyphs carved into its chest flare with suppressing magic. All enemies within a 30-foot radius must pass a Willpower(9) test. On a failure, they gain the Slowed condition for 1 round (their Movement is halved, and they lose 1 Action on their next turn) as time itself seems to grind to a halt around the titan.\n\nAvalanche Stride (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Golem uses its massive weight to trample its foes. It moves up to its full 30 Movement speed in a straight line, freely entering the spaces of smaller creatures. Any creature whose space it enters must pass an Agility(8) test or take 40 Bludgeoning Wounds and be knocked Prone."
