      "Thunderhead Armor, Continent-Splitter Greatsword",
      "Continent-Splitter",
      "Supercell Bolt",
      "Passive Traits\nPhilosopher’s Foresight: Having spent decades predicting the future, the Tempest-Lord cannot be Surprised, automatically wins Initiative ties, and forces any attacker rolling a Critical Hit against him to re-roll and take the lower result.\n\nEye of the Supercell: The area within 120 feet of the Giant is a Category 5 hurricane. All non-magical Ranged attacks automatically fail (the wind tears the arrows away). Any enemy attempting to fly within this radius is instantly violently grounded, taking falling damage.\n\nThunderhead Recoil: His armor is made of dying clouds and raw static. Any Melee attack that strikes the Giant triggers a recoil of lightning, instantly dealing 15 Lightning Wounds back to the attacker and pushing them 5 feet backward.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nContinent-Splitter (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Giant swings a greatsword that arcs with apocalyptic power. Make a Melee attack (+7 To-Hit) with a 40-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 120 Slashing/Lightning Wounds, and completely destroys any non-magical cover, shields, or structures in the weapon's path.\n\nAtmospheric Guillotine (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Tempest-Lord uses the atmosphere itself as a blade, condensing air pressure into a razor-sharp wave. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) in a 60-foot line. On a hit, targets take 1d10 + 70 Force/Slashing Wounds and are knocked Prone.\n\nWrath of the Exploding Star (Cost: 4 Actions): The Giant spends his entire Titanic turn to unleash the cosmic power of his burning eyes. A 100-foot radius around the Giant is bombarded with devastating celestial lightning. All enemies must pass a severe Agility(15) test. On a failure, they take 5d10 + 50 Lightning/Radiant Wounds and are permanently Blinded and Deafened by the sheer magnitude of the blast."
