      "Frozen Tear Jewelry",
      "Desperate Rake, Velvet-Down Wings & Claws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nAura of Frozen Tears: The sorrowful gems she wears emit a 30-foot aura of profound, crushing emotional despair. Any enemy within this radius completely loses the benefits of any Morale bonuses, Inspire actions, or Focus points. Furthermore, healing spells cast within this radius only heal for half their normal amount, as the target's will to live is actively suppressed.\n\nPhantom Motion: She moves with a blurring, unnatural grace. The Matriarch never triggers free attacks or attacks of opportunity when moving out of melee range, and she can move seamlessly through spaces occupied by other creatures without penalty.\n\nShifting Visage of Desire: The Matriarch's face and form constantly shift to reflect the deepest subconscious desires of the person looking at her. Any enemy attempting to target her with a Melee or Ranged attack must first pass a Willpower(12) test. On a failure, they suffer Disadvantage on the To-Hit roll because their mind actively fights their body's attempt to harm her.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nEcstatic Agony(TN12) (Casting Cost: 1 Action): The Matriarch touches a target's mind, flooding their nervous system with a conflicting mix of extreme pleasure and agonizing pain. Make a Casting roll (+4 To-Cast). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 45 psychic Wounds. The target must pass a severe Willpower(12) test or become Charmed for 1 turn. While Charmed this way, they cannot willingly move away from the Matriarch and will actively step in front of the next physical attack aimed at her.\n\nPhantom Step (Cost: 1 Action): The Matriarch blurs into a cloud of violet mist, instantly teleporting up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space she can see. If she teleports adjacent to a Charmed ally, she heals 10 Wounds by passively siphoning their devotion.\n\nThe Velvet Puppeteer(TN11) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): This is her ultimate tool of betrayal. She locks eyes with a target within 60 feet. Make a Casting roll (+4 To-Cast) directly against the target's Willpower defense. On a success, she forcefully overtakes their nervous system. The Matriarch immediately forces the target to make one free Melee or Ranged attack against another target of her choice, using the victim's own stats, weapons, and bonuses.\n\nWeaponize the Subconscious(TN13) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Matriarch rips a dark secret or hidden resentment from a target's mind and broadcasts it telepathically to the rest of the party. The target must pass a severe Willpower(15) test. If they fail, they suffer 2 Stunned conditions as their mind reels from the exposure, and all allied creatures within 30 feet of the target take 2d10 + 20 psychic Wounds from the mental shockwave of the revelation."
