      "Treant: The Elder-Bark",
      "Enormous",
      "Plant (Elemental / Boss)",
      "",
      "A Treant stands nearly 30 feet tall, its \"skin\" a thick, gnarled armor of iron-hard bark covered in layers of ancient moss and lichen. Its arms are massive boughs capable of sweeping aside a line of knights like autumn leaves, and its legs are trunk-like pillars that leave deep craters in the earth with every step. Generally peaceful, meditative beings, they possess a \"Slow-Burning Rage.\" When a forest is desecrated, the Treant awakens, and its wrath is as unstoppable as a mudslide. They don't just fight; they mobilize the environment itself, commanding the very brush and roots to rise up and strangle the invaders.",
