      "None",
      "Massive Boughs",
      "Uprooted Boulders/Trees",
      "Passive Traits\nIron-Bark Anatomy: The Treant is a massive construct of dense living wood. It is completely immune to the Bleeding and Poison conditions. Piercing weapons (like arrows, spears, or rapiers) simply get stuck in its bark, dealing exactly half Wounds. However, it is highly vulnerable to Fire; any Fire-based attacks that bypass its Armor Mitigation deal double Wounds.\n\nDeep Roots: As long as the Treant is standing on natural earth, it cannot be knocked Prone, physically moved, or teleported against its will by any mortal force. Furthermore, at the start of its turn, it draws nutrients from the soil, automatically healing 2d10 + 20 Wounds.\n\nSlow-Burning Rage: The Treant's fury escalates as the forest (or itself) is harmed. For every 50 Wounds the Elder-Bark loses, it permanently gains +1 to its Melee To-Hit and its Movement increases by 10 feet as its sluggishness burns away into violent frenzy.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nAutumn Sweeper (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Treant swings its massive, bough-like arms in a brutal 180-degree arc in front of it. It makes a single To-Hit roll (+6) applied against the Defense of up to 4 targets in the arc. Anyone hit takes normal 1d10 + 45 Wounds, is violently pushed 20 feet backward, and must pass a Physique(13) test or be knocked Prone.\n\nEarth-Crater Stomp (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Elder-Bark raises a pillar-like leg and brings it down with the force of a mudslide. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit) against a single target. On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 50 Bludgeoning Wounds. If the target survives, they are driven directly into the earth and gain the Paralyzed condition until they can dig themselves out.\n\nReclaim the Soil(TN10) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Treant commands the surrounding environment to consume the intruders. Massive, thorny roots erupt from the ground in a 60-foot radius around the Treant. The entire area becomes severe difficult terrain. Any enemy starting their turn in this zone must pass an Agility(10) test or become Grappled by the roots (Movement 0) and take 2d10 crushing Wounds as the earth tries to pull them under.\n\nTimber Toss (Range Cost: 1 Action): The Treant reaches down, easily uproots a fully grown tree or a massive boulder, and hurls it across the battlefield. Make a Ranged attack (+2 To-Hit) at a target up to 120 feet away. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 30 Wounds. If this attack misses, the projectile shatters on the ground, dealing 2d10 shrapnel Wounds to anyone within 10 feet of the impact zone."
    ],
