      "Massive Boughs",
      "Can hurl large rocks or heavy deadwood",
      "Passive Traits\nDeep-Rooted: Because of its immense weight and wooden physiology, the Warden is completely immune to being pushed, Grappled, or knocked Prone by any creature of Large size or smaller.\n\nTimber Hide: The Warden's bark is exceptionally thick. It gains resistance (takes half damage) from all non-magical Piercing and Bludgeoning weapons. However, it possesses a severe vulnerability to Fire, taking double damage from all flame-based attacks as its dry foliage ignites.\n\nFalse Canopy: While the Treant stands completely still in a forested environment, it is visually indistinguishable from a normal, mundane tree. It automatically gains Advantage on checks made to ambush intruders.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nCrushing Branch (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A straightforward, heavy swing with a massive wooden arm. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 28 Bludgeoning Wounds.\n\nUprooting Sweep (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Treant drags a heavy branch across the ground in a wide arc. All enemies within a 15-foot cone must pass an Agility(7) test. On a failure, they take 1d10 + 28 Bludgeoning Wounds and are violently knocked Prone.\n\nSplintering Grasp (Cost: 1 Action): The Treant attempts to crush a target within its massive hands. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 15 Bludgeoning Wounds and the target is Grappled. While Grappled in this way, the target takes an automatic 10 Bludgeoning Wounds at the start of their turn from the sheer pressure."
    ],
