      "Iron Chains, Beastmaster's Harness",
      "Unbreakable Horns",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nSiege-Breaker: The beast's horns are designed to shatter fortifications. It deals double Wounds to all inanimate objects, structures, gates, and barricades. Furthermore, if the Beast strikes a target wielding a Shield, the Shield is instantly destroyed.\n\nUnstoppable Mass: Because of its Giant size and quadrupedal stance, the Siege Beast is completely immune to being Grappled, pushed, or knocked Prone by any creature of Large size or smaller. It can walk freely through the spaces of Medium or smaller creatures.\n\nFrontal Bone Crest: The massive frill of bone protecting its head makes it incredibly resilient from the front. The beast gains a permanent +2 to its Defense against any Ranged or Melee attacks originating from directly in front of it.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nJuggernaut Charge (Cost: 2 Actions): The beast lowers its head and thunders forward. It moves up to 35 in a straight line. Any creature in its path must make an Agility(8) test against its Physical To-Hit. On a failure, they take 1d10 + 45 Piercing/Bludgeoning Wounds, are launched 15 feet to the side, and knocked Prone.\n\nGore and Toss (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The beast violently jerks its head upward to skewer a target. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 45 Piercing Wounds, and if the target is Medium or smaller, they are violently thrown 20 feet backward by the toss.\n\nEarthshaking Stomp (Cost: 1 Action): The juggernaut rears up and slams its massive front legs into the earth. All enemies within a 20-foot radius must pass an Agility(7) test or take 15 Bludgeoning Wounds and fall Prone due to the localized tremor."
