      "1-5",
      "Relies on its claws and environment.",
      "Filthy Claws & Bite",
      "Hurled Filth/Boulders",
      "Passive Traits\nHyper-Cellular Regeneration: The Troll’s signature terrifying trait. At the start of its turn, the Troll automatically heals 1d10 Wounds and instantly removes 1 Bleeding condition. However, if the Troll took any Fire or Acid Wounds during the previous round, its regenerating cells are cauterized, and this ability does not trigger for that turn.\n\nPutrid Blood-Spatter: The Troll's veins are pumped full of highly toxic, acidic sludge. Any time the Troll is struck by a melee attack that deals Piercing or Slashing damage, it violently bleeds on the attacker. The attacker must pass an Agility(9) test or immediately take 1d10 Acid Wounds and gain 1 Poison condition (1d10 wounds) as the filth gets in their eyes and lungs. (Blunt/Crushing weapons bypass this trait).\n\nRubbery Anatomy: Because its flesh and bones are constantly mutating and somewhat soft, the Troll is highly resistant to concussive force. It takes only half Wounds from all physical Blunt/Crushing weapons (maces, hammers, staves), but takes normal Wounds from Slashing/Piercing weapons.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nFeral Rending (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Troll lashes out with its massive, dirty claws. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 30 melee Wounds. Because its claws are caked in rotting meat, the target must pass a severe Physique(8) test or suffer 1 Disease condition, halving their healing received until cured.\n\nCorrosive Regurgitation (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Troll violently empties its highly acidic stomach contents in a 20-foot cone. All enemies in the cone must pass an Agility(8) test. On a failure, they take 3d10 + 20 Acid Wounds, and the acid begins eating their gear—permanently reducing the target's Armor Mitigation by 5. On a success, they take half damage and their armor is spared.\n\nDismembering Bearhug (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Troll attempts to grab an enemy in both of its massive arms and literally squeeze the life out of them. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, the target is Grappled and Prone. If the Troll uses this ability on a target that is already Grappled from a previous turn, it deals 2d10 + 50 Wounds and automatically inflicts 2 Bleeding conditions as it begins to pull their limbs from their sockets.\n\nFrenzied Thrash (Melee Cost: 3 Action): The brute flails wildly, turning its body into a blender of muscle and claw. The Troll makes a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit) against all targets within its 10-foot reach. On a hit, targets take 1d10 + 18 Slashing Wounds and are pushed 5 feet away."
    ],
