      "he accumulated wealth, secrets, and artifacts of lost civilizations.",
      "Deity's Claws & Jaws",
      "Calamity Breath",
      "Passive Traits\nOmniscient Arrogance: Thanks to its 12 Intelligence, the True Dragon already knows everything about the heroes. It automatically knows the highest and lowest stats, current Hit Points, and exact magical loadouts of every character on the battlefield. It uses this information to ruthlessly exploit their weakest saves.\n\nElemental Embodiment: The True Dragon chooses one Element (Fire, Cold, Lightning, Acid) at the start of combat. It becomes completely immune to that Element, and any Ranged or Casting attacks it makes completely ignore the players' Wound Mitigation/Resistances against that chosen Element.\n\nThe Weight of Ages: The sheer physical and magical pressure it exerts is suffocating. Any Ranged attack (like an arrow or thrown spear) loses all kinetic energy as it approaches the dragon, completely failing to deal Wounds unless the attacker spends 1 Focus point to push the projectile through the pressure field.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBreath of the Calamity (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The dragon exhales pure, unadulterated elemental destruction. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit) against a massive 80-foot cone. On a hit, targets take 1d10 + 40 Wounds of the dragon's chosen element. The sheer force of the blast permanently destroys all non-magical cover (trees, boulders, walls) in the area.\n\nWord of Ruin(TN10) (Casting Cost:  Actions): Weaponizing its ancient knowledge, the dragon speaks a forgotten word of unmaking. Make a Casting attack (+5 To-Hit) against one target within 60 feet. On a hit, it deals 2d10 + 30 Psychic Wounds, and the target's strongest equipped magical item is temporarily deactivated/suppressed for 1 full round.\n\nTectonic Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The dragon simply brings a massive claw down upon the earth. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 60 Wounds. Regardless of if the attack hits or misses, the impact causes the ground within a 20-foot radius to rupture, instantly becoming severe Difficult Terrain."
