      "Tyrannosaurus Rex: The Apex Maw",
      "Giant",
      "(Prehistoric / Reptilian)",
      "",
      "The undisputed tyrant of the primeval jungles. A towering, bipedal predator stretching over forty feet from snout to tail, the Tyrannosaurus Rex is an engine of pure, uncompromising meat-eating aggression. It moves with a terrifying, ground-eating stride, crashing through ancient trees as if they were dry weeds. Its massive skull is lined with serrated teeth the size of daggers, driven by jaw muscles capable of crushing solid steel. To hear the deep, chest-rattling boom of its roar is to know you have stepped off the top of the food chain.",
