      "Bone-Crushing Jaws, Tail",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nBlood Scent: The T-Rex becomes a flawless tracker the moment blood is spilled. If any creature within 100 feet is suffering from Wounds or the Bleeding condition, the T-Rex automatically gains Advantage on all Awareness checks to find them and Advantage on its Melee To-Hit rolls against them.\n\nColossal Stride: The beast treats dense jungle underbrush, deep mud, and water as normal terrain. Due to its Giant size, it cannot be physically pushed, Grappled, or knocked Prone by Medium or smaller creatures, and it can simply walk through their spaces.\n\nArmor-Piercing Bite: The sheer kinetic force of the Tyrant's jaws bypasses standard defenses. All Melee attacks made by the T-Rex ignore 5 points of the target's WM-Arm (Armor Mitigation) as the teeth punch clean through plate metal.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nTyrant's Snap (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A lightning-fast, devastating lunge with its massive jaws. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 35 Piercing/Slashing Wounds.\n\nThrash and Pin (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The T-Rex bites down on a target and violently shakes its massive head. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 45 Piercing Wounds, and the target is violently slammed into the earth, gaining the Grappled and Prone conditions.\n\nDeafening Bellow (Cost: 1 Action): The beast fills its massive lungs and unleashes a chest-rattling roar. All enemies within a 60-foot cone must pass a Willpower(9) test or suffer the Frightened condition, their primal instincts forcing them to drop their weapons and flee."
