      "Umber-Hulk: The Chitinous Delver",
      "Large",
      "Monstrosity (Subterranean)",
      "",
      "A horrific fusion of ape-like musculature and dense, beetle-like chitin. Compressed into a terrifyingly heavy man-sized frame, the Umber-Hulk is the ultimate subterranean ambush predator. Its arms end in massive, diamond-hard claws capable of shearing through solid granite like wet clay. However, its most dreaded feature is its face: a cluster of four glowing, multifaceted eyes that project a localized psychic distortion. Those who lock eyes with the beast find their spatial reasoning shattered, leaving them wandering aimlessly or swinging at phantoms while the Hulk closes in for the kill.",
