      "1-2",
      "None",
      "Stone-Borer Claws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Alien Gaze: The Umber-Hulk's four compound eyes scramble the mortal mind. Any enemy that starts its turn within 30 feet and has line of sight to the Hulk's face must pass a Willpower test against the Hulk's 5 Charisma. On a failure, the target gains the Dazed condition, and the target's Movement is forced in a random direction (determined by the Game Master) for that turn.\n\nTremorsense: The creature's 4 Awareness is tied to the earth. It completely ignores magical darkness, invisibility, and visual illusions as long as its target is touching the ground within 60 feet.\n\nTunnel-Borer: The Hulk burrows through solid rock, leaving behind a 5-foot wide permanent tunnel. Because its claws are designed to crush granite, any Melee attack it makes completely ignores 5 points of the target's WM-Arm (Armor Mitigation).\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nChitinous Rake (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A brutal, heavy swipe with its massive claws. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 22 Slashing/Bludgeoning Wounds.\n\nMandible Crush (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Hulk attempts to bite a target cleanly in half. Target an enemy suffering from the Dazed or Prone condition. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 1d10 + 35 Piercing Wounds, and the target is violently pinned in the creature's jaws, gaining the Grappled condition.\n\nSubterranean Eruption (Cost: 1 Action): If the Umber-Hulk is currently burrowed beneath the earth, it violently erupts into an unoccupied space on the surface. Any adjacent enemies must pass an Agility(7) test or take 10 Bludgeoning Wounds from the flying stone and be violently knocked Prone."
