    "values": [
      "Umbra-Witch: The Void-Weaver",
      "Medium",
      "Monstrosity (Shadow / Caster)",
      "",
      "A tall, slender figure draped in \"Living Silk\"—a flowing garment woven from the captured shadows of executed enemies. Her skin is a translucent, porcelain white, pulsing with veins of liquid, pitch-black ink. Viewing the physical world as dirty and its inhabitants as \"unworthy,\" she glides an inch above the earth. Lacking physical weapons, she wields a floating Shadow-Loom of obsidian needles to stitch localized pockets of void and mind-breaking illusions. She is a master of \"The Mirror Game,\" a psychological torment that turns a hero's own memories and shadow against them, unmaking their sanity thread by thread.\n\nSometimes accompanied by mindless thralls made from the husks of past victims",
      "4",
      "5",
      "2",
      "12",
      "1",
