      "Wizardry",
      "5",
      "1",
      "Floating Shadow-Loom, Obsidian Needles",
      "Will use magical abilities or flee if engaged.",
      "Obsidian Loom Needles",
      "Passive Traits\nUnworthy Earth (Hover): Because she glides an inch above the ground, the Umbra-Witch is completely immune to all ground-based traps, pressure plates, tremorsense (rendering her invisible to Midnight-Hounds if they ever turned on her), and localized ground-spells (like Earthquake or Mud Wall).\n\nLiving Silk Shroud: The captured shadows she wears have a will of their own and actively move to protect her fragile porcelain body. Any normal Ranged attacks (arrows, bolts, throwing axes) directed at her suffer Disadvantage on the To-Hit roll, as the shadows reach out to swat the projectiles from the air.\n\nInk-Stitched Veins: She lacks warm blood. If she takes Wounds from a slashing or piercing melee attack, the pressurized pitch-black ink in her veins sprays outward. Any enemy within 5 feet of her when she is struck must pass an Agility(10) test or suffer 1d10 acid/shadow Wounds and be temporarily blinded until they wipe the ink from their eyes.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nThe Mirror Game (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Witch plucks a dark memory from a target's mind within 80 feet, weaving it into a terrifying, lifelike hallucination. The target must pass a severe Willpower(16) test. If they fail, they are convinced an ally or a loved one is attacking them. They immediately suffer the Stunned condition and take 4d10 + 45 psychic Wounds as their mind breaks under the psychological torture.\n\nPuppet Master (Melee Cost: 1 Action): She plucks the strings of a victim's mind. Target one enemy suffering from the Frightened or Dazed condition. Make a Casting attack (+4 To-Hit) against their Willpower. On a hit, the Witch takes total control of the target's shadow, physically forcing the hero to immediately make one free Melee attack against an adjacent ally of the Witch's choice.\n\nStitch the Shadow (Casting Cost: 2 Action): The Witch flicks her fingers, sending obsidian needles flying at a target's feet up to 60 feet away. Make a Casting roll (+8 To-Cast). If successful, she deals 2d10 + 20 Wounds, and the target's shadow is literally stitched to the floor. The target's Movement is reduced to 0 until they spend an Action to physically tear their shadow free (which causes an additional 1d10 Wounds to themselves).\n\nVoid-Pocket Evasion (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Witch weaves a localized pocket of the void and steps into it. She instantly teleports up to 50 feet away to any location she can see. When she vanishes, the void pocket violently collapses, creating an implosion. Any enemy within 10 feet of where she was standing takes 3d10 Wounds and is pulled 5 feet toward the center of the implosion."
    ],
