      "Disjointed Raking Claws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nBlood Frenzy: The Reaper's obsidian claws are highly reactive to spilled life force. If the Reaper attacks a target that is currently suffering from a Bleeding condition, it gains Advantage on its To-Hit rolls.\n\nElongated Reach: Because its limbs are disproportionately long and end in massive, forearm-length claws, the Reaper has a melee reach of 10 feet. This allows it to safely strike from behind a frontline of Midnight-Hounds without stepping into standard melee range itself.\n\nParadoxical Density: The obsidian-like material of its skeleton is both impossibly dense and unnaturally light. It completely ignores the first 10 Wounds of any non-magical physical attack that hits it. Furthermore, because it is so light, it never triggers pressure plates, leaves no footprints, and makes absolutely no sound when it walks, granting it Advantage on all Stealth or Surprise attempts.\n\nShadow-Burst Evasion: Because of its 9 Agility, the Flayer never triggers defensive or counter-attacks when moving out of an enemy's melee range. It can effortlessly slip through gaps in a frontline formation.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nFlaying Rake (Melee Cost: 2 Action): The Reaper sweeps its massive claws in a brutal arc. Make a melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 25 Wounds, and the sheer density of the claws actively shreds the target's defenses, permanently reducing the target's Armor Mitigation by 1 for the rest of the encounter (this effect stacks with multiple hits).\n\nUmbric Impalement (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Reaper lunges with terrifying speed, attempting to drive both of its elongated claws directly through a target's torso. Make a melee attack at +4 To-Hit. If successful, it deals 2d10 + 25 Wounds. The target is instantly inflicted with 2 Bleeding conditions and is considered Grappled, pinned on the end of the Reaper's claws until they can break free with a Physique vs Physique test.\n\nShadow-Step Evisceration (Cost: 2 Actions): The Reaper merges its lightweight frame with the shadows, instantly teleporting up to 30 feet to appear directly in the blind spot of an enemy. Make a melee attack (+6 To-Hit) that completely ignores the target's worn Armor Mitigation. If the target is already Bleeding, the shock of the sudden, brutal strike forces them to pass a Physique(8) test or immediately suffer a Stunned condition."
    ],
