      "Aristocratic Garb, Master-Crafted Rapier, Signet Ring, Vials of Vitae",
      "Master-Crafted Rapier, Crimson Claws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nUndead Anatomy & Sunlight Aversion: As a creature of the night, the Vampire is completely immune to the Poison and Disease conditions. However, they take double Wounds from any Radiant, Holy, or Fire-based attacks. If the Vampire starts its turn in direct sunlight (or magical equivalent), it suffers 2d10 Wounds and loses 1 Action for that turn.\n\nMist-Step Evasion: When the Vampire moves, it temporarily dissolves into a cloud of crimson mist. It never triggers free attacks or attacks of opportunity when moving out of melee range, and it can move through physical obstacles like iron grates, arrow slits, or even spaces occupied by other creatures without any movement penalty.\n\nBlood-Frenzy Regeneration: The Vampire is vitalized by the scent of fresh blood. If the Vampire starts its turn within 30 feet of any creature currently suffering from a Bleeding condition, the Vampire automatically heals 2d10 + 10 Wounds as it draws the ambient life force through the air.\n\nThe Crimson Gaze: Any enemy that starts its turn within 30 feet and has line of sight to the Vampire must pass a Willpower test against the Vampire's Charisma. On a failure, they gain the Charmed condition, viewing the Vampire as an awe-inspiring sovereign and becoming unable to target them with hostile actions.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nFlawless Lunge (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A blurring, textbook strike with their rapier. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Piercing Wounds and ignores 5 points of the target's WM-Arm.\n\nPredator's Gaze(TN9) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Vampire locks eyes with a target within 40 feet, attempting to completely dominate their will. Make a Casting roll (+4 To-Cast) against the target's Willpower defense. If successful, the target is Charmed. On their next turn, the Charmed target must use their movement to walk directly toward the Vampire and immediately drop any weapons they are holding.\n\nSever the Artery (Melee Cost: 2 Action): A blindingly fast swipe of elongated, hardened fingernails. Make a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 15 melee Wounds and bypasses half of the target's Armor Mitigation. The target automatically suffers 1 Bleeding condition.\n\nThe Crimson Kiss (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Vampire's signature feeding maneuver. This attack can only be used on a target that is currently Grappled, Stunned, or Charmed. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, the Vampire sinks its fangs into the victim, dealing 3d10 + 30 Wounds. The Vampire instantly heals Wounds equal to the damage dealt, and the victim permanently loses 1 point of Physique until they complete a long rest."
    ],
