      "Legendary",
      "Gilded Plate",
      "Sun-Forged Spear",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nDivine Presence (Aura): All allied Pyreborn units within 40ft gain +2 to Willpower and are immune to the Fear condition.\n\nMolten Fur: Any creature that hits the Vulkan-Kahn with a melee attack takes 2d10 fire damage as the god's fur superheats upon contact.\n\nApex Instinct: The Vulkan-Kahn gains a +5 bonus to Initiative and cannot be surprised or flanked.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSolar Roar (TN 8 - 2 Actions): A thunderous, magical roar that mimics the sun's birth. All enemies within 30ft must pass a Willpower test or be Stunned for 1 turn.\n\nBrass Strike (1 Action): A heavy melee strike with a sun-forged spear. Deals 3d10+12 damage and ignites the target (5 Burn damage per turn).\n\nThe Ancestral Shift (3 Actions): The Vulkan-Kahn reverts to its feral, four-legged form. For 3 turns, it loses its Spear and Armor, but its Movement doubles, it gains 2 extra Actions per turn, and its melee attacks gain 'Advantage 1' as it strikes with tooth and claw."
