      "\"The World-Splitter\" (Star-Iron Halberd)",
      "The World-Splitter, Tectonic Claws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nThe First Forge: Vulkan-Kahn is the literal origin of heat. He is entirely immune to Fire, Magma, and Heat damage. Furthermore, any enemy that strikes him with a melee attack takes 2d10 Fire Wounds immediately from his shimmering, white-hot needle fur.\n\nFeline Elegance: Despite his Titanic size, his 18 Agility allows him to ignore the standard penalties of his mass. He cannot be flanked, ignores all difficult terrain, and never triggers traps. He takes no falling damage.\n\nTectonic Heart: The rhythmic pulsing of his fissures regulates his god-like form. At the start of every turn, he automatically cures himself of all negative conditions (Bleeding, Poison, Disease, Stunned, Prone) and restores 10 Wounds.\n\nActions\nEruption of the Forge(12) - (Casting/Area Cost: 3): Vulkan-Kahn slams the butt of \"The World-Splitter\" into the ground, detonating the tectonic pressure within his stripes. All enemies within a 100 ft radius must make a Physique(14) Save. On a failure, they take 4d10 + 25 Casting Wounds, are knocked Prone, and are pushed 30 feet away from him by the shockwave.\n\nOn All Fours - (Movement/Melee Cost: 1): Vulkan-Kahn drops to all fours, becoming a blurring streak of white-hot fire. He dashes up to 250 feet in a straight line, passing directly through enemies. Any creature in his path must make an Agility(15) Test or take 1d10 +25 Wounds (half his normal melee output) and gain 2 Bleeding conditions.\n\nRoar of the Loom (Cost: 1 Action): He rears up on his hind legs and unleashes a roar that sounds like the earth splitting open. All enemies within an 80-foot cone must pass a Willpower test against his 9 Charisma or suffer the Paralyzed condition for 1 round, their nervous systems completely overwhelmed by the sonic pressure.\n\nWorld-Splitter Cleave - (Melee Cost: 2): A sweeping strike with his Star-Iron Halberd. Deals normal 1d10 + 50 Melee Wounds. If the target survives, their armor is instantly melted and destroyed, reducing their WM-Arm to 0, if non-magical, for the remainder of the encounter."
    ],
