      "Rusted Battleaxe, Heavy Iron-Bound Shield, Crude Plate",
      "Rusted Battleaxe, Iron-Bound Shield",
      "",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Iron Tide: An Iron-Bound warrior's strength is its formation. While standing adjacent to at least one allied Iron-Bound, it gains a +1 to its Defense and becomes completely immune to the Frightened condition.\n\nCrude Resilience: Because they feel no pain, the Iron-Bound ignore the first 5 Wounds of any non-magical Piercing or Slashing attack, shrugging off glancing blows that would cripple a normal man.\n\nHeavy Footing: Due to the sheer weight of their armor and mutated mass, they are immune to being physically pushed or knocked Prone by Melee attacks from Medium or smaller creatures.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBrutal Hack (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A straightforward, heavy swing with their rusted axe. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 15 Slashing Wounds.\n\nShield Bash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The warrior steps forward and violently shoves its heavy iron-bound shield into the target. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). On a hit, it deals 4 Bludgeoning Wounds, and the target must pass a Physique test or be violently knocked Prone.\n\nLock the Line (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The warrior locks its shield with its neighbors. Until the start of its next turn, all Melee and Ranged attacks made against this warrior suffer Disadvantage."
