      "Hell-Forged Greatsword, Fused Spiked Plate",
      "Hell-Forged Greatsword",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nBattle-Ready: Through extensive slaughter, they can confront up to 3 enemies in melee combat simultaneously without those enemies gaining an advantage to-hit, and they gain a passive +1 Melee Wound bonus.\n\nSpiked Monolith: The Warrior's armor is designed to punish those who get close. Any enemy that successfully strikes the Champion with an Unarmed attack, or Grapples them, automatically takes 8 Piercing Wounds from the jagged, barbed plate.\n\nUnholy Resilience: The dark gods do not allow their champion to fall easily. The Warrior is completely immune to the Frightened, Charmed, and Fatigued conditions. If an attack would reduce them to 0 Wounds, they may roll a Willpower(7+) test; on a success, they drop to 1 Wound instead and keep fighting.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBerzerker (Melee: Cost 1 Action): With ferocious but decisive strikes, the warrior loses any disadvantage on to-hit rolls for this turn. A successful strike causes normal 1d10 + 30 wounds plus an additional d10. On an unmodified 10, they deal normal plus 2d10 additional wounds.\n\nBoon of Ruin (Cost: 2 Actions): The Champion pauses to offer a bloody tribute to the dark gods. By actively destroying a fallen corpse on the battlefield (or sacrificing 5 of their own Wounds), the Champion's weapon erupts in dark energy, granting them Advantage on all Melee To-Hit rolls and +10 Wounds to all damage dealt until the end of their next turn.\n\nExecutioner's Cleave (Cost: 1 Action): A brutal, tactical swing with the dark iron greatsword. Make a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 30 Slashing/Necrotic Wounds and ignores 5 points of the target's WM-Arm.\n\nImpact (Melee Cost 2 Actions): Gripping their 2H weapon, they rear back with a powerful swing to stun their opponent. A successful hit deals normal 1d10 + 30 + 2x Physique(24) wounds, and causes 1 Stunned condition."
