      "None",
      "Crushing Jaws / Rending Claws",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nSilver Anathema: The Lycanthrope's ultimate weakness. Any attack made with a Silver weapon completely ignores the Werewolf's Armor Mitigation (dealing damage directly to Wounds). Furthermore, if the Werewolf takes damage from a Silver weapon, its Lycanthropic Vigor is entirely disabled for the rest of the round.\n\nLycanthropic Vigor: The beast's cursed blood rapidly knits flesh back together. At the start of its turn, if it has not taken damage from a Silver weapon in the previous round, it automatically heals 1d10 Wounds.\n\nScent of the Hunter: The Sun-Sentry has been magically engineered to detect threats to its master. It has automatic Advantage on any Awareness tests to detect sneaking enemies, and it can perfectly track invisible creatures within 60 feet by the scent of their sweat and heartbeat. It cannot be surprised.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBlood-Maddened Howl (Cost: 2 Actions): The Werewolf unleashes a terrifying, deafening howl that rattles the courage of anyone nearby. All enemies within a 40-foot radius must pass a Willpower(9) test. On a failure, they are inflicted with 1 Exhausted condition (as the adrenaline violently leaves their system in terror) and suffer Disadvantage on their next attack roll. If the Werewolf uses this while it is currently below half its maximum Wounds, the howl also summons 1d4 mundane wolves from the surrounding wilderness to join the fight on the next round.\n\nHelmet-Crushing Bite (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The werewolf locks its jaws onto a vital area. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 20 Piercing Wounds and completely ignores 5 points of the target's WM-Arm as the teeth puncture steel.\n\nProtector's Intercept (Melee Cost: 1 Action): This ability can be triggered at any time during an enemy's turn. If an enemy declares a physical attack against an allied creature (or an object, like the Vampire's coffin) within 30 feet, the Werewolf can instantly cross the distance, physically throwing itself in the way. The Werewolf takes the damage instead, and if the attacker is within melee range, the Werewolf immediately gets a free retaliation Melee attack (+4 To-Hit).\n\nSavage Disembowelment (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Werewolf lunges to tear into the softest parts of its prey. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 20 Melee Wounds, and the target must pass a severe Physique(11) test. On a failure, the target suffers 2 Bleeding conditions and drops whatever is in their hands as they clutch their ruined torso."
    ],
