      "The frozen, half-eaten corpses of past adventurers",
      "Rending Claws & Fangs",
      "Sub-Zero Gale",
      "Passive Traits\nSnow-Blind Stalker: The White Dragon ignores all visibility penalties from blizzards, fog, or darkness. Furthermore, it ignores Movement penalties on ice or deep snow, and can climb sheer vertical ice walls.\n\nFeral Bloodlust: Fighting entirely on emotion, if the White Dragon takes any Wounds during a round, it flies into a rage, automatically gaining Advantage on its first Melee attack during its next turn.\n\nIcebound Camouflage: When partially submerged in snow or pressed against a glacier, the dragon is effectively invisible. If it initiates combat from this state, it automatically wins the Initiative tie and its first attack completely ignores the target's Shield mitigation.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nGlacier Pounce (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The dragon leaps directly onto its prey. It moves up to 40 feet and makes a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 35 Wounds, and the target is forcefully knocked Prone and Grappled beneath its massive claws.\n\nSub-Zero Gale (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The dragon exhales a roaring, 40-foot cone of absolute-zero ice shards. Make a Ranged attack (+5 To-Hit). On a hit, targets take 3d10 + 20 Cold Wounds and have their Movement speed reduced to 0 on their next turn.\n\nThrashing Tail (Melee Cost: 1 Action): Operating on pure instinct to clear its flanks, the dragon violently thrashes its heavy tail. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit) against all enemies behind or beside the dragon. On a hit, targets take half Wounds 1d10 + 18) and are thrown 15 feet away."
