  {
    "values": [
      "Wight Grave Knight: The Crypt-Commander",
      "Medium",
      "Undead (Commander)",
      "",
      "“The eyes aren't feral; they are focused. It parries your strike not by instinct, but by memory. It remembers how you were taught to fight, and it remembers why those techniques fail against the dead.” A Grave Knight is a terrifying sight: a tall, skeletal figure clad in ancient, blackened plate armor etched with glowing necromantic runes. A tattered, burial-stained cloak flows behind them like smoke. Their helmet, often crowned with rusted iron spikes, houses two pinpricks of icy blue balefire that flicker with malevolent intelligence. While the Grave Guard skeletons they command are formidable, the Warden is the catalyst that makes them invincible. They carry a Warden’s Glaive or a heavy Soul-Mace, which they use to direct their troops with rhythmic, silent commands. They are the keepers of the gate between life and death, and they take their \"watch\" very personally.",
