    "values": [
      "Wither-Walker: The Blighted Sylvan",
      "Giant",
      "Plant / Undead",
      "",
      "A Wither-Walker stands 18 to 22 feet tall, appearing as a skeletal, humanoid tree. Its bark is a sickly, charcoal grey, weeping a thick, black sap that smells of ozone and vinegar. Its \"leaves\" are clusters of jagged obsidian shards and dried, razor-sharp briars. Moving with a slow, agonizing creak like a door being forced off its hinges, they are the ultimate \"Attrition\" bosses. They view all flesh-beings as parasites, turning the environment so toxic that victims simply collapse from exhaustion, ready to be mulched and fed to the dying forest.",
