      "Obsidian-Briar Boughs",
      "Volatile Sap-Glob. Hurls globs of acidic sap up to 60ft",
      "Passive Traits\nAura of the Blight: The Wither-Walker constantly radiates a suffocating, toxic miasma smelling of vinegar and ozone. Any enemy starting their turn within 30 feet of the Walker must pass a severe Physique(10) test. On a failure, they gain 1 Poison condition and 1 Exhausted condition as the toxic air burns their lungs and saps their stamina.\n\nWeeping Black Sap: The Walker’s charcoal bark constantly oozes thick, highly acidic sap. Any Melee attack made against the Walker with a physical weapon causes the sap to splash. The attacker automatically takes 1d10 Acid Wounds, and non-magical weapons suffer a permanent -1 to their damage output as the acid immediately begins eating the metal or wood.\n\nPetrified Undead Anatomy: As a fusion of dead wood and necromancy, the Walker is immune to Bleeding and takes only half Wounds from Piercing weapons. However, because its sap is highly volatile (smelling of ozone), any Fire-based attacks that hit the Walker deal double Wounds, but also cause the sap to explode, dealing 2d10 Fire Wounds to anyone within 10 feet of the Walker.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nObsidian-Briar Sweep (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Walker sweeps its massive, razor-sharp arms in a 20-foot frontal arc. It makes a single To-Hit roll (+6) against the Defense of all targets in the area. Anyone hit takes normal 1d10 + 40 melee Wounds and must pass an Agility(6) test or suffer 2 Bleeding conditions as the obsidian leaves flay their armor.\n\nFlesh into Mulch (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Walker attempts to grab an exhausted victim to feed the roots. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals no immediate Wounds, but the target is Grappled and lifted into the Walker's blighted, open trunk. At the start of the Walker's next turn, if the target has not broken free, they take 3d10 + 40 Acid Wounds, and the Walker heals Wounds equal to the damage dealt as it digests them.\n\nRoots of Attrition (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Walker violently plunges its arms into the ground, causing blackened, necrotic roots to erupt beneath up to 3 different targets within 60 feet. Make a Casting roll (+8 To-Cast). If successful, the targets take 1d10 + 35 Necrotic Wounds, have their Movement reduced to 0 for their next turn, and immediately lose 1 Focus or Reroll point (target's choice) as the roots drain their mental resolve."
    ],
