      "None",
      "Iron-Thorn Protrusions",
      "Darts, Wood Splinters",
      "Passive Traits\nPerfect Camouflage: When standing perfectly still against a tree trunk or within autumn foliage, the Sprite is indistinguishable from the environment. They automatically gain Advantage on all Ambush attacks against unsuspecting targets.\n\nHive-Mind of the Grove: The Sprites share a collective consciousness. If one Sprite is aware of a hidden enemy, all Sprites within 60 feet are instantly aware. They cannot be successfully flanked as long as another Sprite has line of sight.\n\nTinder-Dry: Because their bodies are composed of dried leaves and kindling, they possess a severe, lethal vulnerability to Fire. Any Fire damage they take completely ignores their WM-Arm and deals double Wounds.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nNeedle Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A sudden, vicious jab with their thorn-like limbs. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 5 Piercing Wounds.\n\nGuerrilla Fade (Cost: 1 Action): The Sprite instantly scuttles backward into the brush. It moves up to 15 feet without triggering any defensive or counter-attacks, allowing it to seamlessly merge back into the treeline after striking.\n\nRoot Cage (Cost: 2 Actions): The Sprite channels the grove's energy to manipulate the environment. Target one enemy within 30 feet. The ground beneath them animates, and the target must pass an Agility(6) test or gain the Restrained condition as heavy roots wrap around their ankles. They remain trapped until they use an Action to physically break the roots."
    ],
