    "values": [
      "Wraith: The Hollow-Champion",
      "Medium",
      "Undead / Incorporeal",
      "",
      "A Wraith appears as a tall, hooded silhouette of tattered, midnight-colored robes. Where a face should be, there is only an endless, swirling vacuum of smoke and two freezing white pinpricks of light. They carry the \"Echo\" of the weapon they wielded in life—a blade made of solidified shadow that doesn't cut the flesh so much as it severs the soul's connection to the body. They drift through solid stone walls and iron doors as if they were mist. The air around them drops to sub-zero temperatures, misting breath and withering plants. They do not just kill; they consume. A victim slain by a Wraith leaves no corpse for resurrection—their soul is pulled into the Wraith's hollow chest to fuel its dark power.",
