      "The \"Echo\" Blade (Solidified Shadow Weapon)",
      "Echo Blade (Targets the soul, not the body)",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nAura of the Grave-Chill: The Wraith projects a 20-foot aura of sub-zero temperatures. Any living creature that starts its turn within this aura takes 1d10 Cold Wounds and must pass a Willpower(10) test or suffer 1 Exhausted condition as the freezing air literally saps the warmth from their blood.\n\nConsume the Soul: The most terrifying mechanic in the Wraith's arsenal. If the Wraith reduces a target to 0 Wounds, it does not just kill them; it sucks their soul into its hollow chest. The Wraith instantly heals to its maximum Wounds. Furthermore, the slain target cannot be revived by normal resurrection magic—their soul is trapped. The party must destroy the Wraith within 24 hours to release the soul, or the party member is permanently erased from existence.\n\nIncorporeal Entity: The Wraith has no physical body. It takes only half Wounds from all non-magical physical weapons. It is completely immune to the Grappled, Prone, Bleeding, Poison, and Disease conditions. It can move its full Movement speed through solid walls, closed doors, and other creatures without penalty.\n\nSub-Zero Vacuum (Aura): The Wraith drains the ambient heat from the world. Any living creature that ends its turn within 15 feet of the Wraith takes 5 Cold Wounds and suffers a -1 penalty to their Agility as frost rimes their armor and joints.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nDissipate (Cost: 1 Action): The Wraith breaks apart into a cloud of freezing black smoke and instantly teleports up to 40 feet to an unoccupied space it can see, ignoring all defensive or counter-attacks.\n\nHollow Siphon(TN11) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Wraith reaches out with a spectral, freezing hand to drain the life force of a target within 30 feet. Make a Casting roll (+5 To-Cast). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 30 Necrotic Wounds. The target permanently loses 1 point of Willpower until they complete a long rest, and the Wraith heals Wounds equal to the damage dealt.\n\nPhase-Step Retreat (Cost: 1 Action): The Wraith instantly drops its physical manifestation, becoming pure smoke. It Disengages from all melee combat without triggering any free attacks, and instantly moves up to 30 feet directly through the nearest floor, ceiling, or wall, placing a solid barrier between itself and the party to wait for its cooldowns.\n\nSever the Soul (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Wraith swings its Echo Blade, aiming not for armor, but for the spirit. Make a Melee attack (+6 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 25 melee Wounds. Because the blade passes directly through physical matter, this attack completely ignores all Armor Wound Mitigation (using only the target's natural or magical mitigation)."
    ],
