      "Wyvern: The Sky-Scourge",
      "Giant",
      "Monstrosity (Reptilian / Aerial)",
      "",
      "A colossal reptilian predator with two powerful, clawed legs and a pair of vast, leathery wings serving as its forelimbs. Bred to a staggering Giant size, these specific Wyverns are exclusively claimed by Orc Warbosses as their personal mounts. Its most feared feature is its long, prehensile tail ending in a jagged, chitinous stinger dripping with a viscous, purple neurotoxin. It perfectly embodies the Orcish philosophy: loud, violent, and relentless. It dive-bombs enemy ranks, crushing entire phalanxes beneath its staggering mass, allowing the Warboss upon its back to shatter the survivor's morale. Its scent—rotting meat and acrid chemicals—is the terrifying herald of an approaching war-host.",
