      "Neurotoxic Stinger / Crushing Talons",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nAcrid Herald: The Wyvern absolutely reeks of rotting meat and chemical toxins. Any enemy that starts its turn within 20 feet of the Wyvern must pass a Physique(6) test or suffer 1 Exhausted condition from gagging on the foul stench, giving them Disadvantage on their next attack roll.\n\nAerial Launch: The Wyvern can use its powerful legs to vault directly into the air. It can Disengage from melee combat and launch into flight without triggering any free attacks of opportunity from engaged enemies.\n\nDive-Bomber's Momentum: If the Wyvern flies at least 30 feet directly downward toward a target before making a melee attack, it turns its massive weight into a weapon. It gains Advantage on its To-Hit roll, and a successful hit automatically bypasses the first 10 points of the target's Armor Mitigation.\n\nPrehensile Tail: The Wyvern’s stinger is incredibly long and dextrous. Its Melee attacks with the stinger have a 15-foot reach, allowing it to execute targets while hovering just out of sword-range, protecting its rider from melee reprisal.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nThe Sky-Crush (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Wyvern utilizes its signature dive-bomb maneuver. The Wyvern crashes into a 15-foot radius area on the ground. Make a single To-Hit roll (+4) against the Defense of all enemies in the impact zone. Anyone hit takes 2d10 + 50 melee Wounds and is violently knocked Prone and Stunned as the air is driven from their lungs by the beast's breastplate.\n\nNeurotoxic Execution (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Wyvern whips its prehensile tail around to sting a survivor. This attack gains Advantage if used against a Prone or Stunned target. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals half normal 1d10 + 25 Wounds, but injects a massive dose of purple neurotoxin. The target must pass a severe Physique(13) test or suffer 3 Poison conditions and become Paralyzed (Movement 0, Actions 0) for 1 round as their nervous system completely shuts down.\n\nSavage Talon Toss (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Wyvern attempts to grab a target in its talons and fling them aside to isolate the weakest prey. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 50 melee Wounds and the target is physically thrown 15 feet in a direction of the GM's choosing, taking an additional 1d10 blunt Wounds upon landing."
    ],
