      "Prismatic Claws & Fangs",
      "Resonant Spine-Burst. Shoots a focused beam of sonic energy up to 60ft",
      "Passive Traits\nPhotonic Resonance: The Xaver does not rely on normal vision. It detects the soul-light and movement of living beings. It is completely immune to the Blinded condition, magical darkness, and visual illusions. Furthermore, no living creature can benefit from Invisibility or Stealth while within 100 feet of the Xaver—it sees them perfectly.\n\nFiber-Optic Camouflage: The Xaver's diamond scales passively bend light around its body. Whenever the Xaver is not taking an Action, it is completely Invisible. Any Ranged attacks made against it while it is moving suffer Disadvantage. However, the moment it prepares to strike, its spines glow, briefly dropping the invisibility until its turn ends.\n\nHexapedal Sprint: The Xaver ignores all difficult terrain modifiers for rubble, underbrush, and steep inclines, effortlessly using its six legs to maintain its blistering 40 Movement speed.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nThe Humming Pounce (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Xaver sprints up to 30 feet and launches itself at a target. Make a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 25 melee Wounds. If the Xaver started this attack while Invisible, the sudden prismatic flash blinds the target's defenses, automatically bypassing all of the target's Armor Mitigation for this strike.\n\nShatter-Frequency (Cost: 2 Actions): The Xaver arches its back, and its crystalline spines violently vibrate, emitting a devastating sonic wave in a 30-foot radius. All enemies in the area must pass a severe Willpower(11) test. On a failure, they take 3d10 + 20 Sonic Wounds, gain 1 Stunned condition (from ruptured eardrums), and any fragile glass items they are carrying (like health potions or vials) instantly shatter and are destroyed.\n\nPrismatic Flay (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Xaver unleashes a flurry of strikes with its six clawed limbs. Make a Melee attack (+5 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 25 Wounds and the target must pass an Agility(8) test or suffer 2 Bleeding conditions as the diamond-hard claws effortlessly shred through leather and flesh."
