      "None",
      "Obsidian Jaws & Titan Tail",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nCold-Blooded Hive-Mind: Xochitonal projects a telepathic command aura over all reptiles, amphibians, and serpentine beasts within a 1-mile radius. In combat, any allied cold-blooded creature within 100 feet of Xochitonal gains automatic Advantage on all their To-Hit rolls, and Xochitonal can perceive the battlefield perfectly through their eyes.\n\nWarden of the Threshold: As a cosmic guardian, Xochitonal cannot be banished, teleported, or moved against its will by any magical or physical force. It is completely immune to mind-altering effects (like Charm or Fear) and ignores any environmental penalties associated with water or mud.\n\nSun-Blood Glyphs: The turquoise glyphs etched into its obsidian scales pulse with intense thermal energy. Any Melee attack made against Xochitonal with a physical weapon causes the glyphs to flare, instantly dealing 1d10 Fire Wounds back to the attacker and passively illuminating any Invisible or Stealthed enemies within 30 feet.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nThe Soul-Anchor Bite (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The most feared mechanic in Xochitonal's arsenal. Make a Melee attack (+8 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 165 melee Wounds. The massive obsidian teeth physically tether the victim's soul to the ground they are standing on. The target is permanently inflicted with the Soul-Anchored condition: they cannot move more than 30 feet from the spot they were bitten, they cannot use teleportation magic to flee, and if they are reduced to 0 Wounds while anchored, their soul is instantly pulled into the eternal dark, making them completely immune to all resurrection magic short of a divine wish.\n\nCrushing River-Fist(TN12) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): Xochitonal commands the very water of its domain to rise up and strike. Make a Casting roll (+6 To-Cast) against up to 3 different targets within 100 feet. On a success, the water forms massive, pressurized fists that crash down, dealing 1d10 + 40 Bludgeoning Wounds. Targets hit must pass a severe Physique(11) test or be knocked Prone and gain 1 Stunned condition from the sheer weight of the river.\n\nDeath-Roll Annihilation (Cost: 2 Actions): This brutal execution move can only be used on a target that is currently Prone or Grappled. Xochitonal bites down and violently spins its 40-foot body. Make a Melee attack (+8 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 3d10 + 65 Wounds, instantly shreds any physical armor the target is wearing (permanently reducing their Armor Mitigation to 0 for the remainder of the battle), and inflicts 2 Bleeding conditions."
    ],
