      "None. Relies on massive fists and environmental debris.",
      "Simian Fists & Fangs",
      "Hurled Ice Chunks. Throws heavy debris up to 60ft",
      "Passive Traits\nGhost of the Glacier: The Yeti is completely immune to Cold/Ice damage and all weather-related Movement penalties (deep snow, slick ice, etc.). Furthermore, its pristine white fur provides perfect camouflage. When in a snowy environment, the Yeti gains automatic Advantage on all Stealth tests, and any Ranged attacks made against it from further than 30 feet suffer Disadvantage due to the optical illusion of the snow blending with its fur.\n\nHypothermic Grip: The Yeti's body temperature is supernaturally cold to the touch. Any creature that is currently Grappled by the Yeti automatically suffers 1d10 Cold Wounds and 1 Exhausted condition at the start of their turn as the beast's freezing fur rapidly saps their body heat.\n\nSnowdrift Ambush: The Yeti can use 1 Action to perfectly bury itself in deep snow. While buried, it is completely undetectable by non-magical means. If an enemy walks within 10 feet of the buried Yeti, it can instantly erupt from the snow, gaining a free Surprise Action before Initiative is rolled.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nSavage Pummel (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Yeti brings its massive, heavy fists down like sledgehammers. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 25 melee Wounds, and the target must pass a severe Physique(11) test or suffer 1 Stunned condition from the sheer concussive force of the blow.\n\nWhiteout Roar (Cost: 2 Actions): The Yeti beats its chest and unleashes a deafening roar that literally calls the storm down. A 40-foot radius around the Yeti instantly becomes a howling vortex of snow and wind for 1 round. All enemies within the radius are permanently Blinded to anything further than 5 feet away while inside the storm, and must pass a Willpower(8) test or drop their weapons as they cover their ears against the deafening noise.\n\nThe Spine-Breaker (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Yeti attempts to grab an enemy in a horrifying bear-hug. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, the target is Grappled and lifted off the ground. The Yeti deals 2d10 + 25 Wounds as it violently compresses the target's ribcage. If the target is wearing physical armor, the sheer pressure buckles the metal, permanently reducing the target's Armor Mitigation by 5."
