      "Scimitar & Fangs",
      "Venom Spit. Shoots a concentrated stream of acid/venom up to 40ft",
      "Passive Traits\nThe Emotionless Void: Because the Yuan-ti are biologically incapable of empathy or fear, they are completely immune to the Charmed, Fear, and Taunted conditions. Any illusion or spell that relies on manipulating the target's emotions automatically fails against them.\n\nSerpent's Thermoreception: The Abomination has heat-sensing pits along its jawline. It perceives the thermal signatures of living creatures, allowing it to see perfectly in magical darkness and completely ignore Invisibility as long as the invisible creature emits body heat.\n\nSurgical Precision: The Yuan-ti never wastes an opening. Any time the Abomination makes an attack against a target that is currently suffering from Poison, Stunned, or Grappled, its attacks automatically bypass half of the target's Armor Mitigation.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nThe Whisper Over the Fang(TN11) (Casting Cost: 2 Actions): The Yuan-ti's eyes flash with a hypnotic, prismatic light as it speaks a soothing, magically laced command into a target's mind. Make a Casting roll (+5 To-Cast) against the Willpower of a target within 60 feet. On a success, the target's mind is subverted: they must use their Reaction (or their very next turn) to make a full physical attack against their closest ally, dealing an additional 2d10 psychic Wounds from the mental violation.\n\nNeurotoxic Strike (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Abomination lashes out with its venom-coated scimitar or fangs. Make a Melee attack (+3 To-Hit). If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 25 Wounds and the target must pass a severe Physique(11) test. On a failure, they suffer 2 Poison conditions and become Blinded by the neurotoxin for 1 round, making them easy prey for the rest of the serpent brood.\n\nCrushing Coils (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Abomination whips its massive serpentine lower body around a target. Make a Melee attack (+8 To-Hit). If successful, the target takes 2d10 + 20 Wounds and is Grappled (Movement reduced to 0). While a target is Grappled this way, the Yuan-ti can use a free action at the start of its subsequent turns to automatically squeeze them for 2d10 crushing Wounds as long as the hold isn't broken."
    ],
