      "None",
      "Pressurized Blades",
      "",
      "Passive Traits\nAmorphous Colossus: The Greater Zephyr can move through solid structures by simply eroding them. Because it has no solid body, it is completely immune to the Grappled and Prone conditions, and takes exactly half damage from all non-magical Piercing and Bludgeoning weapons (cannonballs and greatswords simply pass through the funnel).\n\nHurricane Wall: The air surrounding the Zephyr is a chaotic shield. Any Ranged attack made against the Zephyr or any creature hiding behind the Zephyr automatically suffers Disadvantage, as the wind rips the projectiles off course.\n\nThe Razor's Edge: Wind finds the gaps in every defense. All Melee attacks made by the Zephyr completely ignore up to 15 points of the target's WM-Arm (Armor Mitigation), as the pressurized air cuts perfectly between armor plates.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nBasic Ranged Attack\nRanged Details: Centrifugal Ejection. Range 200 ft. Base +20 Bludgeoning/Slashing Wounds.\n\nBallistic Shrapnel (Range Cost: 2 Actions): The Zephyr focuses its rotation to eject a massive object—a shattered wagon, a boulder, or a suit of jagged plate armor—at a specific target. Make a Ranged attack (+2 To-Hit) against a target within 120 feet. On a hit, the target takes 1d10 + 35 Bludgeoning/Slashing Wounds and must pass a Physique(10) test or be violently knocked Prone by the staggering impact.\n\nF5 Cleave (Melee Cost: 1 Action): A sudden, massive sweep of pressurized air that acts like an invisible guillotine. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit) with a 20-foot reach. If successful, it deals 1d10 + 32 Slashing Wounds.\n\nEye of the Storm (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Greater Zephyr moves directly into the space of its enemies, pulling them into the sky. All creatures within the Zephyr's massive space (a 20-foot radius) must pass a Physique(10) test. On a failure, they take 40 Bludgeoning/Slashing Wounds, are violently lifted 30 feet into the air, and thrown 20 feet outward (taking standard fall damage and gaining the Prone condition upon landing and taking additional 3d10 wounds).\n\nCatastrophic Slipstream (Cost: 1 Action): The Zephyr violently shifts its path. It instantly moves up to 40 feet in a straight line without triggering any defensive or counter-attacks. Any enemy or structure it passes through during this movement automatically takes 15 Slashing Wounds."
    ],
