      "Sand-Whip",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nAmorphous Form: The Dust-Devil can move through gaps as small as 1 inch wide without squeezing. Because it has no solid body, it is completely immune to the Grappled and Prone conditions, and takes exactly half damage from all non-magical Piercing and Bludgeoning weapons.\n\nAbrasive Draft: While they cannot cleanly slice through plate armor like a true Zephyr, their spinning grit finds exposed joints. All Melee attacks made by the Dust-Devil ignore 5 points of the target's WM-Arm (Armor Mitigation).\n\nViolent Dispersion: When a Dust-Devil is reduced to 0 Wounds, its elemental core breaks. It instantly detonates in a localized burst of wind. All adjacent creatures must pass a Physique test or be pushed 5 feet away.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nGrit Lash (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The funnel whips a pressurized arc of sharp sand at an enemy. Make a Melee attack (+2 To-Hit). If successful, it deals 1d10 + 6 Slashing Wounds.\n\nChoking Swarm (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Dust-Devil moves directly into the space of a Medium or smaller creature, filling their eyes and lungs with dirt. The target must pass a Physique(5) test. On a failure, they take 8 Bludgeoning Wounds and gain the Blinded condition for 1 round.\n\nScattering Breeze (Cost: 1 Action): The Dust-Devil instantly scatters into the wind and reforms a short distance away. It moves up to 20 feet without triggering any defensive or counter-attacks."
