      "Pressurized Air-Blades",
      "Vacuum Blades. Hurls crescent waves of sharp wind up to 80ft",
      "Passive Traits\nAmorphous Gale: The Zephyr has no true physical form. It takes only half Wounds from all non-magical Piercing, Slashing, and Bludgeoning weapons. It is completely immune to the Prone, Grappled, and Bleeding conditions. It can move through gaps as narrow as one inch wide without penalty.\n\nCyclone Aura: The air immediately surrounding the Zephyr is a blender of debris and pressurized wind. Any enemy that ends its turn within 5 feet of the Zephyr automatically takes 5 Slashing Wounds.\n\nTailwind & Headwind: The Zephyr constantly manipulates the air pressure around it. Any Ranged weapon attack (arrows, bolts) made against the Zephyr or an ally within 10 feet of it suffers Disadvantage, as the wind knocks the projectiles off course. Conversely, the Zephyr's own Ranged attacks completely ignore any penalties from cover or distance.\n\nVolatile Element: While highly resistant to physical blows, the Zephyr is highly reactive to opposing elements. Any Earth or Lightning-based attacks that successfully hit the Zephyr deal double Wounds as the dirt clogs its vortex or the lightning ionizes its core.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nInvisible Cleave (Range Cost: 1 Action): The Zephyr rapidly pressurizes the air into a razor-sharp crescent. Make a Ranged attack (+4 To-Hit) against a target within 80 feet. If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 25 Wounds. Because the blade is invisible, the target cannot use shields or defensive Reactions to block or mitigate this specific attack.\n\nSuffocating Vacuum (Melee Cost: 2 Actions): The Zephyr attempts to envelope a target within its central vortex. Make a Melee attack (+4 To-Hit). If successful, the target takes 2d10 + 15 Wounds and is immediately Silenced (cannot cast spells with verbal components) and suffers 1 Exhausted condition as the oxygen is instantly ripped from their lungs.\n\nViolent Updraft (Cost: 2 Actions): The Zephyr swoops beneath a target and erupts upward. The target must pass a severe Physique(9) test. On a failure, they take no immediate Wounds, but are violently launched 30 feet straight up into the air. If they cannot fly, they immediately fall, taking 3d10 falling Wounds and landing Prone."
