      "Rotting Hands & Teeth",
      "None",
      "Passive Traits\nDead-Flesh Sponge: Because they lack functioning organs or a nervous system, the Zombie takes only half Wounds from Piercing (arrows, rapiers) and Blunt (maces, hammers) weapons, as the blows just sink harmlessly into dead meat. They take normal Wounds from Slashing weapons (which dismember them) and double Wounds from Fire or Holy magic.\n\nUndead Fortitude: The dark magic animating the corpse is incredibly stubborn. If a Zombie is reduced to 0 Wounds by any damage type other than Fire, Holy, or a deliberate Slashing decapitation, it has a 50% chance to simply stand back up at the start of its next turn with 10 Wounds, continuing its relentless pursuit.\n\nThe Suffocating Horde: Zombies become exponentially more dangerous in numbers. If a Zombie starts its turn adjacent to at least two other allied Zombies, the sheer momentum of the swarm grants it +1 Action for that turn.\n\nAction-Based Abilities\nDead-Weight Grapple (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Zombie lunges with both arms, attempting to drag its prey down. Make a Melee attack. If successful, it deals 0 Wounds, but the target is Grappled (Movement reduced to 0). For every Zombie currently grappling the same target, the target suffers a cumulative -2 penalty to their Agility and Physique tests to break free.\n\nInfectious Bite (Melee Cost: 1 Action): The Zombie attempts to sink its festering teeth into exposed flesh. Make a Melee attack (+1 To-Hit). This attack automatically gains Advantage if the target is currently Grappled. If successful, it deals normal 1d10 + 7 biting Wounds, and the target must pass a Physique(5) test. On a failure, they contract The Rot, a disease condition that completely prevents all magical healing until cured, and inflicts 10 Wounds every hour as the infection spreads.\n\nBile Burst (Reaction): When the Zombie is finally destroyed (reduced to 0 Wounds and fails its Undead Fortitude check), its bloated stomach violently ruptures. Any creature within 5 feet must pass an Agility(6) test or gain 1 Poison condition and take 1d10 Acid Wounds from the spraying, necrotic fluids."
